    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES GROWTH&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sales growth" refers to the increase in sales over a specific period, often measured as a percentage increase from one period to the next. In a specific example, overall sales growth was calculated as $238,500/$200,000, resulting in a +19.25% increase. However, it is noted that sales in the female hairdressing sector have fallen by 15%, calculated as ($200,000 - $170,000)/$200,000.</data>
      <data key="d2">75aa284e3bf8d3b64f3e1feff1c7b3fb,f41491fbf8c72d2afdc444dec24f9e1e</data>
      <data key="d7">23</data>
