    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHALLENGES AND RISKS OF BIG DATA&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Despite the benefits, there are potential dangers and drawbacks of using big data, including cost, time and staff resources, regulation, loss and theft of data, incorrect data, and overfitting."</data>
      <data key="d2">0300615aebb7ef4e2e5e1ed830623ea3</data>
      <data key="d3">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">83</data>
      <data key="d6">fbeef791d19b413a9c93c6608286ab63</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;USES OF BIG DATA AND DATA ANALYTICS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Big data and data analytics are used by companies like Netflix, Amazon, British Airways, and Target to predict customer preferences, personalize marketing, plan routes, and offer targeted discounts."</data>
      <data key="d2">0300615aebb7ef4e2e5e1ed830623ea3</data>
      <data key="d3">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">84</data>
      <data key="d6">d2b629c0396f4180a03e16ddf3818589</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;IMPORTANCE OF DATA VISUALISATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Data visualisation is the display of information graphically, using various forms such as charts, graphs, and maps. It aims to present data in a form that is easy to understand and analyse, summarising big data in a way that even non-technical users may understand."</data>
      <data key="d2">0300615aebb7ef4e2e5e1ed830623ea3</data>
