    <node id="&quot;OPERATIONAL EFFICIENCY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"OPERATIONAL EFFICIENCY" is the ability to deliver products or services in the most cost-effective manner without compromising quality. It is a key factor in achieving profitability and sustainability. Analytical findings can provide operational efficiency to enhance decision-making and performance management.</data>
      <data key="d2">0300615aebb7ef4e2e5e1ed830623ea3,a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">90</data>
      <data key="d6">89c08e793298442686292454a1abff31</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERFORMANCE MEASUREMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Performance Measurement" is the process of evaluating how effectively an organization achieves its objectives, using both financial and non-financial performance indicators. It involves assessing the efficiency and effectiveness of a production system through various metrics and indicators. Performance measurement shows how well an organization achieves its stated objectives, ranking these objectives from the mission level to lower-level goals. Analytical findings derived from performance measurement can enhance decision-making and performance management.</data>
      <data key="d2">0300615aebb7ef4e2e5e1ed830623ea3,1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37,3b375b22ae26edc86618262ee6ace048,3c3175f58893c9a4a545210c49b7c25f</data>
      <data key="d7">4</data>
