    <node id="&quot;COST ALLOCATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Cost allocation is the process of assigning indirect costs to different cost objects, such as products, departments, or projects."</data>
      <data key="d2">508d94702ceaf4b2c327ad21bf49dba3,e63689f85598b937bf7c871cd9494956</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">153</data>
      <data key="d6">87915637da3e474c9349bd0ae604bd95</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COST OBJECT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">A cost object is any item for which a separate measurement of cost is desired. Examples of cost objects include products, services, departments, and projects.</data>
