      <data key="d5">246</data>
      <data key="d6">222f0ea8a5684123a7045986640ec844</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FACTORY HOUR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Factory Hour is a measure of the time a factory or production line is available for production."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">247</data>
      <data key="d6">668cf1fdfd644d39acc6350b86117ea2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RETURN PER FACTORY HOUR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Return per Factory Hour" is a metric used to determine the profitability of products based on the time they spend in the production process. It is calculated as the throughput per unit divided by the hours of bottleneck resource used per unit.</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37,ad658b0aa1714f3d42793f96dd88140e</data>
      <data key="d7">26</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">248</data>
      <data key="d6">478e4c72d8fb46dd8cc9f0691c9878fd</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OPTIMUM PRODUCT MIX&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Optimum Product Mix" refers to the combination of products that maximizes profitability within the constraints of the production process. Specifically, it is the combination that maximizes net profit given the limitations of production capacity and bottlenecks. In practical terms, this involves producing and selling product B up to its maximum demand and then utilizing the remaining capacity to produce product A.</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37,727bae9b2b77a13f165dd415aa129b20</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">249</data>
      <data key="d6">82b0446e7c9d4fc793f7b97f890e9049</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONSTRAINT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Constraint is any factor that limits the performance of a system and restricts its output."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">250</data>
      <data key="d6">8169efeea3ce473d9fd2f1c688126a1c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NON-BOTTLENECK RESOURCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Non-Bottleneck Resource is a part of the production process that has more capacity than the bottleneck and does not limit the overall output."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">251</data>
      <data key="d6">c2d48b75af6a4d7989ccf9eceabd934e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THROUGHPUT PER BOTTLENECK HOUR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Throughput per Bottleneck Hour is a measure of the throughput generated for each hour the bottleneck resource is utilized."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">252</data>
      <data key="d6">5f1fc373a8f34050a5f7dbd8ac852c1b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES REVENUE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">Sales Revenue is the income generated from selling goods or services before any costs or expenses are deducted. It serves as a primary indicator of business performance and is used to assess profitability and growth. The total revenue generated from sales is $9.20 per customer.</data>
      <data key="d2">00157cf30936c417d0c54f1dfce77654,002794ec024434f7ac2bd26217b3897d,01294aa83ab1143451866d43087f9eba,01d1ff33e985b6f8cd09ff45ebfedc0e,026b22934152d61a6b625fae071b3bcd,0279d26139c7d66d51896f7ebfe162ee,02defdad562458f44c0d0fa31dc9693d,03721d9b5064cc002df514cca9896c3b,039a2a6ce8c94f49aa8954c72332cea2,05e25a78a53e695fd01856df3a302292,0622f4f26dbe7479c871198b2e72b940,078e47b3223db97709a37da2a01302c5,08f6c24c7f87b7ffc3b8a5dfc505c552,0a1392ec8d4dc63bfee377dc6d552da3,0af2d78ba77677f806a697c0deb0ced3,0cafbc1007afddae5f416e6fb910386a,0d6ca97290394110da0bcfffa12dac11,0dbbae65ee89b4c5d53a1b0a83d84535,0e0632925a4598cac64c13be234f1755,0f59fe901f330c6a95c810cdae18b305,10a6cfb7beb226418463ca4749be7451,1198b5b37a51d0315db68af2bdb139bd,11b64c42e42e94e3f0881a9cd9457d74,122be7bb4778bacae6dba8d18b50c025,12bf561fb0f443af5c38c4055dae476d,14d295eb69556ed8203b13909d341a07,158846b2d51075f1de4279110c7a2ae1,16965b8a36bbe6bac45c7b81a6b17c48,181a68483be6482e8b136a2d540875a9,185572ab91ea67a36a262b55dffde450,1872b59f14e8fe91c616b29960e49fb9,19092af48cfe51bac1503c304f3ca707,1aa84a5288fe62c1d778b9f9013d51c3,1c07f0d21b37bda63c238ee6e4ed571b,1d33c979d505d0dcd027d816d2ab2695,1dbcdd2207ed07f8e45dc35658ecbd2a,1e37a7be9b892b604c2e7b6cf6a2c49f,1f06696499d837582d3dac671cb07649,1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37,2154b2cf6113011b3816974155d6ed8d,2207ef547588f07b856f3a5c961e39a0,22f7850b6ee24babd9cf367c0fc478a4,2343dedcae64d2e174ab981dfc3b23a0,2381a9a278f9cf058d7c71932fad4841,238ba7ae5def49a914d13c1bcf1e1332,24cd8c3feefdefe57b7e7da7db59d031,258563e1a008a7977296119e059fdf11,27370737012393c709c89a56df8ea2d4,27fde199847b14399dfca384e07a77a4,2922f29fc45ffc98655fc81f9a40fa79,299f4bc827fb4c62a74f3271557514e9,2a57a845054dd3fd23f0910ad239a201,2ad6c0ee81f4b0da1c6b2f2821dff6b6,2b35add90aa38f95a0510f9302a559f9,2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a,2ec07a1112223c3286057400e3b2eca9,2f4d122e57ceca3100dab3886c99ca27,2fd1d6134ec72f26d7a900391b7261fd,303f0ef8328d2aefc4bfae1067a85f72,30748d6dcf5a2da70804db75296cee3c