      <data key="d7">14</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">253</data>
      <data key="d6">0c010fa3aeac4b28b2fbb8c2339c2521</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DIRECT MATERIAL COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Direct Material Costs are the expenses directly associated with the production of goods, such as raw materials."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">254</data>
      <data key="d6">c2999bdca08a478b84b10219875b285e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FIXED COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Fixed Costs" are expenses that do not change with the level of production or sales. These costs remain constant regardless of the business activity level and include items such as rent, salaries, heat and power costs, fixed machine costs, depreciation, and insurance costs. While fixed costs are generally irrelevant to decision-making unless there is an incremental step in the fixed cost, they can be considered in decision-making when they can be avoided or reduced as a result of the decision.</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37,23de7e5f5aa4638cfdebaec8afd6c5de,27b66fcc5173aa41f6af55ff955c7910,2b7c12bc08e4dff98f807210499e82ee,5c4312b5c5c803bc38cc120660340db3,98d761e221e6915f156753807cb8fbe1,e77413580f69933c7e20f96d9b9b60cf</data>
      <data key="d7">14</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">7</data>
      <data key="d5">255</data>
      <data key="d6">263d07354a1b4336b462024288f9bcd3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PROFITABILITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">Profitability is the ability of a company to generate income relative to its revenue, expenses, and other costs. It is a key indicator of financial health and long-term sustainability. Additionally, profitability refers to the company's capacity to generate profit from its operations.</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37,a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">256</data>
      <data key="d6">f9005e5c01b44bb489f7112322fd1162</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EFFICIENCY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"EFFICIENCY" is a component of Value for Money (VFM) that examines the relationship between resources used and the output of goods and services, focusing on the cost-effectiveness of operations. In a business context, efficiency refers to the ability to achieve maximum productivity with minimum wasted effort or expense, making it a key factor in improving profitability and sustainability. It involves producing the desired output with the minimum amount of input, such as time, materials, and labor. Efficiency links inputs and outputs and considers whether the maximum outputs are obtained given the level of inputs.</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37,3d86fa6cff193e8919165e686b8e6427,963bb5be84f30224d6e25ea423602dfd,a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">5</data>
      <data key="d5">257</data>
      <data key="d6">d9ef017549724f4fbc4ff4ba6701dac0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRODUCTIVITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Productivity is the measure of the efficiency of production, often expressed as the ratio of output to input."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">258</data>
      <data key="d6">33b9e826af3f43838c07c847b6349497</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RESOURCE UTILIZATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Resource Utilization" is a dimension of Fitzgerald and Moon's Building Block Model that measures how effectively a company's resources, particularly staff, are used. It encompasses the extent to which resources such as labor and machinery are utilized effectively. Additionally, resource utilization evaluates various aspects of business activity, including non-productive time, hours of operation with no customers, and the number of meals served per seat.</data>
      <data key="d2">05e25a78a53e695fd01856df3a302292,1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37,e7d75450db353b8413fb68bdd98ac99c</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">259</data>
      <data key="d6">dbe9063124d047dc8d6fcaeadcda038f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CAPACITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Capacity is the maximum output that a production system can achieve under normal conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">260</data>
      <data key="d6">c885166d0c454a748376b56279f96408</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LEAD TIME&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Lead Time is the total time it takes from the initiation of a process to its completion, including production and delivery."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">261</data>
      <data key="d6">586bccefb1e344289c1ee984e165de9c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CYCLE TIME&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Cycle Time is the time it takes to complete one cycle of a production process from start to finish."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">262</data>
      <data key="d6">a2201b8753ba4847ab0b22054e27d2c0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BOTTLENECK ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bottleneck Analysis is the process of identifying and analyzing the bottleneck in a production system to improve overall performance."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">263</data>
      <data key="d6">b5ecd0553dd742f5813c9b855d548a41</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONSTRAINT ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Constraint Analysis is the process of identifying and managing constraints in a system to optimize performance."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">264</data>
      <data key="d6">89b2003e97804961805ea1886d078ebd</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRODUCTION SCHEDULING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Production Scheduling is the process of planning and organizing the production process to ensure efficient use of resources and timely delivery of products."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">265</data>
      <data key="d6">6dd7f5f6b4544271a97f6a136f82fc3d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RESOURCE ALLOCATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Resource Allocation" is the process of assigning available resources to various tasks and activities to optimize production and achieve business goals. It involves distributing financial, human, and material resources to various projects or departments. Effective allocation is crucial for achieving sustainability goals and optimizing performance. The process aims to distribute available resources among various uses in an optimal way.</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37,853d45efddaa3a59672a25aa124ddf0b,8f4de102f0f6dd238b08498336b2ce30,a5a7a3e9a59209ce811c1f9470684fa6,a8e02bf8056e93a035c9327f23da7d38,a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">266</data>
      <data key="d6">eb01db8435554f2cbafe39a50f62f20a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PROCESS OPTIMIZATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Process Optimization is the practice of improving production processes to increase efficiency, reduce costs, and enhance product quality."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">267</data>
      <data key="d6">3d175ad1f0014cd4871eff4e86db9f88</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LEAN MANUFACTURING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Lean Manufacturing is a production philosophy that focuses on minimizing waste and maximizing value by continuously improving processes."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">268</data>
      <data key="d6">c8e706fbdc90420d952deed03c4f04b4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SIX SIGMA&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Six Sigma is a data-driven methodology for improving quality by identifying and eliminating defects in production processes."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">269</data>
      <data key="d6">cf6115e69d6649cc99ef2bd11854ccfb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;KAIZEN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Kaizen is a Japanese term meaning 'continuous improvement,' and it involves making small, incremental changes to improve processes over time."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">270</data>
      <data key="d6">9ed7e3d187b94ab0a90830b17d66615e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;JUST-IN-TIME (JIT)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Just-in-Time (JIT) is a production strategy that aims to reduce inventory and increase efficiency by producing goods only as they are needed."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">271</data>
      <data key="d6">b4c7432f712849d7aba9dccbb77471ef</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TOTAL QUALITY MANAGEMENT (TQM)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">Total Quality Management (TQM) is a management approach focused on improving the quality of products, processes, and services through continuous improvement and the active involvement of all employees in quality initiatives.</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37,24cd8c3feefdefe57b7e7da7db59d031</data>
      <data key="d7">22</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">272</data>
      <data key="d6">434e752b992c4e6a812557529315c5b9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VALUE STREAM MAPPING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Value Stream Mapping is a visual tool used in Lean Manufacturing to analyze and design the flow of materials and information required to bring a product to the customer."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">273</data>
      <data key="d6">df79a27b9a4f42fd839c90bb8a79ad91</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Root Cause Analysis is a problem-solving method used to identify the underlying causes of defects or issues in a production process."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">274</data>
      <data key="d6">8f140fd7126f47b6b00307b0181509f9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PARETO ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Pareto Analysis is a statistical technique used to identify the most significant factors contributing to a problem, based on the Pareto Principle (80/20 rule)."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">275</data>
      <data key="d6">40450f2c91944a81944621b94f190b49</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FISHBONE DIAGRAM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Fishbone Diagram, also known as an Ishikawa or cause-and-effect diagram, is a tool used to identify the root causes of a problem by categorizing potential causes."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">276</data>
      <data key="d6">5b9fa6a959294dc29c8420b2d7d3096f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;5 WHYS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The 5 Whys is a problem-solving technique that involves asking 'why' five times to drill down to the root cause of a problem."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">277</data>
      <data key="d6">b84d71ed9c3b45819eb3205fd28e13a0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PDCA CYCLE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The PDCA Cycle (Plan-Do-Check-Act) is a four-step model for continuous improvement in business processes."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">278</data>
      <data key="d6">b0b464bc92a541e48547fe9738378dab</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GEMBA WALK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Gemba Walk is a practice where managers go to the 'Gemba' (the place where work is done) to observe processes and identify opportunities for improvement."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">279</data>
      <data key="d6">44c65dda6fb7472dae36f6eea720ab47</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;KANBAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Kanban is a visual scheduling system used in Lean Manufacturing to manage work and inventory at every stage of production."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">280</data>
      <data key="d6">5d97ff82691c4482973d73d1860e4757</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;5S&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"5S is a workplace organization method that uses five Japanese words: Seiri (Sort), Seiton (Set in order), Seiso (Shine), Seiketsu (Standardize), and Shitsuke (Sustain)."</data>
      <data key="d2">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">281</data>
      <data key="d6">2567445079794d1e84f17abc48776002</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INTERPRETING TPAR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"TPAR is interpreted as follows: If TPAR &gt; 1, the product is profitable as the throughput contribution exceeds the fixed costs. If TPAR = 1, the product breaks even. If TPAR &lt; 1, the product is loss-making as the throughput contribution does not cover the fixed costs required to make it."</data>
      <data key="d2">ad658b0aa1714f3d42793f96dd88140e</data>
      <data key="d3">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d7">26</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">282</data>
      <data key="d6">392be891f8b649fabdc20e7bf549f669</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WAYS TO IMPROVE TPAR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Ways to improve TPAR include eliminating bottlenecks or reducing the time spent on bottleneck resources, reducing other factory costs, increasing selling prices, or reducing material costs. However, increasing selling prices may not be feasible in a competitive environment, and reducing material costs may affect quality."</data>
      <data key="d2">ad658b0aa1714f3d42793f96dd88140e</data>
      <data key="d3">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d7">26</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">283</data>
      <data key="d6">0111777c4e9e4260ab2e5ddea7cbcf58</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ENVIRONMENTAL ISSUES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Environmental issues include global warming caused by greenhouse gas emissions, depletion of global reserves of scarce natural resources, and pollution and rising sea levels causing loss of habitats for many species."</data>
      <data key="d2">ad658b0aa1714f3d42793f96dd88140e</data>
      <data key="d3">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">284</data>
      <data key="d6">785f7f32471c439e89601ab81c828d1d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;IMPORTANCE OF THE ENVIRONMENT FOR BUSINESS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The importance of the environment for business includes the impact of poor environmental behavior on an organization's image, potential loss of sales due to customer boycotts, and heavy fines imposed by governments for harming the environment."</data>
      <data key="d2">ad658b0aa1714f3d42793f96dd88140e</data>
      <data key="d3">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">285</data>
      <data key="d6">6768339b54084020aec27adcef8994ff</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ENVIRONMENTAL BEHAVIOUR AND PERFORMANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Environmental behavior and performance can improve a company's performance by becoming more aware of its impact on the environment. Poor environmental behavior can harm an organization's image, leading to a loss of sales, and governments may impose heavy fines on companies that harm the environment."</data>
      <data key="d2">ad658b0aa1714f3d42793f96dd88140e</data>
      <data key="d3">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">286</data>
      <data key="d6">f09f381c319f4251847d1a4bb8cdcac1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COST PER FACTORY HOUR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Cost per factory hour is calculated as Other factory costs divided by Bottleneck resource hours available."</data>
      <data key="d2">ad658b0aa1714f3d42793f96dd88140e</data>
      <data key="d7">26</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">287</data>
      <data key="d6">eec11f567e7f4943b157c3a657eb9a46</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THROUGHPUT PER UNIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Throughput per unit" is calculated as the selling price of a product minus the total variable costs associated with producing one unit of the product. This includes subtracting the direct materials cost from the selling price to determine the throughput per unit.</data>
      <data key="d2">ac68069ef08bb5822225377a605ac206,ad658b0aa1714f3d42793f96dd88140e</data>
      <data key="d7">26</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">288</data>
      <data key="d6">efef117839b64ce9adf614a461d41ba6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BOTTLENECK RESOURCE HOURS AVAILABLE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bottleneck resource hours available refers to the total hours available for the bottleneck process in a given period."</data>
      <data key="d2">ad658b0aa1714f3d42793f96dd88140e</data>
      <data key="d7">26</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">289</data>
      <data key="d6">2171091ada0942d8ae7944df11659f6e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OTHER FACTORY COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Other factory costs include all fixed and variable costs associated with running the factory, excluding direct material costs."</data>
      <data key="d2">ad658b0aa1714f3d42793f96dd88140e</data>
      <data key="d7">26</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">290</data>
      <data key="d6">bcfdc48e5f044e1d84c5d217c1992d4b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUSTAINABILITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sustainability" is defined as meeting the needs of the present without compromising the ability of future generations to meet their own needs. This concept emphasizes the importance of long-term environmental, social, and economic health. It is both a challenge and an opportunity for organizations.</data>
      <data key="d2">421ca5734d703d01e7e43fa8cb11733f,a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">291</data>
      <data key="d6">b232fb0f2ac14790b931d1e7fcddd8ad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sustainable development requires organizations to consider the long-term consequences of their decisions. It involves integrating environmental, social, and governance (ESG) factors into business strategies to ensure long-term value creation and sustainability."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">292</data>
      <data key="d6">1c16b22e18d3483b8d41b284754274e2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ESG INFORMATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"ESG (Environment, Social, and Governance) information is used by investors to gauge a business's long-term value creation potential and sustainability. It includes data on environmental impact, social responsibility, and governance practices."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">293</data>
      <data key="d6">0080f96708cd4054a5f0986ca86889f4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUSTAINABILITY STRATEGY PERSPECTIVES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A sustainability strategy involves building value for shareholders while contributing to a sustainable society. It requires an integrated focus on value creation from capitals, stakeholder perspectives, megatrends affecting opportunities and threats, and customer preferences."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">294</data>
      <data key="d6">e683130322ac47708a852a5e51abb7c5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ROLE OF ACCOUNTANTS IN DEVELOPING SUSTAINABLE PRACTICES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Accountants play a central role in driving sustainability by identifying trends and impacts, integrating natural and social capital issues into management information, assessing benefits of environmental and social matters, organizing systems for decision-making, linking to value creation, driving efficiency, providing data credibility, and communicating transparently."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">295</data>
      <data key="d6">71a0a8c1beb64da08124205e9a803d98</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LEADERSHIP AND BUSINESS STRATEGY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"In the context of sustainability, leadership and business strategy involve making sustainability strategic rather than tactical, identifying the business case, facilitating leadership and commitment, engaging finance and accounting functions, and connecting sustainability to strategy, risk, and performance."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">296</data>
      <data key="d6">f84314943bee4c859c9a62f268c9c216</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MANAGEMENT, OPERATIONS AND ACCOUNTING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This area focuses on improving the process of information and data collection, analysis, and reporting. Finance professionals work closely with sustainability professionals to generate information and analysis to support decisions and reduce the sustainability impact of products, services, and operations."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">297</data>
      <data key="d6">ba481175ee1d4329bf07757a30abd3a1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMMUNICATIONS, REPORTING AND DISCLOSURE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Finance professionals integrate meaningful sustainability performance information into business reporting processes and disclosures. This includes developing a business reporting strategy, integrating sustainability impacts into financial reporting, and assuring sustainability disclosures and reports."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">298</data>
      <data key="d6">8d8da35190bf43c5878fa38f3eb4f3d2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ENVIRONMENTAL MANAGEMENT ACCOUNTING (EMA)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Environmental management accounting (EMA) provides management with monetary and non-monetary (physical) information to understand and manage the environmental impact of the organization&#8217;s activities. EMA techniques include input/output analysis, activity-based costing (ABC), and life-cycle costing."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">299</data>
      <data key="d6">2fb7e14a3f124526bd7b24867fc18e81</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RELEVANT COST ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Relevant cost analysis" involves identifying and analyzing costs that are directly related to a specific decision. It helps in making informed decisions by focusing on costs that will change as a result of the decision. These costs are future, incremental, and cash flows, which are affected by specific management decisions.</data>
      <data key="d2">836c03bc0c3a85400d4d39d4278e3a51,a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d7">14</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">300</data>
      <data key="d6">5c13c7d61e6c4bfe839f21e7ad3530a7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DECISION-MAKING TECHNIQUES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Decision-making techniques" covered in this chapter include various methods and tools used to analyze and make informed business decisions. These techniques help in evaluating different options and selecting the best course of action. Specifically, decision-making techniques for dealing with risk and uncertainty include research techniques to reduce uncertainty, such as focus groups and market research. Additionally, the use of simulation, expected values, sensitivity analysis, and the techniques of maximax, maximin, and minimax regret are discussed. These techniques assist in interpreting decision trees, solving multi-stage decision problems, and calculating the value of perfect and imperfect information.</data>
      <data key="d2">35cfdb511a04dc63dee7570f6be9f000,a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">301</data>
      <data key="d6">a621663edba64d99b7e50f1e53f32ee7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SOCIAL CAPITAL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Social capital refers to the networks, relationships, and norms that shape the quality and quantity of a society's social interactions. It contributes to societal well-being and economic performance by fostering cooperation and trust."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">302</data>
      <data key="d6">42be4e140061482ea509dd3e26189480</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GOVERNANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Governance involves the structures, policies, and practices that ensure an organization operates in a legal, ethical, and transparent manner. Good governance is crucial for long-term sustainability and stakeholder trust."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">303</data>
      <data key="d6">4da4ef951ff340f1a3dd679de4be3341</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STAKEHOLDER ENGAGEMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Stakeholder engagement is the process of involving individuals, groups, or organizations that may be affected by or have an effect on a company's actions. Effective engagement helps build trust and can lead to better decision-making and outcomes."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">304</data>
      <data key="d6">2f05fcce857e4a499ca4e89a3cefbcb3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MEGATRENDS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Megatrends are large, transformative global forces that impact businesses, economies, industries, and societies. Examples include climate change, urbanization, technological advancements, and demographic shifts."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">305</data>
      <data key="d6">b3aeb7ae009a4f52ae3ae4586e32fe11</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CUSTOMER PREFERENCES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Customer preferences refer to the tastes, preferences, and expectations of consumers regarding products and services. Understanding these preferences is crucial for businesses to meet market demands and achieve long-term success."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">306</data>
      <data key="d6">089b9b9841714b8da043777e2cda3767</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VALUE CREATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Value creation is the process by which businesses generate value for their stakeholders, including shareholders, customers, employees, and society at large. It involves enhancing the worth of products, services, or the business itself."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">307</data>
      <data key="d6">38f1e44579d0437dac1203c34678d3c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TRANSPARENCY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Transparency involves being open and honest about company operations, decisions, and performance. It builds trust with stakeholders and is essential for good governance and accountability."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">308</data>
      <data key="d6">1ca24718a96b47f3a8855550506c4b41</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ENVIRONMENTAL IMPACT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Environmental impact refers to the effect that a company's activities have on the natural environment. This includes factors such as resource consumption, waste generation, and emissions."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">309</data>
      <data key="d6">9c980dfe3cab44b7a83408405edab0b6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SOCIAL RESPONSIBILITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Social responsibility is the obligation of a business to contribute positively to society and minimize negative impacts. This includes ethical labor practices, community engagement, and philanthropy."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">310</data>
      <data key="d6">f23484b1b45d44c3b7847e1906dddd37</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GOVERNANCE PRACTICES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Governance practices are the policies and procedures that guide an organization's operations and decision-making. Effective governance practices ensure accountability, fairness, and transparency."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">311</data>
      <data key="d6">929f30875e1744b49e7b416eaf5a790c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BUSINESS REPORTING STRATEGY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A business reporting strategy involves the systematic approach to collecting, analyzing, and presenting business performance information. It ensures that stakeholders receive accurate and relevant information."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">312</data>
      <data key="d6">4920fda031804ce8a1073ace8e061ed6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FINANCIAL REPORTING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Financial reporting involves the disclosure of financial information to stakeholders about the financial performance and position of a business. It includes financial statements, notes, and other relevant information."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">313</data>
      <data key="d6">4b8aa4587c7344adac2cbfa69d5e40fa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUSTAINABILITY DISCLOSURES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sustainability disclosures are reports that provide information on a company's environmental, social, and governance (ESG) performance. These disclosures help stakeholders understand the company's sustainability practices and impacts."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">314</data>
      <data key="d6">52701d941dfb45359693baae8f267056</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ASSURANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Assurance in the context of sustainability involves the verification of sustainability reports and disclosures by an independent third party. It enhances the credibility and reliability of the reported information."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">315</data>
      <data key="d6">31499ee6277a4d71b19cb5b6be554c69</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INPUT/OUTPUT ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Input/output analysis" is a technique used in environmental management accounting (EMA) to track the flow of materials and energy through a system. It helps identify inefficiencies and areas for improvement.</data>
      <data key="d2">836c03bc0c3a85400d4d39d4278e3a51,a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d7">2</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">316</data>
      <data key="d6">d99eabad5dfd47278692569d2a9395b1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONTINGENT COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Contingent costs" are potential costs that may be incurred depending on the outcome of future events. These costs are uncertain and can include legal liabilities, environmental fines, and cleanup costs.</data>
      <data key="d2">836c03bc0c3a85400d4d39d4278e3a51,a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d7">16</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">317</data>
      <data key="d6">d53f15cb7f7845de91cc44ad44ff9f6e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;IMAGE AND RELATIONSHIP COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Image and relationship costs are expenses related to maintaining and improving a company's reputation and relationships with stakeholders. These costs can include public relations efforts, community engagement, and corporate social responsibility initiatives."</data>
      <data key="d2">836c03bc0c3a85400d4d39d4278e3a51,a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d7">16</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">318</data>
      <data key="d6">23becf8c6fca4f47a53ec4883d4bf63f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONVENTIONAL COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Conventional costs" refer to the direct costs associated with production, including raw materials, labor, and manufacturing expenses. These costs also encompass overheads and are typically accounted for in traditional financial statements.</data>
      <data key="d2">836c03bc0c3a85400d4d39d4278e3a51,a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d7">16</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">319</data>
      <data key="d6">d0ffa3bcd1234258953ff4956d19f561</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;POTENTIALLY HIDDEN COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Potentially hidden costs" are costs that are not immediately apparent or accounted for in traditional financial statements. These can include indirect costs such as regulatory compliance, future disposal costs, environmental degradation, health impacts, and long-term resource depletion.</data>
      <data key="d2">836c03bc0c3a85400d4d39d4278e3a51,a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d7">16</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">320</data>
      <data key="d6">ac41b77ba33c4c84877eb425aba03aa1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRICING STRATEGY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A pricing strategy is a plan or method used by a business to set the prices of its products or services. It takes into account factors such as market demand, competition, production costs, and overall business objectives."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">321</data>
      <data key="d6">5d3184dabfd647a5a7e565f72c60ff24</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRODUCT DESIGN PHASE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The product design phase is the stage in the product development process where the product's features, specifications, and aesthetics are determined. Effective design can help manage costs and improve product sustainability."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">322</data>
      <data key="d6">0ec262c2cfef4dd581f3655e5e496e31</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CUMULATIVE COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Cumulative costs refer to the total costs incurred over the entire life cycle of a product, from development to disposal. Tracking these costs helps in understanding the long-term financial impact of a product."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">323</data>
      <data key="d6">100c2fccd7f74d9281707082f062ba72</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REVENUE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Revenue" is the total amount of income generated by the sale of goods or services related to a company's primary operations. It is a key indicator of a company's financial performance and is used to assess profitability and growth. Revenue is calculated as the product of sales units and sales price, representing the total income before any costs or expenses are deducted. Recently, revenue decreased by 8.3% from $72,025 to $66,028, but this figure was still 14.6% higher than expected given the market decline.</data>
      <data key="d2">00157cf30936c417d0c54f1dfce77654,002794ec024434f7ac2bd26217b3897d,01294aa83ab1143451866d43087f9eba,01d1ff33e985b6f8cd09ff45ebfedc0e,026b22934152d61a6b625fae071b3bcd,0279d26139c7d66d51896f7ebfe162ee,02defdad562458f44c0d0fa31dc9693d,03721d9b5064cc002df514cca9896c3b,039a2a6ce8c94f49aa8954c72332cea2,05e25a78a53e695fd01856df3a302292,0622f4f26dbe7479c871198b2e72b940,078e47b3223db97709a37da2a01302c5,08f6c24c7f87b7ffc3b8a5dfc505c552,0a1392ec8d4dc63bfee377dc6d552da3,0af2d78ba77677f806a697c0deb0ced3,0cafbc1007afddae5f416e6fb910386a,0d6ca97290394110da0bcfffa12dac11,0dbbae65ee89b4c5d53a1b0a83d84535,0e0632925a4598cac64c13be234f1755,0f59fe901f330c6a95c810cdae18b305,10a6cfb7beb226418463ca4749be7451,1198b5b37a51d0315db68af2bdb139bd,11b64c42e42e94e3f0881a9cd9457d74,122be7bb4778bacae6dba8d18b50c025,12bf561fb0f443af5c38c4055dae476d,14d295eb69556ed8203b13909d341a07,158846b2d51075f1de4279110c7a2ae1,16965b8a36bbe6bac45c7b81a6b17c48,181a68483be6482e8b136a2d540875a9,185572ab91ea67a36a262b55dffde450,1872b59f14e8fe91c616b29960e49fb9,19092af48cfe51bac1503c304f3ca707,1aa84a5288fe62c1d778b9f9013d51c3,1c07f0d21b37bda63c238ee6e4ed571b,1d33c979d505d0dcd027d816d2ab2695,1dbcdd2207ed07f8e45dc35658ecbd2a,1e37a7be9b892b604c2e7b6cf6a2c49f,1f06696499d837582d3dac671cb07649,2154b2cf6113011b3816974155d6ed8d,2207ef547588f07b856f3a5c961e39a0,22f7850b6ee24babd9cf367c0fc478a4,2343dedcae64d2e174ab981dfc3b23a0,2381a9a278f9cf058d7c71932fad4841,238ba7ae5def49a914d13c1bcf1e1332,24cd8c3feefdefe57b7e7da7db59d031,258563e1a008a7977296119e059fdf11,27370737012393c709c89a56df8ea2d4,27fde199847b14399dfca384e07a77a4,2922f29fc45ffc98655fc81f9a40fa79,299f4bc827fb4c62a74f3271557514e9,2a57a845054dd3fd23f0910ad239a201,2ad6c0ee81f4b0da1c6b2f2821dff6b6,2b35add90aa38f95a0510f9302a559f9,2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a,2ec07a1112223c3286057400e3b2eca9,2f4d122e57ceca3100dab3886c99ca27,2fd1d6134ec72f26d7a900391b7261fd,303f0ef8328d2aefc4bfae1067a85f72,30748d6dcf5a2da70804db75296cee3c,312c3cf9edbc058c6e810c1e9c9cd81a