      <data key="d7">10</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">13</data>
      <data key="d5">324</data>
      <data key="d6">378fc7636eeb4aabbfd40995a6960c64</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BOTTLENECK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A bottleneck is a point of congestion or blockage in a production process that limits overall output. Identifying and managing bottlenecks is crucial for improving efficiency and throughput."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">325</data>
      <data key="d6">80a04aa18cd649d584292f23b10c0727</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MATERIAL COST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Material cost refers to the expense incurred to acquire raw materials used in production. It is a significant component of the total cost of goods sold and impacts pricing and profitability."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">326</data>
      <data key="d6">4e9ca18ccc1d4527a3bc035d07f5e162</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MONETARY INFORMATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Monetary information in environmental management accounting (EMA) includes financial data related to environmental costs and benefits. It helps in making informed decisions about resource allocation and sustainability initiatives."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">327</data>
      <data key="d6">5564257e89f1428486a64fcf52f49490</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NON-MONETARY (PHYSICAL) INFORMATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Non-monetary (physical) information in environmental management accounting (EMA) includes data on material and energy flows, emissions, and waste. It provides insights into the environmental impact of business activities."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">328</data>
      <data key="d6">83c76fbd2a004d90a5b0a6736ffed61d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ENVIRONMENTAL IMPACT OF ACTIVITIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The environmental impact of activities refers to the effects that a company's operations have on the natural environment. This includes resource use, emissions, waste generation, and ecological footprint."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">329</data>
      <data key="d6">d9779c41e3c74fe0b26e23822a4b995b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ENVIRONMENTAL AND SOCIAL MATTERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Environmental and social matters encompass issues related to a company's impact on the environment and society. Addressing these matters is crucial for sustainable development and long-term value creation."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">330</data>
      <data key="d6">9d7a563b3b2d405092c31f1fe08cff77</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DECISION-MAKING SYSTEMS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Decision-making systems are processes and tools used to make informed business decisions. These systems integrate various types of information, including financial, environmental, and social data, to support strategic planning and operational efficiency."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">331</data>
      <data key="d6">bd43f3d439a54781bd4b721a9a269b92</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DATA CREDIBILITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Data credibility refers to the trustworthiness and reliability of information used in decision-making. Ensuring data credibility is essential for accurate reporting, transparency, and stakeholder trust."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">332</data>
      <data key="d6">adc0f95733e74351a891c4dadf650a52</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LONG-TERM VALUE CREATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Long-term value creation involves strategies and actions that enhance the sustainable growth and profitability of a business over an extended period. It focuses on balancing short-term gains with long-term objectives."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">333</data>
      <data key="d6">225105a7be14447cb03186bd40756059</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STRATEGIC SUSTAINABILITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Strategic sustainability involves integrating sustainability into the core business strategy. It ensures that sustainability considerations are part of decision-making processes and long-term planning."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">334</data>
      <data key="d6">efce8a9d61254447a26aee99e53f0398</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TACTICAL SUSTAINABILITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Tactical sustainability involves short-term actions and initiatives aimed at improving sustainability performance. While important, it is distinct from strategic sustainability, which focuses on long-term integration."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">335</data>
      <data key="d6">4a75a9f0b18a48bea9c0601c0fc395c4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BUSINESS CASE FOR SUSTAINABILITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The business case for sustainability refers to the justification for integrating sustainability into business operations. It includes potential benefits such as cost savings, risk management, brand enhancement, and long-term profitability."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">336</data>
      <data key="d6">e19287afe00a431f9a593a4827d1b448</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FINANCE AND ACCOUNTING FUNCTIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Finance and accounting functions involve managing a company's financial resources, including budgeting, forecasting, reporting, and compliance. These functions are critical for integrating sustainability into business strategy and operations."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">337</data>
      <data key="d6">f2c06f3a0c704296bf3353b91ee8af47</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STRATEGY, RISK, AND PERFORMANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Strategy, risk, and performance are interconnected aspects of business management. Effective strategies consider potential risks and aim to enhance overall performance, including sustainability outcomes."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">338</data>
      <data key="d6">f512103ed4624accac6cbbf90d7d250a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INFORMATION AND DATA COLLECTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Information and data collection involves gathering relevant data to support business decisions. In the context of sustainability, this includes environmental, social, and governance (ESG) data."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">339</data>
      <data key="d6">2325dafe50d1435cbee8ebcaa69688df</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DATA ANALYSIS AND REPORTING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Data analysis and reporting involve interpreting collected data and presenting it in a meaningful way. This process supports decision-making and helps communicate performance to stakeholders."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">340</data>
      <data key="d6">469aeef98cd1421fa123277b93d7b83a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUSTAINABILITY IMPACT OF PRODUCTS, SERVICES, AND OPERATIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The sustainability impact of products, services, and operations refers to the environmental and social effects of a company's offerings and activities. Managing these impacts is crucial for sustainable development."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">341</data>
      <data key="d6">2fb66f9a0de6406d83b61742a3b52cd6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUSTAINABILITY PERFORMANCE INFORMATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sustainability performance information includes data on a company's environmental, social, and governance (ESG) performance. This information is used to assess and improve sustainability practices."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">342</data>
      <data key="d6">b0e6cfd979ea48b997019b059999d3c2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BUSINESS PERFORMANCE INFORMATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Business performance information includes financial and non-financial data that indicate how well a company is achieving its objectives. This information is critical for strategic planning and decision-making."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">343</data>
      <data key="d6">ef00ec3a324f4f5986141401002af3f6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUSTAINABILITY IMPACTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sustainability impacts refer to the effects of a company's activities on the environment, society, and economy. Understanding these impacts is essential for developing effective sustainability strategies."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">344</data>
      <data key="d6">a542fd7aed7341468028928937ea2983</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUSTAINABILITY REPORTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sustainability reports are documents that provide information on a company's sustainability practices and performance. These reports are used to communicate with stakeholders and demonstrate commitment to sustainability."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">345</data>
      <data key="d6">1c5e296a5ac541c1b5cac4357537c22d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUSTAINABILITY REPORTING PROCESSES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sustainability reporting processes involve the systematic collection, analysis, and disclosure of sustainability performance information. These processes ensure transparency and accountability."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">346</data>
      <data key="d6">5ecf534a9ffe46e0b1c2144110c691c0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INDEPENDENT THIRD PARTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An independent third party is an external organization or individual that provides objective verification or assurance services. In sustainability, third-party assurance enhances the credibility of reported information."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">347</data>
      <data key="d6">4d183e7007624fcd98af96b9d752c16d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VERIFICATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Verification is the process of checking the accuracy and reliability of information. In the context of sustainability, verification ensures that reported data is accurate and trustworthy."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">348</data>
      <data key="d6">718c507cb8ac49e6a35c251ac951b5ca</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUSTAINABILITY INITIATIVES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sustainability initiatives are projects or actions undertaken by a company to improve its environmental, social, and governance (ESG) performance. These initiatives contribute to long-term sustainability."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">349</data>
      <data key="d6">b45ef27279c043269b23b894461d7d8c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ECOLOGICAL FOOTPRINT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"An ecological footprint measures the environmental impact of a company's activities in terms of the amount of natural resources consumed and waste generated. It is used to assess sustainability performance."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">350</data>
      <data key="d6">10983a248cc448c59c94df4d1d0898f0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ETHICAL LABOR PRACTICES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Ethical labor practices involve treating employees fairly, providing safe working conditions, and ensuring fair wages. These practices are part of a company's social responsibility and contribute to sustainability."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">351</data>
      <data key="d6">e2ec7d3cdbeb4dd086ae6eb399332363</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMMUNITY ENGAGEMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Community engagement involves building relationships and working collaboratively with local communities. It helps address social issues, supports local development, and enhances a company's social license to operate."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">352</data>
      <data key="d6">67f10971666240ea930f3b875aabdc1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PHILANTHROPY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Philanthropy involves charitable giving and support for social causes. It is a component of corporate social responsibility and helps build a positive reputation and contribute to societal well-being."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">353</data>
      <data key="d6">8b95083939ad4771b57a97c2d5805f36</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PUBLIC RELATIONS EFFORTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Public relations efforts involve managing a company's communication with the public and media. Effective PR helps build and maintain a positive image and manage stakeholder perceptions."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">354</data>
      <data key="d6">3c4062de44d64870a3cc5913d5769244</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CORPORATE SOCIAL RESPONSIBILITY INITIATIVES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Corporate social responsibility (CSR) initiatives are actions taken by a company to contribute positively to society and minimize negative impacts. These initiatives include environmental sustainability, ethical labor practices, and community support."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">355</data>
      <data key="d6">24652fab20d84381b112b8491de2887e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LEGAL LIABILITIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Legal liabilities are potential legal obligations that a company may face due to its actions or inactions. These can include fines, penalties, and lawsuits related to environmental or social issues."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">356</data>
      <data key="d6">d4602d4a27b34358baa86814a3836d68</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ENVIRONMENTAL FINES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Environmental fines are penalties imposed on a company for violating environmental regulations. These fines are part of contingent costs and can impact a company's financial performance and reputation."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">357</data>
      <data key="d6">36be44627ece444284f9e759b8cd25c6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CLEANUP COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Cleanup costs are expenses associated with cleaning up environmental damage caused by a company's activities. These costs are part of contingent costs and can be significant, affecting long-term profitability."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">358</data>
      <data key="d6">a64b4b17b07a44e4b1ac33580d811936</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RAW MATERIALS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Raw materials are the basic materials used in the production of goods. The cost and availability of raw materials impact production costs and overall business performance."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">359</data>
      <data key="d6">423b72bbd56f4caa98f3328202c1c3c9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MANUFACTURING EXPENSES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Manufacturing expenses are the costs associated with producing goods, including labor, materials, and overhead. These expenses are a key component of the total cost of goods sold."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">360</data>
      <data key="d6">5c7ef01f46a94641bf1ae5cd25f8a538</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARKET DEMAND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Market demand refers to the total quantity of a product or service that consumers are willing and able to purchase at a given price. Understanding market demand is crucial for setting prices and planning production."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">361</data>
      <data key="d6">aefde1f7617f4c0e9aed31db77f6d862</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMPETITION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Competition refers to the rivalry between businesses in the same industry to attract customers and achieve market share. Competitive dynamics influence pricing strategies, product development, and overall business strategy."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">362</data>
      <data key="d6">ad52ba79a84748a49067e53b1d5095f9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BUSINESS OBJECTIVES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Business objectives are the specific goals that a company aims to achieve. These objectives guide strategic planning and decision-making and can include financial targets, market expansion, and sustainability goals."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">363</data>
      <data key="d6">289616058bf4495887292003b27ba216</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRODUCT DEVELOPMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Product development is the process of creating new products or improving existing ones. It involves research, design, testing, and commercialization and is critical for innovation and market competitiveness."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">364</data>
      <data key="d6">7ffa3a064bce468082739c5a164df5a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DISPOSAL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Disposal refers to the process of discarding or getting rid of products or materials that are no longer needed. Effective disposal practices are important for minimizing environmental impact and managing costs."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">365</data>
      <data key="d6">ce36d1d637cf4a4e93f5e37ffbc6bd76</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE" is a dimension of Fitzgerald and Moon's Building Block Model that measures the financial health and profitability of an organization. It evaluates how well a company can use its assets from its primary mode of business to generate revenues and create value for shareholders. Key metrics used to assess financial performance include gross profit margin, net profit margin, continuous turnover growth, annual compound growth rate, profit growth, and the ratio of fixed costs to revenues. Additionally, financial performance is measured through financial statements and key performance indicators (KPIs) such as growth in sales and return on investment (ROI).</data>
      <data key="d2">00157cf30936c417d0c54f1dfce77654,002794ec024434f7ac2bd26217b3897d,01294aa83ab1143451866d43087f9eba,01d1ff33e985b6f8cd09ff45ebfedc0e,026b22934152d61a6b625fae071b3bcd,0279d26139c7d66d51896f7ebfe162ee,02defdad562458f44c0d0fa31dc9693d,03721d9b5064cc002df514cca9896c3b,039a2a6ce8c94f49aa8954c72332cea2,05e25a78a53e695fd01856df3a302292,0622f4f26dbe7479c871198b2e72b940,078e47b3223db97709a37da2a01302c5,08f6c24c7f87b7ffc3b8a5dfc505c552,0a1392ec8d4dc63bfee377dc6d552da3,0af2d78ba77677f806a697c0deb0ced3,0cafbc1007afddae5f416e6fb910386a,0d6ca97290394110da0bcfffa12dac11,0dbbae65ee89b4c5d53a1b0a83d84535,0e0632925a4598cac64c13be234f1755,0f59fe901f330c6a95c810cdae18b305,10a6cfb7beb226418463ca4749be7451,1198b5b37a51d0315db68af2bdb139bd,11b64c42e42e94e3f0881a9cd9457d74,122be7bb4778bacae6dba8d18b50c025,12bf561fb0f443af5c38c4055dae476d,14d295eb69556ed8203b13909d341a07,158846b2d51075f1de4279110c7a2ae1,16965b8a36bbe6bac45c7b81a6b17c48,181a68483be6482e8b136a2d540875a9,185572ab91ea67a36a262b55dffde450,1872b59f14e8fe91c616b29960e49fb9,19092af48cfe51bac1503c304f3ca707,1aa84a5288fe62c1d778b9f9013d51c3,1c07f0d21b37bda63c238ee6e4ed571b,1d33c979d505d0dcd027d816d2ab2695,1dbcdd2207ed07f8e45dc35658ecbd2a,1e37a7be9b892b604c2e7b6cf6a2c49f,1f06696499d837582d3dac671cb07649,2154b2cf6113011b3816974155d6ed8d,2207ef547588f07b856f3a5c961e39a0,22f7850b6ee24babd9cf367c0fc478a4,2343dedcae64d2e174ab981dfc3b23a0,2381a9a278f9cf058d7c71932fad4841,238ba7ae5def49a914d13c1bcf1e1332,24cd8c3feefdefe57b7e7da7db59d031,258563e1a008a7977296119e059fdf11,27370737012393c709c89a56df8ea2d4,27fde199847b14399dfca384e07a77a4,2922f29fc45ffc98655fc81f9a40fa79,299f4bc827fb4c62a74f3271557514e9,2a57a845054dd3fd23f0910ad239a201,2ad6c0ee81f4b0da1c6b2f2821dff6b6,2b35add90aa38f95a0510f9302a559f9,2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a,2ec07a1112223c3286057400e3b2eca9,2f4d122e57ceca3100dab3886c99ca27,2fd1d6134ec72f26d7a900391b7261fd,303f0ef8328d2aefc4bfae1067a85f72,30748d6dcf5a2da70804db75296cee3c,312c3cf9edbc058c6e810c1e9c9cd81a