      <data key="d4">8</data>
      <data key="d5">366</data>
      <data key="d6">eeb9c02c0efa4131b9e95d33c31019fc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GROWTH&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Growth refers to the increase in a company's size, revenue, market share, or other key metrics over time. Sustainable growth is essential for long-term success and competitiveness."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">367</data>
      <data key="d6">7b2472c5dd9949c58828413387b94659</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRODUCTION PROCESSES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Production processes are the methods and techniques used to manufacture goods or deliver services. Efficient production processes are crucial for cost management, quality control, and sustainability."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">368</data>
      <data key="d6">bdddcb17ba6c408599dd395ce64f960a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COST OF GOODS SOLD (COGS)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Cost of goods sold (COGS) is the direct costs attributable to the production of goods sold by a company. It includes raw materials, labor, and manufacturing expenses and impacts gross profit."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">369</data>
      <data key="d6">bc70fee2061541148833d19e86f225b3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GROSS PROFIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">Gross profit is the difference between sales revenue and the cost of goods sold (COGS). It indicates the efficiency of production and the profitability of core business activities. Gross profit is the profit a company makes after deducting the costs associated with making and selling its products, or the costs associated with providing its services.</data>
      <data key="d2">a22eae134ce57b58870ae60a9afaf634,a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d7">10</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">370</data>
      <data key="d6">0fc15cc3b44c4142a770feb4c037a6f7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;KEY PERFORMANCE INDICATORS (KPIS)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Key performance indicators (KPIs) are measurable values that demonstrate how effectively a company is achieving its business objectives. KPIs are used to assess performance and guide strategic decisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">371</data>
      <data key="d6">a24e9df02e1b4b43bf6324b039e28285</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STRATEGIC PLANNING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Strategic planning is the process of defining a company's direction and making decisions on allocating resources to pursue this direction. It involves setting objectives, analyzing competitive environments, and developing action plans."</data>
      <data key="d2">a9d0dc5f61fc7776a3e266a03f359f3f</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">372</data>
      <data key="d6">ab3a5a6713244fd595a1ace978c3d960</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EMA TECHNIQUES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"EMA techniques include input/output analysis, ABC, and life-cycle costing."</data>
      <data key="d2">836c03bc0c3a85400d4d39d4278e3a51</data>
      <data key="d3">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d7">2</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">373</data>
      <data key="d6">02a88c0d128e4586b2f1f64329786d3c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUSTAINABILITY AND BUSINESS RESILIENCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Accountants must be able to link sustainability to the broader business agenda by highlighting elements that build resilience and develop a sustainable strategy."</data>
      <data key="d2">836c03bc0c3a85400d4d39d4278e3a51</data>
      <data key="d3">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d7">2</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">374</data>
      <data key="d6">1ca41537c47c4752a17a44d1d7086d96</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RELEVANT COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Relevant costs" are costs that will be affected by a decision. In the context of further processing decisions, relevant costs include additional processing costs and any incremental revenues. They are used to determine the minimum price that can be used as the basis for a quotation. Relevant costs encompass those costs that are influenced by a specific management decision, including future costs and revenues, incremental costs, and cash flows.</data>
      <data key="d2">2b7c12bc08e4dff98f807210499e82ee,836c03bc0c3a85400d4d39d4278e3a51,c0117b1a829ee89c41385c27964ebda4,c072010f60f9a31fe566e35a7ad7d3cc,f48e76ebf07d8d7de318d46534f42fd9</data>
      <data key="d3">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d7">14</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">10</data>
      <data key="d5">375</data>
      <data key="d6">7e0d14ca308b4796bdc675a64bd3a36e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OPPORTUNITY COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Opportunity costs" are the benefits foregone by choosing one alternative over another. They represent the potential benefits an individual, investor, or business misses out on when making a choice between different options.</data>
      <data key="d2">00157cf30936c417d0c54f1dfce77654,002794ec024434f7ac2bd26217b3897d,01294aa83ab1143451866d43087f9eba,01d1ff33e985b6f8cd09ff45ebfedc0e,026b22934152d61a6b625fae071b3bcd,0279d26139c7d66d51896f7ebfe162ee,02defdad562458f44c0d0fa31dc9693d,03721d9b5064cc002df514cca9896c3b,039a2a6ce8c94f49aa8954c72332cea2,05e25a78a53e695fd01856df3a302292,0622f4f26dbe7479c871198b2e72b940,078e47b3223db97709a37da2a01302c5,08f6c24c7f87b7ffc3b8a5dfc505c552,0a1392ec8d4dc63bfee377dc6d552da3,0af2d78ba77677f806a697c0deb0ced3,0cafbc1007afddae5f416e6fb910386a,0d6ca97290394110da0bcfffa12dac11,0dbbae65ee89b4c5d53a1b0a83d84535,0e0632925a4598cac64c13be234f1755,0f59fe901f330c6a95c810cdae18b305,10a6cfb7beb226418463ca4749be7451,1198b5b37a51d0315db68af2bdb139bd,11b64c42e42e94e3f0881a9cd9457d74,122be7bb4778bacae6dba8d18b50c025,12bf561fb0f443af5c38c4055dae476d,14d295eb69556ed8203b13909d341a07,158846b2d51075f1de4279110c7a2ae1,16965b8a36bbe6bac45c7b81a6b17c48,181a68483be6482e8b136a2d540875a9,185572ab91ea67a36a262b55dffde450,1872b59f14e8fe91c616b29960e49fb9,19092af48cfe51bac1503c304f3ca707,1aa84a5288fe62c1d778b9f9013d51c3,1c07f0d21b37bda63c238ee6e4ed571b,1d33c979d505d0dcd027d816d2ab2695,1dbcdd2207ed07f8e45dc35658ecbd2a,1e37a7be9b892b604c2e7b6cf6a2c49f,1f06696499d837582d3dac671cb07649,2154b2cf6113011b3816974155d6ed8d,2207ef547588f07b856f3a5c961e39a0,22f7850b6ee24babd9cf367c0fc478a4,2343dedcae64d2e174ab981dfc3b23a0,2381a9a278f9cf058d7c71932fad4841,238ba7ae5def49a914d13c1bcf1e1332,24cd8c3feefdefe57b7e7da7db59d031,258563e1a008a7977296119e059fdf11,27370737012393c709c89a56df8ea2d4,27fde199847b14399dfca384e07a77a4,2922f29fc45ffc98655fc81f9a40fa79,299f4bc827fb4c62a74f3271557514e9,2a57a845054dd3fd23f0910ad239a201,2ad6c0ee81f4b0da1c6b2f2821dff6b6,2b35add90aa38f95a0510f9302a559f9,2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a,2ec07a1112223c3286057400e3b2eca9,2f4d122e57ceca3100dab3886c99ca27,2fd1d6134ec72f26d7a900391b7261fd,303f0ef8328d2aefc4bfae1067a85f72,30748d6dcf5a2da70804db75296cee3c,312c3cf9edbc058c6e810c1e9c9cd81a