      <data key="d6">91407be8c3e54e23918d3a7183d962db</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES PRICE PER UNIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sales price per unit is the amount of money charged to customers for each unit of a product or service. It is a key component in calculating revenue and contribution."</data>
      <data key="d2">98d761e221e6915f156753807cb8fbe1</data>
      <data key="d7">6</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">449</data>
      <data key="d6">3831134696584d83bbf676a6b3bfa8f9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TOTAL REVENUE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Total revenue" refers to the total amount of money received from sales of goods or services, calculated by multiplying the sales volume by the sales price per unit. In the context of Best Night Co, total revenue (net of discounts) has increased by 2.4% in 20X7 compared to 20X6. This increase is particularly noteworthy given the tough competitive environment, and any rise in revenues can be seen as a positive outcome. Additionally, as long as the revenue from selling a room exceeds the variable cost of providing it, higher occupancy levels should contribute positively to the hotel's profit.</data>
      <data key="d2">23de7e5f5aa4638cfdebaec8afd6c5de,98d761e221e6915f156753807cb8fbe1,c559ece83ebebc82b7241fbb0cd0dd92</data>
      <data key="d7">6</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">450</data>
      <data key="d6">50e512a5dbe941f5af68bfdf74b1c3c0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TOTAL COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Total costs are the sum of fixed and variable costs incurred by a business in the production of goods or services. It is a crucial factor in determining profitability."</data>
      <data key="d2">98d761e221e6915f156753807cb8fbe1,d4cbc64c9c49dd951f9997a26ee9d9f9</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">451</data>
      <data key="d6">edc717747e904728b57185f5013461f9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARGIN OF SAFETY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Margin of Safety" is a financial metric that represents the difference between actual or projected sales and the breakeven sales volume. It measures the risk of a business falling below its breakeven point. The margin of safety can be expressed in units, dollars, or as a percentage, indicating the amount by which anticipated or existing activity exceeds (or falls short of) the breakeven point.

For example, in a quiz on calculating the margin of safety for Cummings Co., which manufactures a single product sold for $5, with annual sales revenue of $80,000, annual fixed costs of $25,000, and a contribution/sales ratio of 40%, the margin of safety is calculated as ((16,000 - 12,500) / 16,000) * 100% = 21.9%. This calculation demonstrates how the margin of safety can be applied in a real-world scenario to assess the financial health and risk of a business.</data>
      <data key="d2">23de7e5f5aa4638cfdebaec8afd6c5de,3ef6ffef196ce21eb853bd7cf7b00da2,98d761e221e6915f156753807cb8fbe1</data>
      <data key="d7">3</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">452</data>
      <data key="d6">8fba1fea719d49d380ac2d9c310d68b3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OPERATING LEVERAGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Operating leverage is a measure of how sensitive net operating income is to a given percentage change in sales volume. It is influenced by the proportion of fixed costs in a company's cost structure."</data>
      <data key="d2">98d761e221e6915f156753807cb8fbe1</data>
      <data key="d7">6</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">453</data>
      <data key="d6">532da08f04f645708e747c57e9c4ee05</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;UNIT CONTRIBUTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Unit contribution" is calculated as the selling price per unit minus the variable cost per unit. It is used to determine the breakeven point and target profit. The unit contribution represents the amount each unit contributes to covering fixed costs and generating profit.</data>
      <data key="d2">00157cf30936c417d0c54f1dfce77654,002794ec024434f7ac2bd26217b3897d,01294aa83ab1143451866d43087f9eba,01d1ff33e985b6f8cd09ff45ebfedc0e,026b22934152d61a6b625fae071b3bcd,0279d26139c7d66d51896f7ebfe162ee,02defdad562458f44c0d0fa31dc9693d,03721d9b5064cc002df514cca9896c3b,039a2a6ce8c94f49aa8954c72332cea2,05e25a78a53e695fd01856df3a302292,0622f4f26dbe7479c871198b2e72b940,078e47b3223db97709a37da2a01302c5,08f6c24c7f87b7ffc3b8a5dfc505c552,0a1392ec8d4dc63bfee377dc6d552da3,0af2d78ba77677f806a697c0deb0ced3,0cafbc1007afddae5f416e6fb910386a,0d6ca97290394110da0bcfffa12dac11,0dbbae65ee89b4c5d53a1b0a83d84535,0e0632925a4598cac64c13be234f1755,0f59fe901f330c6a95c810cdae18b305,10a6cfb7beb226418463ca4749be7451,1198b5b37a51d0315db68af2bdb139bd,11b64c42e42e94e3f0881a9cd9457d74,122be7bb4778bacae6dba8d18b50c025,12bf561fb0f443af5c38c4055dae476d,14d295eb69556ed8203b13909d341a07,158846b2d51075f1de4279110c7a2ae1,16965b8a36bbe6bac45c7b81a6b17c48,181a68483be6482e8b136a2d540875a9,185572ab91ea67a36a262b55dffde450,1872b59f14e8fe91c616b29960e49fb9,19092af48cfe51bac1503c304f3ca707,1aa84a5288fe62c1d778b9f9013d51c3,1c07f0d21b37bda63c238ee6e4ed571b,1d33c979d505d0dcd027d816d2ab2695,1dbcdd2207ed07f8e45dc35658ecbd2a,1e37a7be9b892b604c2e7b6cf6a2c49f,1f06696499d837582d3dac671cb07649,2154b2cf6113011b3816974155d6ed8d,2207ef547588f07b856f3a5c961e39a0,22f7850b6ee24babd9cf367c0fc478a4,2343dedcae64d2e174ab981dfc3b23a0,2381a9a278f9cf058d7c71932fad4841,238ba7ae5def49a914d13c1bcf1e1332,23de7e5f5aa4638cfdebaec8afd6c5de,24cd8c3feefdefe57b7e7da7db59d031,258563e1a008a7977296119e059fdf11,27370737012393c709c89a56df8ea2d4,27fde199847b14399dfca384e07a77a4,2922f29fc45ffc98655fc81f9a40fa79,299f4bc827fb4c62a74f3271557514e9,2a57a845054dd3fd23f0910ad239a201,2ad6c0ee81f4b0da1c6b2f2821dff6b6,2b35add90aa38f95a0510f9302a559f9,2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a,2ec07a1112223c3286057400e3b2eca9,2f4d122e57ceca3100dab3886c99ca27,2fd1d6134ec72f26d7a900391b7261fd,303f0ef8328d2aefc4bfae1067a85f72,30748d6dcf5a2da70804db75296cee3c