    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TOTAL BUDGETED REVENUE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Total budgeted revenue = Sum of budgeted revenue for all products"</data>
      <data key="d2">abd4a68d8185b413e829914bc2f86480</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">487</data>
      <data key="d6">2139b0906dc541e094138a978d070416</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;C/S RATIO&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">The "C/S RATIO" is defined as the ratio of the contribution per unit to the selling price per unit. For products C, S, and D, the C/S ratios are 0.55, 0.35, and 0.23 respectively.</data>
      <data key="d2">08f6c24c7f87b7ffc3b8a5dfc505c552,feda6b4c9964e8465efd20e4a6167582</data>
      <data key="d7">6</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">488</data>
      <data key="d6">ff5466607e5d4453b1d833629292f664</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BREAKEVEN REVENUE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Breakeven revenue = Fixed cost / C/S ratio"</data>
      <data key="d2">08f6c24c7f87b7ffc3b8a5dfc505c552</data>
      <data key="d7">6</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">489</data>
      <data key="d6">71f95003936e46a98d90757ffd845d40</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MULTI-PRODUCT BREAKEVEN CHARTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz involves constructing a PV chart for two products, 'boy racer' and 'family saloon,' based on budgeted sales and different sales assumptions."</data>
      <data key="d2">08f6c24c7f87b7ffc3b8a5dfc505c552</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">490</data>
      <data key="d6">bada987ea7da4c939393ee1c3d08ccd4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MULTI-PRODUCT SITUATIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"In multi-product situations, a fixed product mix is necessary to work with. If the product mix varies, there could be many breakeven points. Multi-product PV charts help in visualizing the relationship between revenue and profit."</data>
      <data key="d2">08f6c24c7f87b7ffc3b8a5dfc505c552</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">491</data>
      <data key="d6">d0a274e7934d446fb91847bb53a961a6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SUMMARY OF CVP ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The summary of CVP analysis includes the breakeven point, breakeven chart, profit-volume chart, and the limitations due to simplifying assumptions."</data>
      <data key="d2">08f6c24c7f87b7ffc3b8a5dfc505c552</data>
      <data key="d7">6</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">5</data>
      <data key="d5">492</data>
      <data key="d6">0a799eab61bc4e6b884db6689f9c2c4a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONTRIBUTION PER UNIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Contribution per unit" is calculated as the selling price per unit minus the variable cost per unit. It represents the amount each unit contributes to covering fixed costs and generating profit. The variable cost per unit includes materials cost, direct labor, and variable overhead.</data>
