    <node id="&quot;VARIABLE COST PER UNIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Variable cost per unit" is the cost that varies with the level of output. It is calculated by summing the per-unit costs of materials, labor, and variable overheads. In this case, it is $21 per unit. Additionally, "variable cost per unit" is represented by the gradient of the total cost line, which is also constant.</data>
