    <node id="&quot;COST-VOLUME-PROFIT (CVP) ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">Cost-Volume-Profit (CVP) Analysis is a method used by managers to understand the relationship between cost, volume, and profit in decision-making. This analysis assumes that the variable cost per unit and the selling price per unit remain constant over the full range of production. Additionally, CVP analysis ignores the impact of changes in inventory.</data>
