    <node id="&quot;DIMENSIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Dimensions" are measurable extents of some kind, such as length, breadth, depth, or height. Additionally, dimensions can refer to the aspects of performance that must be measured. In the Fitzgerald and Moon model, there are six specific dimensions: financial performance, competitiveness, quality, resource utilization, flexibility, and innovation.</data>
