    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SYSTEM OUTPUTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"System Outputs refer to the results produced by information systems, such as projections and responses to queries."</data>
      <data key="d2">9cb3ca1f088473aac339bd044b8a7507</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1224</data>
      <data key="d6">323a4c7407ac401db79a6023c3a5a17d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ENTERPRISE RESOURCE PLANNING (ERP) SYSTEMS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"ERP Systems are integrated systems that allow all departments within an organization to share information and typically include modules for accounting, budgeting, and other functions."</data>
      <data key="d2">9cb3ca1f088473aac339bd044b8a7507</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1225</data>
      <data key="d6">686bc2bd59644e398dde88ffd37bf49b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MANAGEMENT INFORMATION SYSTEMS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Management Information Systems are designed to report on existing operations and provide information to help management plan and control the operations of the organization."</data>
      <data key="d2">9cb3ca1f088473aac339bd044b8a7507</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
