    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THEORY OF CONSTRAINTS QUIZ&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">The "THEORY OF CONSTRAINTS QUIZ" is designed to test knowledge on the theory of constraints, with a particular focus on managing bottlenecks and maximizing throughput contribution. It assesses understanding by evaluating the ability to identify bottlenecks in production and the appropriate operation of non-bottleneck resources.</data>
      <data key="d2">bf895221917dacb42684c64f347d269d,c072010f60f9a31fe566e35a7ad7d3cc</data>
      <data key="d7">12</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1248</data>
      <data key="d6">53032c2afcb5474a88446ad7c5506980</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TARGET COST CALCULATION QUIZ&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">The "TARGET COST CALCULATION QUIZ" involves determining the target cost for a product given its selling price, expected sales volume, and required return on investment. The quiz provides the necessary data to calculate the target cost per unit and tests knowledge on calculating target costs based on expected revenue, required profit, and investment.</data>
      <data key="d2">71a15e253f55633783cde51ebbef843e,c072010f60f9a31fe566e35a7ad7d3cc</data>
      <data key="d7">16</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1249</data>
      <data key="d6">5c66a88612a245cb91fbba9c094f12fc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PROFITABILITY CALCULATION FOR SPECIAL PROJECTS QUIZ&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The quiz tests knowledge on calculating the cost of staff for special projects, focusing on relevant costs and choosing the option with the lowest incremental cost."</data>
      <data key="d2">c072010f60f9a31fe566e35a7ad7d3cc</data>
      <data key="d7">14</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1250</data>
      <data key="d6">b4c54fb7ce0b4b77afd5fbe5a8a2527f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RELEVANT COST OF RAW MATERIALS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A company is evaluating a new contract which requires 400 kg of raw material M. It has 100 kg of material M in inventory which were purchased recently. Since then the purchase price of material M has risen by 4% to $52 per kg. Raw material M is used regularly by the company in normal production. The relevant cost of material M for the contract is calculated based on the replacement cost of $52 per kg, giving a total cost of 400 * 52 = $20,800."</data>
      <data key="d2">181a68483be6482e8b136a2d540875a9</data>
      <data key="d4">5</data>
      <data key="d5">1251</data>
      <data key="d6">c8b60cdb74104667b5d2b4b70d74d039</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RELEVANT COST OF AN IDLE MACHINE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A machine owned by a company has been idle for some months but could now be used on a one-year contract which is under consideration. The net book value of the machine is $1,000. If not used on this contract, the machine could be sold now for a net amount of $1,200. After use on the contract, the machine would have no saleable value and the cost of disposing of it in one year&#8217;s time would be $800. The total relevant cost of the machine to the contract is $2,000."</data>
      <data key="d2">181a68483be6482e8b136a2d540875a9</data>
      <data key="d4">5</data>
      <data key="d5">1252</data>
      <data key="d6">333e294d7cc34df4abc47ad9ced3d186</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MAKE-OR-BUY DECISION COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz question asks about the relevant costs in a make-or-buy decision. The correct answer is the differential costs of both options."</data>
      <data key="d2">181a68483be6482e8b136a2d540875a9</data>
      <data key="d4">5</data>
      <data key="d5">1253</data>
      <data key="d6">15e66e10d12f4520abca20985d2cb39c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PROCESSING FURTHER OR SELLING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Loxwood Co is considering whether to sell its product, the tom, or process it further to make a different product, the tig. It has already incurred processing costs of $3 per unit in relation to the tom. If it sells the tom, it will sell 60,000 units at $8 per unit. Each unit of the tig requires 3 units of the tom and Loxwood Co would expect to sell 20,000 units of the tig. Further variable costs associated with the tig would be $6 per unit and further fixed costs would be $150,000. The selling price of the tig would be $40 per unit. The gain or loss of using the available units of tom to manufacture the tig is a $50,000 profit."</data>
      <data key="d2">181a68483be6482e8b136a2d540875a9</data>
      <data key="d4">5</data>
      <data key="d5">1254</data>
      <data key="d6">2a271d9b5d7b46fea4046d5590eed1d7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DISCONTINUATION OF A PRODUCT TO MAXIMIZE SHORT-TERM PROFIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Cornaur Products uses a scarce material in the manufacture of four products. Data per unit of each product is shown. In the next period, insufficient material will be available to manufacture all four products and therefore one product must be discontinued. To maximize short-term profit, the product with the lowest contribution per unit of limiting factor, i.e., Product W, should be discontinued."</data>
      <data key="d2">181a68483be6482e8b136a2d540875a9</data>
      <data key="d4">5</data>
      <data key="d5">1255</data>
      <data key="d6">99e372089bed4a0394af57175679f8e4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SHADOW PRICE OF MATERIAL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">The "SHADOW PRICE OF MATERIAL" is a concept related to Burseldon Co, which manufactures two products, the Cee and the Dee. Information about these products includes details such as selling price, material cost, labor cost, variable overhead, and fixed overhead. The context likely involves calculating the shadow price of material based on the provided data for these products.</data>
      <data key="d2">181a68483be6482e8b136a2d540875a9,fffb7846349c5bcd39f06b1473186140</data>
      <data key="d4">8</data>
      <data key="d5">1256</data>
      <data key="d6">62afe93767684ea38f861d20fb05ff71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SLACK RESOURCES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz involves identifying slack resources for Riley Co, which manufactures two products, eg and pey. The constraints are related to labour and machine time, and the quiz checks if these constraints are fully utilized or if there is slack."</data>
      <data key="d2">fffb7846349c5bcd39f06b1473186140</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">1257</data>
      <data key="d6">8fc1fbff7e6c459c93ce2c2f5a62226e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PROFIT-MAXIMISING OUTPUT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz involves determining the profit-maximising output of product x for Bruno Co, which manufactures two products, x and y. The constraints are related to materials and labour time, and the solution involves using simultaneous equations."</data>
      <data key="d2">fffb7846349c5bcd39f06b1473186140</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">1258</data>
      <data key="d6">04b3ae04020349a9bc568f26d17eab14</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REQUIRED SALES FOR TARGET PROFIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz involves calculating the number of units Morava Co must sell to generate a target profit. The product has a variable cost and a selling price, and the quiz uses the amended break-even formula for sales volume required to achieve the target profit."</data>
      <data key="d2">fffb7846349c5bcd39f06b1473186140</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">1259</data>
      <data key="d6">bbc4d367c60f41ad8a279c12e5cc7da6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BREAKEVEN POINT IN SALES REVENUE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz involves calculating the breakeven point in sales revenue for Dilnot Co, which produces and sells rucksacks and shoulder bags in a standard mix. The quiz uses the contribution to sales ratio and fixed costs to determine the breakeven point."</data>
      <data key="d2">fffb7846349c5bcd39f06b1473186140</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">1260</data>
      <data key="d6">9a1aff251eda416ea6270e6158e663fc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES PRICE CALCULATION FOR RUCKSACK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sales price for Rucksack is calculated as Variable cost / (1 - C/S ratio) = $54 / (1 - 0.4) = $90."</data>
      <data key="d2">3ef6ffef196ce21eb853bd7cf7b00da2</data>
      <data key="d7">3</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1261</data>
      <data key="d6">7a9e50846c274338ab09e7313b540edb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES PRICE CALCULATION FOR SHOULDER BAG&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sales price for Shoulder bag is calculated as Variable cost / (1 - C/S ratio) = $32.50 / (1 - 0.5) = $65."</data>
      <data key="d2">3ef6ffef196ce21eb853bd7cf7b00da2</data>
      <data key="d7">3</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1262</data>
      <data key="d6">b268cc3ef860434ba663dd46af633cc5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONTRIBUTION CALCULATION FOR RUCKSACK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Contribution for Rucksack is calculated as Sales price * C/S ratio = $90 * 0.4 = $36."</data>
      <data key="d2">3ef6ffef196ce21eb853bd7cf7b00da2</data>
      <data key="d7">3</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">1263</data>
      <data key="d6">1c9f67904a4c4fcc8cdac6a605900248</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONTRIBUTION CALCULATION FOR SHOULDER BAG&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Contribution for Shoulder bag is calculated as Sales price * C/S ratio = $65 * 0.5 = $32.50."</data>
      <data key="d2">3ef6ffef196ce21eb853bd7cf7b00da2</data>
      <data key="d7">3</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">1264</data>
      <data key="d6">e00c403d1dc84ba6a37ee193596e320f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WEIGHTED AVERAGE SALES REVENUE FOR SALES MIX&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Weighted average sales revenue for the sales mix is calculated as $90 * (3/(3 + 2)) + $65 * (2/(3 + 2)) = $80."</data>
      <data key="d2">3ef6ffef196ce21eb853bd7cf7b00da2</data>
      <data key="d7">3</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1265</data>
      <data key="d6">3f2e726c3b624fe7bf11de9be2c0457e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WEIGHTED AVERAGE CONTRIBUTION FOR SALES MIX&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Weighted average contribution for the sales mix is calculated as $36 * (3/(3 + 2)) + $32.50 * (2/(3 + 2)) = $34.60."</data>
      <data key="d2">3ef6ffef196ce21eb853bd7cf7b00da2</data>
      <data key="d7">3</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">1266</data>
      <data key="d6">f71dc0c394f04771af7e2ed37f85647e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARKET SKIMMING PRICING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"MARKET SKIMMING PRICING" is a pricing strategy where a high price is initially charged for a product, such as an anti-malaria drug, to maximize profits from early adopters who are willing to pay more. This approach is particularly effective for unique products with high development costs and significant barriers to entry. Over time, the price is gradually lowered to attract more price-sensitive customers. This strategy is also appropriate when the price sensitivity of demand is unknown, as it aims to maximize unit profit during the early stages of the product life cycle.</data>
      <data key="d2">324c0fb49870acc800392f7d78685514,3ef6ffef196ce21eb853bd7cf7b00da2,952e2d04d2cd9b755ccdb34c8be68396</data>
      <data key="d7">19</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">1267</data>
      <data key="d6">2fea9c1856e54a91b79a9ce85755fbf5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SELLING PRICE TO MAXIMIZE PROFIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Quiz on determining the selling price to maximize profit using the equation P = 60 - 0.01Q and total cost TC = 5,000 + 8Q. The selling price that maximizes profit is $34."</data>
      <data key="d2">3ef6ffef196ce21eb853bd7cf7b00da2</data>
      <data key="d7">19</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1268</data>
      <data key="d6">7823b4c5b3364c5f890d05f33a46bdde</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MAINTAINING MARK-UP ON FULL COST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Quiz on maintaining a mark-up of 25% on full cost for Roe, which sold 2,000 units at a selling price of $100 with fixed costs of $40,000. The selling price to maintain the mark-up is $107.50."</data>
      <data key="d2">3ef6ffef196ce21eb853bd7cf7b00da2</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">1269</data>
      <data key="d6">183f3a0b73ff41c5bb4a19fd7adf0c1d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FULL COST PLUS PRICING CALCULATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Full costs in current year = (2,000 * $100)/125% = $160,000. Of which, Variable costs = $160,000 &#8722; $40,000 = $120,000. Next year: variable costs = $120,000 * 110% = $132,000. Therefore, total costs = $132,000 + $40,000 = $172,000. To maintain 25% mark-up on cost, sales revenue = $172,000 * 1.25 = $215,000. Therefore selling price per unit = $215,000/2,000 = $107.50."</data>
      <data key="d2">bfcf79d5de016af045c8328487a8850c</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">1270</data>
      <data key="d6">392e06f17d724484a9cfb85fe69aac50</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;QUIZ ON FULL COST PLUS PRICING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz tests knowledge on full cost plus pricing, including its appropriateness for long-term pricing and its ability to guarantee profit if budgeted sales levels are achieved."</data>
      <data key="d2">bfcf79d5de016af045c8328487a8850c</data>
      <data key="d7">2</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1271</data>
      <data key="d6">6f49e00cdac04a358173ecd40351ee00</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRICE ELASTICITY OF DEMAND CALCULATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"PED = % change in quantity demanded/% change in price = [(2,600 &#8722; 2,000)/2,000 * 100%]/[(40 &#8722; 50)/50 * 100%] = 30%/20% = 1.50."</data>
      <data key="d2">bfcf79d5de016af045c8328487a8850c</data>
      <data key="d7">19</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1272</data>
      <data key="d6">3fef96af4ec343da8c34f8b09518de8a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;QUIZ ON PRICE ELASTICITY OF DEMAND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">The "QUIZ ON PRICE ELASTICITY OF DEMAND" calculates and tests the price elasticity of demand for a product based on changes in price and quantity sold. It involves determining the elasticity by analyzing different prices and quantities sold, ensuring a comprehensive understanding of how price changes impact demand.</data>
      <data key="d2">238ba7ae5def49a914d13c1bcf1e1332,bfcf79d5de016af045c8328487a8850c</data>
      <data key="d7">19</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1273</data>
      <data key="d6">bd403eff654e42c997e5656a2b1c1a20</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EXPECTED VALUES IN DECISION MAKING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Expected values in decision making involve calculating the average outcome when the future includes scenarios that may or may not happen. It is useful for recurring events but ignores the risk associated with decisions."</data>
      <data key="d2">bfcf79d5de016af045c8328487a8850c</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1274</data>
      <data key="d6">5763d829837144f199fac2b490b38110</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;QUIZ ON EXPECTED VALUES IN DECISION MAKING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz tests understanding of expected values in decision making, focusing on their usefulness for recurring events and their limitation in ignoring risk."</data>
      <data key="d2">bfcf79d5de016af045c8328487a8850c</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1275</data>
      <data key="d6">234c6f1859f0405ab607f0be53e7b06c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MINIMAX REGRET CRITERION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">The minimax regret criterion is a decision rule used in decision theory for minimizing the maximum possible regret. Regret is defined as the difference between the payoff from the best action and all other actions.</data>
      <data key="d2">bfcf79d5de016af045c8328487a8850c,cd8b354390a3589e53eb5960af7c375b</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1276</data>
      <data key="d6">21800eab85b94d4880bcada7a60763e5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;QUIZ ON MINIMAX REGRET CRITERION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">The "QUIZ ON MINIMAX REGRET CRITERION" is a quiz designed to test the application of the minimax regret criterion in decision making. It involves using a given regret matrix to decide which venue NG should use to stage an entertainment event. The quiz scenario includes different fee levels and staffing mixes, challenging participants to apply the minimax regret criterion effectively.</data>
      <data key="d2">bfcf79d5de016af045c8328487a8850c,cd8b354390a3589e53eb5960af7c375b</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">1277</data>
      <data key="d6">b8bb28a7a9624b6d805be89adfe29eb5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VALUE OF SURVEY FOR CINEMA DECISION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">The "VALUE OF SURVEY FOR CINEMA DECISION" involves a decision-making scenario where Greenwood Movies Co must decide whether to build a small or large cinema based on market demand data and associated risks. Additionally, this quiz requires calculating the maximum amount Greenwood Movies Co should pay for a survey to predict demand for a new cinema. The calculation is based on expected values with and without the survey.</data>
      <data key="d2">8cf592364030d479cf1085a135ca8d22,bfcf79d5de016af045c8328487a8850c</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">1278</data>
      <data key="d6">61f26f8850504d56a6b7cd764c33299d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;QUIZ ON VALUE OF SURVEY FOR CINEMA DECISION&quot;">
      <data key="d0" />
      <data key="d1" />
      <data key="d2">bfcf79d5de016af045c8328487a8850c</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1279</data>
      <data key="d6">d4456fac0ada4b6fbe3cfee873403d00</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DECISION RULES FOR RISK-AVERSE INVESTOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz tests knowledge of decision rules suitable for a risk-averse investor, including Maximin and Minimax regret."</data>
      <data key="d2">8cf592364030d479cf1085a135ca8d22</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1280</data>
      <data key="d6">f8fd3fcf650b47b2b1692506ebe77762</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SENSITIVITY TO CHANGES IN DEMAND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz involves calculating the sensitivity of Product Tom to changes in demand, given its cost card and expected demand."</data>
      <data key="d2">8cf592364030d479cf1085a135ca8d22</data>
      <data key="d7">19</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1281</data>
      <data key="d6">d95acc24180c47caa34114627d501592</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FLEXED BUDGET&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">A flexed budget adjusts the original budget to reflect the actual level of activity, providing a more accurate comparison of actual performance against budgeted figures. It is calculated by adjusting the budgeted figures based on the actual number of customers or units. A flexed budget is prepared at the same level of activity as the actual output. For example, for the month of May, a flexed budget would include calculations for food sales, drink sales, total revenue, variable costs (such as staff wages, food costs, drink costs, and energy costs), contribution, fixed costs (including manager's and chef's pay, rent, rates, and depreciation), and operating profit. This type of budget is updated in response to changes in the level of activity, ensuring that the budget remains relevant and accurate.</data>
      <data key="d2">8cf592364030d479cf1085a135ca8d22,8f25b512050c59a9f6a09fd4549bce3c,a90ec32176608282b11bed138f7007da,e6dcb0a0bf01250a84f45fc9b4de8a13,ed11d697d920edcbfc6a01ce2c257056</data>
      <data key="d7">19</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">7</data>
      <data key="d5">1282</data>
      <data key="d6">f4753ab09adc42a9a52754e95440d4b9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ZERO-BASED BUDGETING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">Zero-Based Budgeting is a method where the budget is prepared from scratch, with all expenses needing justification for each new period. Each new budget is started from a 'zero base,' and every function within an organization is analyzed for its needs and costs. This approach helps in cost control and efficiency but is more time-consuming. This quiz tests knowledge of Zero-Based Budgeting, a method where all activities are re-evaluated each time a budget is formulated.</data>
      <data key="d2">2343dedcae64d2e174ab981dfc3b23a0,6cf39866faa0b75b5fd5a86e16914122,8cf592364030d479cf1085a135ca8d22</data>
      <data key="d7">7</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">1283</data>
      <data key="d6">12f5a7c56b454a3d8aae97f65908f96b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BEYOND BUDGETING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz tests knowledge of Beyond Budgeting, which involves the use of stretch goals and devolution of resource decisions to front-line teams."</data>
      <data key="d2">8cf592364030d479cf1085a135ca8d22</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1284</data>
