    <node id="&quot;SALES VOLUME VARIANCE QUIZ&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz involves calculating the sales volume variance using marginal costing principles. Darwin Co budgeted to sell 25,000 units at a budgeted selling price of $20 per unit, with a budgeted contribution of $12 per unit. The actual sales were 26,500 units, resulting in a sales volume variance of $18,000 favorable."</data>
      <data key="d2">01294aa83ab1143451866d43087f9eba</data>
