    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OBJECTIVE OF THE INITIATIVE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">The objective of the initiative introduced by a local authority is Efficiency, which means achieving greater output for each unit of input. This initiative is designed to ensure that more is accomplished with the same amount of resources. The context of this initiative is highlighted in a quiz that involves identifying its objective, with options including quality improvement, efficiency, effectiveness, and economy. However, the correct objective is Efficiency, focusing on maximizing output relative to input.</data>
      <data key="d2">9c3ce103fc83f7ae19dde7d2e5b4ef01,a5a7a3e9a59209ce811c1f9470684fa6</data>
      <data key="d7">4</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1299</data>
      <data key="d6">b3d3e8ba2ede4574a0498f082f0c15ae</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FITZGERALD AND MOON MODEL DIMENSIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Fitzgerald and Moon building block model provides six dimensions under which performance in service industries can be measured. The quiz question asks which of the following is NOT one of the six dimensions: Resource allocation, Quality of service, Staff satisfaction, Flexibility. The correct answer is C."</data>
      <data key="d2">a5a7a3e9a59209ce811c1f9470684fa6</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">1300</data>
      <data key="d6">8686013390614eca9116ccbab27431d7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHARACTERISTICS OF A SERVICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The quiz question asks which of the following is NOT a typical characteristic of a service: Each service provided has unique physical features, Each service is provided when the customer wants it, Each service is consumed when it is produced, Each service only exists when it is being experienced by the customer. The correct answer is A."</data>
      <data key="d2">a5a7a3e9a59209ce811c1f9470684fa6</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1301</data>
      <data key="d6">fd8c8b7e3b9248abb1d8cb8958ab86d3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EXTERNAL PRESSURES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The quiz question lists examples of pressures that a hospital might face and asks which of the following are external pressures: Fewer doctors qualifying, Increased medicine prices, Stricter government targets in relation to waiting lists, Shortage of beds for seriously ill patients. The correct answer is C."</data>
      <data key="d2">a5a7a3e9a59209ce811c1f9470684fa6</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">1302</data>
