    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ADVANTAGE OF THE BALANCED SCORECARD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The quiz question asks which of the following is an advantage of the balanced scorecard: It provides a clear ranking of performance measures, It encourages managers to focus on the financial aspects of performance, It encourages managers to take a short-term view of performance, It considers internal and external issues. The correct answer is D."</data>
      <data key="d2">a5a7a3e9a59209ce811c1f9470684fa6</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1303</data>
      <data key="d6">d78ce7696ff14234a544de945ffe40d6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PLASTICS DIVISION&#8217;S RESIDUAL INCOME&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The quiz question asks what is the plastic division&#8217;s residual income given the following data: The plastics division of Ladmar has just reported a divisional return on capital employed of 30% for the last 12 months. The capital employed in the plastics division is $1,200,000. The company&#8217;s overall return on capital employed is 18%, and the overall cost of capital is 14%. The plastics division&#8217;s cost of capital is 13%. The correct answer is C. The divisional profit is $1.2m * 30% = $360,000. Imputed interest is $1.2m * 13% = $156,000. Therefore, residual income = $360,000 &#8722; $156,000 = $204,000."</data>
      <data key="d2">a5a7a3e9a59209ce811c1f9470684fa6</data>
      <data key="d7">23</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1304</data>
      <data key="d6">59b21508be904875af22b5c1cfdcd211</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INVESTMENT CENTRE MANAGER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The quiz question asks which one of the following individuals is most likely to be an investment centre manager: The sales manager, The maintenance department manager, A portfolio manager, The manager of a factory, who has the authority to buy new machinery. The correct answer is D."</data>
      <data key="d2">a5a7a3e9a59209ce811c1f9470684fa6</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1305</data>
      <data key="d6">e9c7a1d505b14229afbbef7c0d04751e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERFORMANCE MEASUREMENT OF DIVISIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The quiz question asks which of the following statements is correct in relation to measuring the performance of both divisions: Both methods will favour Division A, Both methods will favour Division B, ROI will favour Division A, RI will favour Division B, RI will favour Division A, ROI will favour Division B. The correct answer is A."</data>
      <data key="d2">a5a7a3e9a59209ce811c1f9470684fa6</data>
      <data key="d7">15</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1306</data>
      <data key="d6">4b0efcd54efc40e8a884ac6c31deada2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RETURN ON INVESTMENT FOR DIVISION D&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The quiz question asks what is the Return on Investment for Division D given the following data: Division D currently has $2,000,000 of net assets included in its accounting records on 31 December 20X2 and is showing an operating profit of $280,000. No entries have yet been made for depreciation. However, the accounting records need to be amended for transactions in relation to non-current assets that took place on 30 December 20X2. A machine with net realisable value of $100,000 was sold for $125,000 and replaced with a machine costing $300,000. A full 20% depreciation charge is charged on machinery in the year of purchase, but no charge is made in the year of sale. The correct answer is B. Revised profit = $280,000 + $25,000 (Profit on sale of old machinery) - $60,000 (Depreciation charge on new machinery) = $245,000. Revised assets = $2,000,000 - $100,000 (Old machinery) + $300,000 (New machinery) - $300,000 (cash paid for new machinery) &#8722; $60,000 (Depreciation charge on new machinery)."</data>
      <data key="d2">a5a7a3e9a59209ce811c1f9470684fa6</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">1307</data>
      <data key="d6">0970f08f3d1a4d638d44e2ccb9237382</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;QUALITY OF SERVICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0" />
      <data key="d1">"QUALITY OF SERVICE" is a dimension of Fitzgerald and Moon's Building Block Model that measures the quality of service provided to customers. Quality of service is indicated by the number of regular customers, customer satisfaction, complaints, complimentary letters, reported cases of food poisoning, and service delivery data.</data>
      <data key="d2">05e25a78a53e695fd01856df3a302292,a5a7a3e9a59209ce811c1f9470684fa6,e7d75450db353b8413fb68bdd98ac99c</data>
