    <node id="&quot;ENVIRONMENTAL MANAGEMENT ACCOUNTING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Environmental Management Accounting (EMA) involves the identification, collection, and analysis of both physical and monetary information related to environmental activities. It helps management make informed decisions by tracking the use of resources, waste generation, and environment-related costs, earnings, and savings."</data>
      <data key="d2">1198b5b37a51d0315db68af2bdb139bd,39e1257b70d1902a0d6b2502ce5b27b5,7b3dd175d38a9f290c9e33467fc9f8a0,bf895221917dacb42684c64f347d269d,cdba52ee4f0e2669ccb29b10b23e609a</data>
