    <node id="&quot;INTERNAL FAILURE COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"INTERNAL FAILURE COSTS" refer to the expenses associated with addressing and rectifying issues related to environmental waste and pollution within an organization before these issues impact the external environment. These costs are incurred during the process of cleaning up and managing environmental waste internally. Additionally, activities classified as environmental internal failure costs are those identified and managed within the organization to prevent any adverse effects on the external environment.</data>
      <data key="d2">af274426ef7643f0032ad5ea75f77a78,e38eef21c8adf52125bdece53d9dd6f3</data>
