    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BUDGETED BREAK-EVEN SALES VOLUME&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz involves calculating the budgeted break-even sales volume for a division manufacturing a single product. It considers the unit cost structure and the budgeted production volume."</data>
      <data key="d2">42cd34884f35d28c36f2156eefcb5c76</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1395</data>
      <data key="d6">34b704124fe94c2f933a344c11165f2e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BREAK-EVEN POINT FORMULA&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">The "BREAK-EVEN POINT FORMULA" is used to determine the level of sales at which total revenues equal total costs, resulting in neither profit nor loss. The formula is expressed as "Break-even point = Fixed costs / Contribution per unit" or alternatively as "Break-even point = Total budgeted fixed costs / Contribution per unit." Both expressions highlight the importance of fixed costs and the contribution per unit in calculating the break-even point.</data>
      <data key="d2">9ed90a7cdaefe000167cdff9a7d5f4b1,b19ebe566f006f8d570bb588768ba2dd</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1396</data>
      <data key="d6">e429a497b01c40f3aef7e2205eaf01d8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARGIN OF SAFETY RATIO&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A quiz that asks for the margin of safety ratio given the production capacity, budgeted sales volume, and break-even volume."</data>
      <data key="d2">9ed90a7cdaefe000167cdff9a7d5f4b1</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1397</data>
      <data key="d6">f521933b91564693b07bd838160083ac</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARGIN OF SAFETY RATIO FORMULA&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Margin of safety ratio = (Budgeted sales volume - Break-even volume) / Budgeted sales volume"</data>
      <data key="d2">9ed90a7cdaefe000167cdff9a7d5f4b1</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1398</data>
      <data key="d6">e0d361b6991b40debf5599e86f2638ca</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VOLUME OF SALES REQUIRED AT NEW SELLING PRICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A quiz that asks for the volume of sales required at a new selling price to increase profit by 10%, given the current variable cost, selling price, budgeted sales volume, and fixed costs."</data>
