      <data key="d6">617a76d54ed546e29428a31dea955b96</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES REVENUE LINE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The sales revenue line starts at zero and increases steadily as more units are sold."</data>
      <data key="d2">bd5dde4a09d21b8f87a58c1da900cd8e</data>
      <data key="d7">6</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1403</data>
      <data key="d6">c88ffd2aa7284ac38eb4351c5fad6f44</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TOTAL COSTS LINE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The total costs line starts at zero but rises more quickly at first. After a certain point, it slows down and runs parallel to the sales revenue line, keeping a consistent gap between them."</data>
      <data key="d2">bd5dde4a09d21b8f87a58c1da900cd8e</data>
      <data key="d7">6</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1404</data>
      <data key="d6">0dace3b24df14aae909a2815653e9db1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WEIGHTED AVERAGE CONTRIBUTION TO SALES RATIO&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">The "WEIGHTED AVERAGE CONTRIBUTION TO SALES RATIO" is a financial metric used to assess the impact of altering the mix of products produced and sold on the overall profitability. It is calculated by dividing the total contribution by the total revenue, expressed as the weighted average contribution to sales ratio (WA C/S ratio). This ratio helps in understanding how changes in product mix can affect the overall financial performance of a business.</data>
      <data key="d2">a5995fbeaf1e8bc061f219d79f9689d1,bd5dde4a09d21b8f87a58c1da900cd8e</data>
      <data key="d7">6</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">1405</data>
      <data key="d6">b3cfde857302479aa59b91d6648a40df</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BREAK-EVEN SALES REVENUE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz involves calculating the break-even sales revenue for a company producing multiple products, given the product mix ratio, contribution to sales ratio for each product, and general fixed costs."</data>
      <data key="d2">bd5dde4a09d21b8f87a58c1da900cd8e</data>
      <data key="d7">6</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">1406</data>
      <data key="d6">01a52a986b6a444badc83fb11aa7a160</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARGIN OF SAFETY IN UNITS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz involves calculating the margin of safety in units for a company that makes a single product, given the selling price per unit, fixed costs, contribution/sales ratio, and sales revenue."</data>
      <data key="d2">bd5dde4a09d21b8f87a58c1da900cd8e</data>
      <data key="d7">6</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">1407</data>
      <data key="d6">2516b3485b754bdabf6820863c918e3d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BREAK-EVEN POINT IN SALES REVENUE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz involves calculating the break-even point in sales revenue for a company that manufactures and sells tables and chairs in a standard mix, given the variable cost per unit, contribution to sales ratio, and annual fixed costs."</data>
      <data key="d2">bd5dde4a09d21b8f87a58c1da900cd8e</data>
      <data key="d7">6</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">1408</data>
      <data key="d6">0523ed6330f4429f8468f5b49169c940</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BREAK-EVEN REVENUE FORMULA&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">The "BREAK-EVEN REVENUE FORMULA" is used to determine the revenue needed to cover all fixed costs, ensuring that a business neither makes a profit nor incurs a loss. The formula is consistently defined as "Break-even revenue = Fixed cost / Weighted average C/S ratio" or "Break-even revenue = Fixed costs / Weighted average C/S ratio." This calculation involves dividing the total fixed costs by the weighted average contribution margin ratio (C/S ratio), providing a clear threshold for financial stability.</data>
      <data key="d2">2ec07a1112223c3286057400e3b2eca9,4a96eda99b984c39366e7b2eb363fe96,a5995fbeaf1e8bc061f219d79f9689d1,b19ebe566f006f8d570bb588768ba2dd</data>
      <data key="d7">3</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">1409</data>
      <data key="d6">0b7ac591dfd34971b24d38e344b40c37</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARGIN OF SAFETY PERCENTAGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz involves calculating the margin of safety percentage for Log Co&#8217;s only product. The quiz provides sales price, direct materials, direct labour, variable production overhead, fixed production overhead, profit per unit, and sales commission, and asks for the margin of safety percentage."</data>
      <data key="d2">b19ebe566f006f8d570bb588768ba2dd</data>
      <data key="d7">3</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1410</data>
      <data key="d6">2864f68297e94d7e84213833e22da077</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OPERATING GEARING RATIO&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This quiz involves calculating the operating profit for Logan Co if its sales increase by 15%. The quiz provides the current sales, operating profit, and operating gearing ratio, and asks for the new operating profit."</data>
