      <data key="d6">040b86f496dc4930a895f2c21cb0731c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES QUANTITY CONTRIBUTION VARIANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">The "Sales Quantity Contribution Variance" measures the impact on profit due to the difference between the actual number of units sold and the budgeted number of units sold. Specifically, it assesses the effect on contribution and profit when the total quantity sold differs from the budgeted total quantity. In Noble's case, this variance is $11,700 favorable, indicating that more units were sold than budgeted, leading to higher profits. The quiz provides budgeted and actual data for a company selling two products and asks what the total sales quantity contribution variance for the period is. The variance is considered favorable when the total quantity sold exceeds the budgeted quantity.</data>
      <data key="d2">2343dedcae64d2e174ab981dfc3b23a0,27fde199847b14399dfca384e07a77a4,8f25b512050c59a9f6a09fd4549bce3c,adea171e6847df263c60c9085bf66897,f97d81426ba6b512862db11eb6fe561a</data>
      <data key="d7">27</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">5</data>
      <data key="d5">1494</data>
      <data key="d6">e13ed464574f483c9f1db5f569e91445</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MATERIALS MIX VARIANCE STATEMENTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"QUIZZES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The quiz asks which statements about the materials mix variance for a company manufacturing different products using the same type of material are correct."</data>
