    <node id="&quot;NON-FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE INDICATORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">Non-financial performance indicators are metrics used to assess various aspects of a company's performance that are not directly related to financial outcomes. These indicators encompass areas such as quality, customer satisfaction, employee engagement, and operational efficiency, which can lead to better long-term performance. They complement financial performance measures and help avoid excessive cost-cutting that may harm the business. Examples of non-financial performance indicators include customer satisfaction, employee turnover, operational efficiency, student transfer rates, late enrolments, exam pass rates, labor turnover, student complaints, and the average number of employees.</data>
      <data key="d2">45719ba72685f5aeb3a5f78de9823406,a22eae134ce57b58870ae60a9afaf634,bc0524558467e4e3eec1a2e2e05b5d33</data>
      <data key="d7">23</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">6</data>
      <data key="d5">1509</data>
      <data key="d6">6b5c42bba0ec48c1a5de177a7f1b9bfc</data>
    </node>
