    <node id="&quot;NET PROFIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">Net profit is the amount of income left after all expenses, including taxes, interest, and head office costs, have been deducted from total revenue. In the year 20X0, net profit was calculated as $78,000 out of $200,000, resulting in a net profit margin of 39%. In the year 20X1, net profit was $80,000 out of $238,500, resulting in a net profit margin of 33.5%.</data>
      <data key="d2">312c3cf9edbc058c6e810c1e9c9cd81a,35c28eb2f5a6b9394801984195b014d9,f41491fbf8c72d2afdc444dec24f9e1e</data>
