    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DIRECT LABOUR&quot;">
      <data key="d0" />
      <data key="d1">"Direct labour" refers to the wages and salaries of employees that can be directly attributed to the production of specific goods or services. It is a variable cost that increases by 3% every quarter to reflect the increase in sales volume. Additionally, in Q3, there is a one-off increase of $5,000 to account for training costs.</data>
      <data key="d2">16965b8a36bbe6bac45c7b81a6b17c48,2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a,9674b500a570fa3a7bf9957943ff48a7</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">1565</data>
      <data key="d6">17127080df794121830177e93631aa3b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ENTERPRISE RESOURCE PLANNING SYSTEM (ERPS)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">The Enterprise Resource Planning System (ERPS) is a comprehensive software system designed to facilitate a seamless flow of information across an entire organization. By utilizing a single database, it ensures that various programs used by different departments can access and share data efficiently. ERPS is an integrated information system that supports multiple simultaneous users, providing real-time information. It includes essential modules for accounting, inventory control, and other critical business processes, thereby enhancing the overall operational efficiency of the organization.</data>
      <data key="d2">2ad6c0ee81f4b0da1c6b2f2821dff6b6,9f2566c80157a915eedb77a1d6dc9dad</data>
      <data key="d7">21</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">8</data>
      <data key="d5">1566</data>
      <data key="d6">374a8f81e6304b6d90b44cdceb90ecb4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REPORTING PROGRAMME&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A reporting programme is a software tool that analyzes data from the ERPS database and provides reports, summaries, and data visualizations such as bar charts, line charts, and pie charts. It includes a 'drill down' facility for detailed analysis and allows managers to design their own reports."</data>
      <data key="d2">2ad6c0ee81f4b0da1c6b2f2821dff6b6</data>
      <data key="d7">21</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">1567</data>
      <data key="d6">8c6aafd2a5da496385bea2c69be03a5a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OPERATIONAL DECISION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"OPERATIONAL DECISION" refers to a decision that is within the control of the organization as a whole and typically involves day-to-day management activities. It encompasses decisions related to the day-to-day running of the business, such as reordering inventory when levels reach a certain point and increasing staff levels.</data>
      <data key="d2">002794ec024434f7ac2bd26217b3897d,2ad6c0ee81f4b0da1c6b2f2821dff6b6</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">1568</data>
      <data key="d6">06b9da0d4d9b4d6bb762bd2eeca7028a</data>
    </node>
