    <node id="&quot;EVALUATING THE IMPACT OF ACTIVITY-BASED COSTING ON PRICING STRATEGIES AT BBB&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Brick By Brick (BBB) provides a range of building services, including garage conversions (GC) and extensions to properties (EX). BBB has a policy to price all jobs at budgeted total cost plus 50%. Overheads are currently absorbed on a labour hour basis. However, BBB has found that it has fewer GC contracts than expected, and it believes that this is because the current overhead absorption method apportions an excessive amount of overheads to GC, leading to a price that is uncompetitive. The company is now considering moving to an activity-based cost approach."</data>
      <data key="d2">94bad6b839398ff56bb1fd1316fb6bc0</data>
      <data key="d7">0</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">6</data>
      <data key="d5">1574</data>
      <data key="d6">3ddb886b220c4bb2ab3d68f7f29ce5c5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ACTIVITY-BASED COSTING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">Activity-based costing (ABC) is a costing method that assigns overhead and indirect costs to related products and services by identifying cost drivers. This methodology involves identifying the activities within an organization and assigning the cost of each activity to all products and services based on their actual consumption. By doing so, ABC helps in more accurately tracing costs to products and services. The method allocates overheads to products based on activities that drive costs, such as machine setups, machine running, procurement, and delivery.</data>
      <data key="d2">1198b5b37a51d0315db68af2bdb139bd,7b3dd175d38a9f290c9e33467fc9f8a0,7ec0c404cb341da6ab1e2341852f4c97,94bad6b839398ff56bb1fd1316fb6bc0</data>
      <data key="d7">0</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">9</data>
      <data key="d5">1575</data>
      <data key="d6">2f482bb08d564072a5ff4f2509dfdda6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CURRENT METHOD OF ABSORBING OVERHEADS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The current method of absorbing overheads at BBB is based on labour hours."</data>
      <data key="d2">94bad6b839398ff56bb1fd1316fb6bc0</data>
      <data key="d7">0</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
