    <node id="&quot;EVALUATING COSTING METHODS FOR ACCURATE PROCEDURE PRICING AT BECKLEY HILL HOSPITAL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Beckley Hill (BH) is a private hospital evaluating the implementation of activity-based costing (ABC) to more accurately price its procedures. The hospital currently uses a simple overhead allocation method but is considering ABC to better reflect the costs associated with different activities such as administrative time, nursing, catering, and general facility costs."</data>
      <data key="d2">03721d9b5064cc002df514cca9896c3b</data>
      <data key="d7">0</data>
