    <node id="&quot;OPTIMIZING RESOURCE ALLOCATION AND PROFIT MAXIMIZATION FOR BVX'S GARDEN FURNITURE PRODUCTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"BVX manufactures three garden furniture products - chairs, benches, and tables. The budgeted unit cost and resource requirements of each item are detailed, and the company faces a constraint on the supply of specialist timber. The sales director has accepted an order for specific quantities of each product, which must be supplied to avoid a financial penalty."</data>
      <data key="d2">feda6b4c9964e8465efd20e4a6167582</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2130</data>
      <data key="d6">5c21149e0f4f4077bdcba68bea39ccf6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BUDGETED UNIT COST AND RESOURCE REQUIREMENTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The budgeted unit cost and resource requirements for chairs, benches, and tables include timber cost, direct labour cost, variable overhead cost, and fixed overhead cost."</data>
      <data key="d2">feda6b4c9964e8465efd20e4a6167582</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2131</data>
      <data key="d6">998b6deec580462bb239114002c74c61</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SPECIALIST TIMBER CONSTRAINT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
