      <data key="d6">4c7b46bb8ce94b1fb336745e31a9c95e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ACCEPTED ORDER QUANTITIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The sales director has accepted an order for 500 chairs, 100 benches, and 150 tables, which must be supplied to avoid a financial penalty of $2,000."</data>
      <data key="d2">feda6b4c9964e8465efd20e4a6167582</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2133</data>
      <data key="d6">9e7d62d41a684d6bbb6cac6b9a25056e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SPECIALIST TIMBER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Specialist timber is a type of timber that is limited in supply to 20,000 square meters per annum due to a problem with the supplier."</data>
      <data key="d2">e7783a6241d7d8fbb8f2530d08f784e9</data>
      <data key="d7">26</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2134</data>
      <data key="d6">c98da14c4d8d4f529aac37adfeb5e101</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LINEAR PROGRAMMING FOR OPTIMAL PRODUCTION PLAN WITH RESOURCE CONSTRAINTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A company uses linear programming to establish an optimal production plan to maximize profit, considering constraints on materials and labor. The company must meet a minimum order requirement for one of its products while optimizing the use of limited resources."</data>
      <data key="d2">e7783a6241d7d8fbb8f2530d08f784e9</data>
      <data key="d7">11</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2135</data>
      <data key="d6">631b76038b3841bbb1c4a58b9bf2268d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONSTRAINT EQUATIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Constraint equations in linear programming are mathematical expressions that represent the limitations or requirements of the problem. In this case, the constraints include the availability of materials and labor, as well as the minimum order requirement for product A."</data>
      <data key="d2">e7783a6241d7d8fbb8f2530d08f784e9</data>
      <data key="d7">11</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2136</data>
      <data key="d6">18cd813cfbb3486e8417b1cfd2acd9ae</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GRAPHICAL SOLUTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Graphical solution involves plotting the constraints on a 2D line chart to determine the optimal production plan. The optimal point is the intersection of the lines: a = 1,000 and materials constraint 3a + 4b = 30,000."</data>
      <data key="d2">026b22934152d61a6b625fae071b3bcd</data>
      <data key="d7">11</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2137</data>
      <data key="d6">f37a095014404f31abec3d2faecd4ade</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OPTIMAL PRODUCTION PLAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The optimal production plan is to make 1,000 units of A and 6,750 units of B."</data>
      <data key="d2">026b22934152d61a6b625fae071b3bcd</data>
      <data key="d7">11</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2138</data>
      <data key="d6">f87e7d895b1e41bca129cccaf0bb4a0e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OPTIMAL PRODUCTION STRATEGY FOR TABLET CO USING LINEAR PROGRAMMING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Tablet Co makes two types of tablet computers, the Xeno (X) and the Yong (Y). The company uses linear programming to determine the optimal production plan to maximize contribution, considering constraints in build, program, and test stages."</data>
      <data key="d2">026b22934152d61a6b625fae071b3bcd</data>
      <data key="d7">11</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2139</data>
      <data key="d6">b4f04f096ed44e5f9b81b5f6a2ea527b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONTRIBUTION FUNCTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Contribution function: C = 30x + 40y, where x is the number of units of Xeno to be produced and y is the number of units of Yong to be produced."</data>
      <data key="d2">026b22934152d61a6b625fae071b3bcd</data>
      <data key="d7">11</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2140</data>
      <data key="d6">ad0568225890493588c9f14be4970437</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DRILLING PROGRAMME&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A drilling programme refers to the planned activities and operations involved in drilling for oil. The success of this programme is dependent on prior geological testing and the likelihood of finding commercially viable quantities of oil."</data>
      <data key="d2">2fd1d6134ec72f26d7a900391b7261fd</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2141</data>
      <data key="d6">6f3791b17c2f45eda4703610b3be7ebd</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NET PRESENT VALUE (NPV)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Net present value (NPV) is a financial metric that calculates the present value of all cash inflows and outflows associated with a project, discounted at a specific rate. It is used to assess the profitability of an investment."</data>
      <data key="d2">2fd1d6134ec72f26d7a900391b7261fd</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2142</data>
      <data key="d6">3f394dc07477404289f766189df6bd26</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DECISION TREE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A decision tree is a graphical representation of possible solutions to a decision based on certain conditions. It helps in identifying the best course of action by mapping out different decision paths and their potential outcomes."</data>
      <data key="d2">2fd1d6134ec72f26d7a900391b7261fd</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2143</data>
      <data key="d6">bc7a5f82a2f64862bcc7d0e48c2f8095</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BUDGET PREPARATION FOR GLASSWARE PRODUCTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"BRT Co makes a range of glassware ornaments and has prepared a marketing plan for 20X1 based on the expected sales and direct manufacturing costs of three popular products: Dog, Bunny, and Cat."</data>
      <data key="d2">2fd1d6134ec72f26d7a900391b7261fd</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2144</data>
      <data key="d6">5ca5acb614614f3ca22a2c6cb3afc64e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DIRECT COSTS OF MANUFACTURING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Direct costs of manufacturing refer to the expenses directly associated with the production of goods, including materials and labor. For BRT Co, these costs include silicates, recycled glass, and labor for blowers."</data>
      <data key="d2">2fd1d6134ec72f26d7a900391b7261fd</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2145</data>
      <data key="d6">5adf4e45982947b9b1c8e65ee7c8d60e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GEOLOGICAL TESTING&quot;">
      <data key="d0" />
      <data key="d1" />
      <data key="d2">2fd1d6134ec72f26d7a900391b7261fd</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2146</data>
      <data key="d6">2b6df31ae4664bf98ee9416637ae0508</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PLANNING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Planning in the context of participative budgeting involves setting objectives and determining the actions required to achieve them. It ensures that all levels of management are involved in the planning process, making it more accurate and comprehensive."</data>
      <data key="d2">dcff42ba3ed5843954c648603089a728</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">2147</data>
      <data key="d6">98b49956d29d4256a3ea2c5ddb36db9b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CO-ORDINATION OF ACTIVITIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Co-ordination of activities in participative budgeting requires synchronizing efforts across different departments and management levels. This ensures that everyone is aware of the overall plan and works towards common goals."</data>
      <data key="d2">dcff42ba3ed5843954c648603089a728</data>
      <data key="d7">7</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2148</data>
      <data key="d6">fa887044b8ed4d0bb262a464b6cf2848</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMMUNICATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Communication in participative budgeting involves sharing the budget plan across all levels of management. Effective communication ensures that everyone understands the plan and any changes made during the budgeting process."</data>
      <data key="d2">dcff42ba3ed5843954c648603089a728</data>
      <data key="d7">7</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2149</data>
      <data key="d6">f4dbfbe20e9b49248ab23faf7af81195</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SYSTEM OF CONTROL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A system of control in budgeting involves comparing actual results to budgeted figures and investigating any differences. This process is crucial for maintaining effective control over organizational activities."</data>
      <data key="d2">dcff42ba3ed5843954c648603089a728</data>
      <data key="d7">7</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2150</data>
      <data key="d6">f97f2773b7cc4ba0aa8999acc9e163e1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERFORMANCE EVALUATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Performance evaluation in participative budgeting involves appraising managers by comparing their actual results to the budgeted results. This method is effective if the participation is genuine and free from budgetary slack."</data>
      <data key="d2">dcff42ba3ed5843954c648603089a728</data>
      <data key="d7">7</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2151</data>
      <data key="d6">e2424afff1964e01855de24fc8d2227a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TIMANA CO&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Timana Co manufactures small-panel display screens for various consumer electronic products. The company faces challenges in a competitive industry with short product life cycles and pricing pressures. The finance director has proposed shifting from incremental budgeting to a rolling budget approach to better adapt to market changes."</data>
      <data key="d2">dcff42ba3ed5843954c648603089a728</data>
      <data key="d7">7</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2152</data>
      <data key="d6">b456a62145834261830699d80b10b134</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DIRECT MATERIAL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"DIRECT MATERIAL" refers to the raw materials and components that are directly used in the manufacturing of a product. It is considered a variable cost that increases by 3% every quarter to reflect the increase in sales volume.</data>
      <data key="d2">16965b8a36bbe6bac45c7b81a6b17c48,2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2153</data>
      <data key="d6">5526a2a9a12546fa8c01dea05284f458</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES VOLUME GROWTH ASSUMPTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The assumption that sales volume would grow at the same fixed compound rate every quarter."</data>
      <data key="d2">2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2154</data>
      <data key="d6">d5d6a709c93f465699f084c117954612</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VARIABLE COSTS ASSUMPTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The assumption that direct material and direct labour are wholly variable costs."</data>
      <data key="d2">2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2155</data>
      <data key="d6">6e391437cfcf42209148973352d70dae</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FIXED PRODUCTION OVERHEADS ASSUMPTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The assumption that fixed production overheads would increase by $10,000 from Q3 onwards due to extra maintenance."</data>
      <data key="d2">2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2156</data>
      <data key="d6">e208c4b55acf410982de77f09486a949</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ADMINISTRATION COSTS ASSUMPTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The assumption that administration costs would increase by 3% in Q3 to account for an increase in the rent for the building."</data>
      <data key="d2">2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2157</data>
      <data key="d6">6ddb5a7299db4ceba8aaf8c2a1604115</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES MANAGER'S COMMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The sales manager's comment that he had to reduce selling prices to boost demand as the market became more competitive."</data>
      <data key="d2">2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2158</data>
      <data key="d6">545c6ed9d5c943adbcbf76be7bd749fa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRODUCTION MANAGER'S COMMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The production manager's comment that the direct labour cost was higher due to an increase in the minimum wage and that there will be a one-off increase of $5,000 in Q3 for additional training required under health and safety legislation."</data>
      <data key="d2">2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2159</data>
      <data key="d6">e551ca8263b34826933c747ec089f1c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHANGE MANAGER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The new position created for a 'change manager' with an annual salary of $150,000 starting at the beginning of Q2, affecting the administration cost."</data>
      <data key="d2">2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2160</data>
      <data key="d6">59f73f2a26e543e89ab0fe094a24c00d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ROLLING BUDGET FOR THE NEXT FOUR QUARTERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EXAMPLES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The rolling budget prepared for Timana Co for the next four quarters, including detailed revenue, direct labour, direct material, contribution, fixed production overhead, administration costs, and profit projections."</data>
      <data key="d2">2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">14</data>
      <data key="d5">2161</data>
      <data key="d6">e9f351186bfc49629fbf3ead0da97dde</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FIXED PRODUCTION OVERHEAD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Fixed production overhead costs will remain at $120,000 in Q2 and increase to $130,000 in Q3 onwards."</data>
      <data key="d2">16965b8a36bbe6bac45c7b81a6b17c48</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2162</data>
      <data key="d6">4f7e74ccceb44ec9abf2faf426421349</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ROLLING BUDGET APPROACH&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A rolling budget approach involves continuously updating the budget to reflect changes in the business environment. This approach requires frequent updates and adjustments to the budget, which can be facilitated by training programs and integrated information systems."</data>
      <data key="d2">16965b8a36bbe6bac45c7b81a6b17c48</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">8</data>
      <data key="d5">2163</data>
      <data key="d6">1e1058d8a2dd4eeb9fa21bd0c2a11447</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TRAINING PROGRAMS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Training programs for sales managers and finance staff are essential to ensure the smooth implementation of the rolling budget approach. These programs will improve their knowledge and reduce resistance to change."</data>
      <data key="d2">16965b8a36bbe6bac45c7b81a6b17c48</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2164</data>
      <data key="d6">268dabcef6424a4a9cf98c38dec9e258</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERFORMANCE MEASURES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Performance measures should be adjusted to reflect the new rolling budget system. This includes setting realistic targets that reflect the current economic environment and spreading targets more evenly throughout the year to improve staff motivation."</data>
      <data key="d2">16965b8a36bbe6bac45c7b81a6b17c48</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2165</data>
      <data key="d6">84fc3438dd694c4a99b41455c4c373d7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ROLLING BUDGET IMPLEMENTATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Rolling budget implementation should involve staff consultation, cost-benefit analysis, and measures to avoid disruption to productivity or morale."</data>
      <data key="d2">16965b8a36bbe6bac45c7b81a6b17c48</data>
      <data key="d7">9</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2166</data>
      <data key="d6">1400929bb6514ce5afa055c5ca661a49</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EVALUATING DECISION PACKAGES AND ZBB TRANSITION FOR PLAINFIELD COUNTY PUBLIC AUTHORITY LIBRARY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Plainfield County Public Authority (PCPA) has transitioned from incremental budgeting to zero-based budgeting (ZBB). The library manager is considering two decision packages for computer upgrades to respond to criticism of the library being old-fashioned. The decision packages include costs for staff, IS maintenance, and website hosting, with varying impacts on library operations and costs."</data>
      <data key="d2">16965b8a36bbe6bac45c7b81a6b17c48</data>
      <data key="d7">5</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2167</data>
      <data key="d6">80ab06d7f5c642e4aec89d3e0073103f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DECISION PACKAGE 1: COMPUTER UPGRADE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EXAMPLES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This decision package involves replacing only the computers at a total cost of $45,000. Annual IS maintenance costs will fall to $9,000, while annual website costs and staff costs will remain constant. This upgrade will not substantially change library operations."</data>
      <data key="d2">16965b8a36bbe6bac45c7b81a6b17c48</data>
      <data key="d7">5</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2168</data>
      <data key="d6">c503a46509674e43ba57bac181678f02</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DECISION PACKAGE 2: COMPUTER UPGRADE AND INTEGRATED LIBRARY SYSTEM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EXAMPLES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This decision package involves purchasing new computers plus additional hardware and software to automate core library processes at a total cost of $98,500. It will allow self-service borrowing of books, reduce staff members to four, increase annual IS maintenance costs to $22,000, and increase annual website costs to $3,000."</data>
      <data key="d2">16965b8a36bbe6bac45c7b81a6b17c48</data>
      <data key="d7">5</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2169</data>
      <data key="d6">53104fc724c1487289ecf0385ac85a13</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DECISION PACKAGE 2&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Decision package 2 involves a computer upgrade including an integrated library system costing $98,500, annual IS maintenance costs of $22,000, website hosting costs of $3,000, and staff costs of $112,000, totaling $235,500 for the first year."</data>
      <data key="d2">ed1f837be30c9135b0fe794ec0162540</data>
      <data key="d7">5</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2170</data>
      <data key="d6">6020a478a6ff4974949c8564d03064f6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ADVANTAGES OF ZBB&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Advantages of ZBB include a focus on the objectives and needs of the community, evaluation of decision packages by value for money, involvement of the library manager in the budgeting process, and identification of operational efficiencies and quality improvements."</data>
      <data key="d2">ed1f837be30c9135b0fe794ec0162540</data>
      <data key="d7">5</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2171</data>
      <data key="d6">5d3c5d881f5b447ca366d9521817c549</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DISADVANTAGES OF ZBB&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Disadvantages of ZBB include being time-consuming for the library manager, potential distraction from other important responsibilities, and a focus on short-term objectives over long-term benefits."</data>
      <data key="d2">ed1f837be30c9135b0fe794ec0162540</data>
      <data key="d7">5</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2172</data>
      <data key="d6">589b878718774941a822c71bc6b38322</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CAPACITY ANALYSIS AND PRODUCTION EFFICIENCY FOR TOY CO&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Toy Co is a small company manufacturing toys for toddlers and children, facing increasing overhead costs and loss of key customers due to shipping errors and missed delivery dates. The management accountant is considering introducing activity-based budgeting to improve efficiency and reduce costs."</data>
      <data key="d2">ed1f837be30c9135b0fe794ec0162540</data>
      <data key="d7">7</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2173</data>
      <data key="d6">375f6c6c66e6420d8fa73057f548fe5f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;QUALITY INSPECTION TIME&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"QUALITY INSPECTION TIME" refers to the time required to inspect the quality of products. For Toy Co, this time is specifically 15 hours per batch. Additionally, quality inspection time encompasses the total hours required to inspect batches within a quarter, which can serve as an indicator of whether the department is operating below or above capacity.</data>
      <data key="d2">02defdad562458f44c0d0fa31dc9693d,ed1f837be30c9135b0fe794ec0162540</data>
      <data key="d7">7</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2174</data>
      <data key="d6">c3fd60bc83d54bf5985afa36d8985599</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PACKAGING AND SHIPPING TIME&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"PACKAGING AND SHIPPING TIME" refers to the time required to package and ship products. For Toy Co, this time is specifically 1 hour per order. Additionally, "PACKAGING AND SHIPPING TIME" can also denote the total hours required to complete the shipment of orders within a quarter. This metric can be used to determine whether there is a shortage or surplus of available hours for packaging and shipping activities.</data>
      <data key="d2">02defdad562458f44c0d0fa31dc9693d,ed1f837be30c9135b0fe794ec0162540</data>
      <data key="d7">7</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2175</data>
      <data key="d6">122cd82bdec9402881ddbbf7a02fc153</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SPARE CAPACITY/SHORTAGE CALCULATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The calculation of spare capacity or shortage involves comparing the required hours for quality inspection and packaging/shipping against the available hours to identify any excess capacity or shortfall."</data>
      <data key="d2">02defdad562458f44c0d0fa31dc9693d</data>
      <data key="d7">7</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2176</data>
      <data key="d6">7e49a0e74d9d45be9a19fbe5ee64ed3d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ESTIMATION OF FIXED AND VARIABLE ELECTRICITY COSTS USING THE HIGH-LOW METHOD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Tomkins Co uses the High-Low Method to estimate the fixed and variable components of electricity costs based on direct labour hours, helping to prepare a flexible budget for the upcoming year."</data>
      <data key="d2">02defdad562458f44c0d0fa31dc9693d</data>
      <data key="d7">8</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2177</data>
      <data key="d6">e5657c3b1ee447a1a3f6bf002f10e402</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ESTIMATING THE LEARNING RATE AND IDENTIFYING STEADY STATE IN PRODUCTION EFFICIENCY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Alex Co uses the Learning Curve to estimate the learning rate and identify when the steady state of production efficiency is reached for a new product, the electroscope."</data>
      <data key="d2">02defdad562458f44c0d0fa31dc9693d</data>
      <data key="d7">8</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2178</data>
      <data key="d6">1e9c2e0e5b6b4a8dbc9ffe8b26e1e306</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CALCULATION OF BATCHES AND ORDERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0" />
      <data key="d1" />
      <data key="d2">02defdad562458f44c0d0fa31dc9693d</data>
      <data key="d7">7</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2179</data>
      <data key="d6">0858bba029214683a3487db3dddee9fb</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STEADY STATE ESTIMATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The steady state estimation identifies the point at which no further improvement in time is taken, meaning the incremental time per unit no longer falls. In this case, the steady state is reached at the beginning of March, as the incremental time of all units in March is 20 and does not fall further in April."</data>
      <data key="d2">b187f3c28f227717529f989789010620</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">2180</data>
      <data key="d6">5ddee66450224667a34f47f754a2f874</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FORECASTING SALES USING REGRESSION ANALYSIS AND EVALUATING SEASONAL TRENDS FOR FRUITEE CO&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Fruitee Co's management accountant is using regression analysis to predict sales of a product introduced three years ago. The sales revenue trend and seasonal indices are calculated to forecast future sales, and the chief executive considers investing in big data analytics for more accurate predictions."</data>
      <data key="d2">b187f3c28f227717529f989789010620</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2181</data>
      <data key="d6">55134d0df6ba425daacef29efef4692a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REGRESSION ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Regression analysis is a statistical method used to predict future values based on the relationship between variables. In this case, it is used to forecast sales trends for Fruitee Co by calculating the trend equation from given data."</data>
      <data key="d2">b187f3c28f227717529f989789010620</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2182</data>
      <data key="d6">ec2e62002ac949a8866c1b104b169dfa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MULTIPLICATIVE SEASONAL INDEX&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The multiplicative seasonal index is used to adjust the forecasted trend values to account for seasonal variations. It is calculated by dividing the actual sales by the trend value for each season."</data>
      <data key="d2">b187f3c28f227717529f989789010620</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2183</data>
      <data key="d6">08a856a5a3c148e5810d80f2090e4a46</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BIG DATA ANALYTICS INVESTMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Big data analytics involves using advanced data processing techniques to analyze large and complex data sets. Fruitee Co's chief executive believes that investing in big data analytics could provide more accurate insights into future sales performance."</data>
      <data key="d2">b187f3c28f227717529f989789010620</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2184</data>
      <data key="d6">fbe019ff4fd8491ca21f18d234c90ff2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FORECAST SALES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Forecast sales for Summer Year 6 ($m) = 138.5 (per trend equation) * 1.35 = 187."</data>
      <data key="d2">bb165972f0b8b6fbf29cb666c55127ec</data>
      <data key="d7">8</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2185</data>
      <data key="d6">c81ee4e2edee4d34bc59a5dd1bc8c406</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;POTENTIAL PROBLEMS IN DATA ANALYTICS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Potential problems in data analytics include issues related to value, volume, variety, velocity, veracity, structure, and reliability of data. These factors can affect the effectiveness and accuracy of data analytics."</data>
      <data key="d2">bb165972f0b8b6fbf29cb666c55127ec</data>
      <data key="d4">7</data>
      <data key="d5">2186</data>
      <data key="d6">b299a3b4ac17431eb997125c71e24464</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VALUE IN DATA ANALYTICS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Value refers to the benefits that Fruitee Co expects to gain from investing in data analytics. These benefits may be uncertain and difficult to measure."</data>
      <data key="d2">bb165972f0b8b6fbf29cb666c55127ec</data>
      <data key="d4">7</data>
      <data key="d5">2187</data>
      <data key="d6">2b304b844d5142ea89ff90643987d1f8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VOLUME IN DATA ANALYTICS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Volume refers to the large amount of data that Fruitee Co could potentially analyze, including data about competitors, economic and social trends, retail sector developments, and customer feedback."</data>
      <data key="d2">bb165972f0b8b6fbf29cb666c55127ec</data>
      <data key="d4">7</data>
      <data key="d5">2188</data>
      <data key="d6">7b9e8b2aecbd4fc6a5063b7be9718a35</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VARIETY IN DATA ANALYTICS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Variety refers to the different categories and types of data collected through Fruitee's systems. The data analytics capabilities need to classify and differentiate this variety to produce usable insights."</data>
      <data key="d2">bb165972f0b8b6fbf29cb666c55127ec</data>
      <data key="d4">7</data>
      <data key="d5">2189</data>
      <data key="d6">667932fdd1504b1199bb0211b09b3346</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VELOCITY IN DATA ANALYTICS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Velocity refers to the speed at which new data is produced and collected. Fruitee Co's data analytics capabilities must deliver useful insights in a timely manner to support decision-making."</data>
      <data key="d2">bb165972f0b8b6fbf29cb666c55127ec</data>
      <data key="d4">7</data>
      <data key="d5">2190</data>
      <data key="d6">b89c4b4692c3488faa4aff95c5117eae</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VERACITY IN DATA ANALYTICS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Veracity refers to the reliability and accuracy of the underlying data. Fruitee Co needs to ensure that its data collection methods capture accurate and timely data."</data>
      <data key="d2">bb165972f0b8b6fbf29cb666c55127ec</data>
      <data key="d4">7</data>
      <data key="d5">2191</data>
      <data key="d6">c9e04a359f124d11802836336f687b62</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STRUCTURE IN DATA ANALYTICS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Structure refers to the organization of data. Much big data is unstructured, requiring more complex and time-consuming techniques to analyze effectively."</data>
      <data key="d2">bb165972f0b8b6fbf29cb666c55127ec</data>
      <data key="d4">7</data>
      <data key="d5">2192</data>
      <data key="d6">9b43795310c94d31bbff41a171ef32bd</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RELIABILITY IN DATA ANALYTICS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Reliability refers to the degree of trustworthiness of data. Different data sources have varying degrees of reliability, and understanding why certain data differs significantly can provide valuable insights."</data>
      <data key="d2">bb165972f0b8b6fbf29cb666c55127ec</data>
      <data key="d4">7</data>
      <data key="d5">2193</data>
      <data key="d6">5478ef370edc47fe8b94201c57a8fb44</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRIORITISATION IN DATA ANALYTICS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Prioritisation in data analytics involves determining which insights are the most significant and relevant for decision-making. Different types of data may provide contradictory indications, and it is crucial to identify which data best indicates short-term and long-term trends."</data>
      <data key="d2">a90ec32176608282b11bed138f7007da</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">2194</data>
      <data key="d6">907e50767e9d4ce0a7a0abb00e7a2003</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CLARITY IN DATA ANALYTICS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Clarity in data analytics refers to the ability to interpret and understand the data clearly. Qualitative insights may be difficult to translate into quantitative effects, and there is a risk of relying on data that provides a clear picture rather than the most significant data."</data>
      <data key="d2">a90ec32176608282b11bed138f7007da</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2195</data>
      <data key="d6">864460904f4b45708aa09499f8460075</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FLEXED BUDGET PREPARATION FOR COWLY RESTAURANT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Yumi Co's Cowly restaurant's budget preparation involves comparing actual performance against budgeted figures. The flexed budget adjusts the original budget based on the actual number of customers, providing a more accurate comparison of revenue and costs."</data>
      <data key="d2">a90ec32176608282b11bed138f7007da</data>
      <data key="d7">19</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2196</data>
      <data key="d6">35a7de4a5e714458acf0308a4a9255d6</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DETAILED VARIANCE ANALYSIS FOR PORTLAND CO'S PRODUCT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Portland Co manufactures a product from a standard grade of material. The case involves calculating various variances such as sales volume variance, sales price variance, materials price variance, materials usage variance, labour rate variance, labour efficiency variance, variable overhead rate variance, variable overhead efficiency variance, and fixed overhead expenditure variance based on the actual and budgeted production and sales data."</data>
      <data key="d2">4ae58f51790b98226f6ec0a6232803a9</data>
      <data key="d7">20</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">8</data>
      <data key="d5">2197</data>
      <data key="d6">531ab152cfad4ba19ab99763da822c4d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VARIANCE ANALYSIS AND FLEXIBLE BUDGETING FOR MERMUS CO&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Mermus Co is comparing budget and actual data for the last three months. The company uses standard costing and absorbs fixed production overheads on a machine hour basis. The case involves preparing a revised budget using a flexible budgeting approach and calculating various variances including raw material total cost variance, direct labour total cost variance, fixed overhead efficiency variance, fixed overhead capacity variance, and fixed overhead expenditure variance."</data>
      <data key="d2">3e31b0e19c2c3d14cdeebdb3d493eb6b</data>
      <data key="d7">20</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">5</data>
      <data key="d5">2198</data>
      <data key="d6">754bb667fd96498d9f34a88d118d18b1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OVERHEAD EFFICIENCY VARIANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0" />
      <data key="d1" />
      <data key="d2">3e31b0e19c2c3d14cdeebdb3d493eb6b</data>
      <data key="d7">20</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2199</data>
      <data key="d6">c9408d57eb4c4a0e8ed561cab4a60a09</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;RAW MATERIALS COST VARIANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The budgeted raw material cost for production of 95,000 units was $1.40 per unit (133,000/95,000) but the actual raw material cost for production of 90,000 units was $1.45 per unit (130,500/90,000). The raw material cost per unit may have increased either because more raw materials per unit were used than budgeted, or because the price per unit of raw material was higher than budgeted."</data>
      <data key="d2">5725a64a66ba9d34bcfa7d683ea0f78e</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">2200</data>
      <data key="d6">d3e710c7843d4af5b9547408d2effc8e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FIXED OVERHEAD EFFICIENCY VARIANCE EXPLANATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The fixed overhead efficiency variance measures the extent to which more or less standard hours were used for the actual production than budgeted. In this case, a total of 27,200 machine hours were actually used, when only 27,000 standard machine hours should have been used. The difference may be due to poorer production planning than expected or to machine breakdowns."</data>
      <data key="d2">5725a64a66ba9d34bcfa7d683ea0f78e</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">2201</data>
      <data key="d6">64036c29c6944c939dd1b66ef3f4f168</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FIXED OVERHEAD EXPENDITURE VARIANCE EXPLANATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The fixed overhead expenditure variance measures the extent to which budgeted fixed overhead differs from actual fixed overhead. Here, actual fixed overhead is $10,100 less than budgeted. This could be due to an error in forecasting fixed production overheads such as rent and power costs, or to a decrease in fixed production overheads, such as changing to a cheaper cleaning contractor."</data>
      <data key="d2">5725a64a66ba9d34bcfa7d683ea0f78e</data>
      <data key="d7">20</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2202</data>
      <data key="d6">d258f3e7df564f7daf8140754b684bed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PURPOSES OF A BUDGETING SYSTEM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Key purposes of a budgeting system include planning, co-ordination, communication, control, motivation, and performance evaluation."</data>
      <data key="d2">5725a64a66ba9d34bcfa7d683ea0f78e</data>
      <data key="d4">6</data>
      <data key="d5">2203</data>
      <data key="d6">ab54b207f3dc46028ac1b7aaffd58cbe</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PLANNING IN BUDGETING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"One of the key purposes of a budgeting system is to require planning to occur. Strategic planning covers several years but a budget represents a financial plan covering a shorter period (i.e. a budget is an operational plan). Planning helps an organisation to anticipate key changes in the business environment that could potentially impact on business activities and to prepare appropriate responses. Planning also ensures that the budgeted activities of the organisation will support the achievement of the organisation's objectives."</data>
      <data key="d2">5725a64a66ba9d34bcfa7d683ea0f78e</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2204</data>
      <data key="d6">c02c448b25eb4da3ad0611e6e4d3443b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CO-ORDINATION IN BUDGETING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Many organisations undertake a number of activities, which need to be co-ordinated, if the organisation is to meet its objectives. The budgeting system facilitates this co-ordination since organisational activities and the links between them are thoroughly investigated during budget preparation, and the overall coherence between the budgeted activities is reviewed before senior managers agree the master budget. Without the framework of the budgeting system, individual managers may be tempted to make decisions that are not optimal in terms of achieving organisational objectives."</data>
      <data key="d2">5725a64a66ba9d34bcfa7d683ea0f78e</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2205</data>
      <data key="d6">191ccf4de4b64a648060e0d818bab2d7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMMUNICATION IN BUDGETING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The budgeting system facilitates communication both vertically (e.g. between senior and junior managers) and horizontally (e.g. between different organisational functions). Vertical communication enables senior managers to ensure that employees at all levels understand organisational objectives. Communication also occurs at all stages of the budgetary control process (e.g. during budget preparation and investigation of period-end variances)."</data>
      <data key="d2">5725a64a66ba9d34bcfa7d683ea0f78e</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2206</data>
      <data key="d6">f85a6929d469410d977a860114f8f350</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONTROL IN BUDGETING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"One of the most important purposes of a budgeting system is to facilitate cost control through the comparison of budgeted costs and actual costs. Variances between budgeted and actual costs can be investigated in order to determine the reason why actual performance has differed from what was planned. Corrective action can be introduced if necessary in order to ensure that organisational objectives are achieved. A budgeting system also facilitates management by exception, whereby only significant differences between planned and actual activity are investigated."</data>
      <data key="d2">5725a64a66ba9d34bcfa7d683ea0f78e</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2207</data>
      <data key="d6">5f5fc93091cb4ae8aee15ea1e9fb057c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MOTIVATION IN BUDGETING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The budgeting system can influence the behaviour of managers and employees, and may motivate them to improve their performance if the target represented by the budget is set at an appropriate level. An inappropriate target has the potential to be de-motivating, however, and a key factor here is the degree of participation in the budget-setting process. It has been shown that an appropriate degree of participation can have a positive motivational effect."</data>
      <data key="d2">5725a64a66ba9d34bcfa7d683ea0f78e</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2208</data>
      <data key="d6">c2268855239b4840a18517e227d34182</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERFORMANCE EVALUATION IN BUDGETING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Managerial performance is often evaluated by the extent to which budgetary targets for which individual managers are responsible have been achieved. Managerial rewards such as bonuses or performance-related pay can also be linked to achievement of budgetary targets. Managers can also use the budget to evaluate their own performance and clarify how close they are to meeting agreed performance targets."</data>
      <data key="d2">5725a64a66ba9d34bcfa7d683ea0f78e</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2209</data>
      <data key="d6">978eeab6320547ed884c9f3973a1afb3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES VOLUME AND VARIANCE ANALYSIS FOR MILBAO CO&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Milbao Co makes and sells three types of electronic game for which the following budget/standard information and actual information is available for a four-week period: Model: Superb, Excellent, Good; Budget sales (units): 30,000, 50,000, 20,000; Standard unit data Selling price ($): 100, 80, 70; Variable cost ($): 40, 25, 22; Actual sales (units): 36,000, 42,000, 18,000; Budgeted fixed costs are $2,500,000 for the four-week period."</data>
      <data key="d2">5725a64a66ba9d34bcfa7d683ea0f78e</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">2210</data>
      <data key="d6">28f97775f75a464eb646cc8c3b4e82ce</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONTRIBUTION BASIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Contribution basis for sales volume variance is calculated as the difference between actual and budgeted sales units multiplied by the contribution per unit."</data>
      <data key="d2">31513de544b09bc77695e746ff044232</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">2211</data>
      <data key="d6">061d11ce6c2445e682bc2192d94b8cc7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NET PROFIT BASIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Net profit basis for sales volume variance is calculated as the difference between actual and budgeted sales units multiplied by the profit per unit."</data>
      <data key="d2">31513de544b09bc77695e746ff044232</data>
      <data key="d7">28</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2212</data>
      <data key="d6">729aeeb24e3045cb89cd0417e9beb488</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MATERIAL AND LABOUR VARIANCE ANALYSIS FOR PAN-OCEAN CHEMICALS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Pan-Ocean Chemicals produces Synthon using three types of materials and labor. The case involves calculating material mix, yield, and usage variances, as well as labor rate and efficiency variances, based on standard and actual costs and quantities."</data>
      <data key="d2">31513de544b09bc77695e746ff044232</data>
      <data key="d7">28</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">5</data>
      <data key="d5">2213</data>
      <data key="d6">761eaa9ab9f2447e8e95414b16e0846c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;REVISED STANDARD COST OF ACTUAL OUTPUT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Revised standard cost of actual output (122,000 units * 1.4 hours * $13 per hour) = $2,220,400"</data>
      <data key="d2">be8ddb66c7e66aaac8c9da8e08378f00</data>
      <data key="d7">28</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2214</data>
      <data key="d6">c1f1928f39bc4bca8e61d9ebd1f13d6d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OPERATING VARIANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Operating variance is the difference between the revised standard cost and the actual cost. In this case, it is $222,040 (F)."</data>
      <data key="d2">be8ddb66c7e66aaac8c9da8e08378f00</data>
      <data key="d7">28</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2215</data>
      <data key="d6">e4fba3413cd24e26ab3a92c8ae85b715</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ACTUAL LABOUR COST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Actual labour cost = $1,998,360"</data>
      <data key="d2">be8ddb66c7e66aaac8c9da8e08378f00</data>
      <data key="d7">28</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2216</data>
      <data key="d6">baa3005fbabc4953b3a4b26da65c716d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LABOUR USAGE PLANNING VARIANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Labour usage planning variance is calculated as the difference between the actual output at original standard time per unit and the actual output at revised standard time per unit, both multiplied by the original standard rate. In this case, it is $219,600 (A)."</data>
      <data key="d2">be8ddb66c7e66aaac8c9da8e08378f00</data>
      <data key="d7">28</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2217</data>
      <data key="d6">5a83a09204484283aea3984db73f441a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LABOUR PRICE PLANNING VARIANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Labour price planning variance is calculated as the difference between the actual output at revised standard time per unit at original standard rate and the actual output at revised standard time per unit at revised standard rate. In this case, it is $170,800 (A)."</data>
      <data key="d2">be8ddb66c7e66aaac8c9da8e08378f00</data>
      <data key="d7">28</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2218</data>
      <data key="d6">003146533c744096934b16018c4c0dfa</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRINCIPLES OF REVISING STANDARDS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Principles of revising standards involve ensuring that managers are judged only on factors they can control. Standards should be revised for uncontrollable factors before variance analysis is performed to reflect accurate performance. Revisions should be authorized by a senior, independent body to ensure fairness."</data>
      <data key="d2">be8ddb66c7e66aaac8c9da8e08378f00</data>
      <data key="d7">28</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2219</data>
      <data key="d6">9a825ed6ec6e4752a0df464bbc38b57a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FACTORS FOR VARIANCE INVESTIGATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Factors to consider in deciding whether a variance should be investigated include the size of the variance, whether it is adverse or favorable, cost versus benefits of investigation, historic pattern of variances, and the reliability and quality of data."</data>
      <data key="d2">be8ddb66c7e66aaac8c9da8e08378f00</data>
      <data key="d7">28</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2220</data>
      <data key="d6">aded800f81924575997f276be3061cd3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BUDGET REVISIONS AND SALES VARIANCE ANALYSIS FOR SPIKE CO&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Spike Co manufactures and sells good quality leather bound diaries. The company budgets for its profits, including detailed budgets for sales, materials, and labour. The managing director is concerned about the frequency of budget revisions, which seem to result in favourable operational variance reports but less profit than promised. The case discusses circumstances for allowing or refusing budget revisions, specific situations for materials and labour budget revisions, and sales performance analysis."</data>
      <data key="d2">398230bc0b5f27c6546a25d2a2e97611</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">2221</data>
      <data key="d6">56ffa8aa3d83429fb03a8025a9df25ff</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES VARIANCE ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sales variance analysis involves calculating the total sales price and total sales volume variance, as well as market size and market share variances, to assess the sales performance of a business."</data>
      <data key="d2">398230bc0b5f27c6546a25d2a2e97611</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2222</data>
      <data key="d6">e0f229e9c72d40e48d8f173243552d60</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MATERIALS BUDGET REVISION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EXAMPLES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A local material supplier was forced into liquidation, and a new supplier 150 miles away charged more for the material and delivery. A budget revision is sought for the two months where higher prices had to be paid."</data>
      <data key="d2">398230bc0b5f27c6546a25d2a2e97611</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2223</data>
      <data key="d6">b5edcc2f52e54190b3234b8e68f5b138</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LABOUR BUDGET REVISION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EXAMPLES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Due to quality issues with support staff, the company decided to recruit only top graduates, increasing costs but improving productivity. A budget revision is requested to cover the extra costs following the change of policy."</data>
      <data key="d2">398230bc0b5f27c6546a25d2a2e97611</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2224</data>
      <data key="d6">7597b1ab04684ddf80b48826137071e8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES PERFORMANCE ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The market for leather bound diaries has been shrinking as electronic versions become more widely available. Spike Co's sales performance is analyzed by calculating total sales price and volume variances, market size and share variances, and commenting on the sales performance."</data>
      <data key="d2">398230bc0b5f27c6546a25d2a2e97611</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2225</data>
      <data key="d6">8c2b34aff6454eb0942c8ff8128de289</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LABOUR ARGUMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The argument in favor of allowing a budget revision for labor costs is based on the fact that the decision to increase staff levels was made by the board, not the departmental manager. This suggests that the extra cost is outside the manager's control."</data>
      <data key="d2">002794ec024434f7ac2bd26217b3897d</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2226</data>
      <data key="d6">915de8b01b8a4305983f7b776c3bbf50</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES PERFORMANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sales performance analysis involves evaluating the effectiveness of sales strategies and decisions, such as pricing and market positioning, in achieving sales targets."</data>
      <data key="d2">002794ec024434f7ac2bd26217b3897d</data>
      <data key="d7">28</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">2227</data>
      <data key="d6">52cf0eb857dc446ab9124b113294cc0b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES PRICE AND QUANTITY VARIANCES ANALYSIS FOR BLOCK CO&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Block Co uses an absorption costing system and sells three types of products. The company faces challenges in maintaining revenues and profits due to economic recession. Sales prices fluctuate, and a market specialist sets budgeted sales prices each quarter. The sales manager negotiates actual sales prices with customers."</data>
      <data key="d2">002794ec024434f7ac2bd26217b3897d</data>
      <data key="d7">0</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">5</data>
      <data key="d5">2228</data>
      <data key="d6">9daf5f7076b44b5eb788233216d8fba4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STANDARD SELLING PRICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Standard selling price is the budgeted price set for a product at the beginning of a period, based on market expectations."</data>
      <data key="d2">002794ec024434f7ac2bd26217b3897d</data>
      <data key="d7">0</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2229</data>
      <data key="d6">d7e61f7a007b4313b2286f77272a5a4c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;VARIABLE PRODUCTION COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Variable production costs are costs that vary directly with the level of production, such as materials and labor."</data>
      <data key="d2">002794ec024434f7ac2bd26217b3897d</data>
      <data key="d7">0</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2230</data>
      <data key="d6">a5e1a0acc6374a94ae7a8f984e90ac1a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMMODITY 2&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Commodity 2 refers to a specific product with actual production and sales units of 30,400, an actual selling price per unit of $34, and an average market price per unit of $33.15."</data>
      <data key="d2">5374b54ad664c71f5b07af0884d0b0c6</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">2231</data>
      <data key="d6">4e98f988900340d592ecd2b3afdd2759</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMMODITY 3&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Commodity 3 refers to a specific product with actual production and sales units of 25,600, an actual selling price per unit of $40.40, and an average market price per unit of $39.10."</data>
      <data key="d2">5374b54ad664c71f5b07af0884d0b0c6</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">2232</data>
      <data key="d6">08dfc9069bb5451594f90b9f389d77c2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES PRICE OPERATIONAL VARIANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sales price operational variance is calculated as (actual price - market price) * actual quantity."</data>
      <data key="d2">5374b54ad664c71f5b07af0884d0b0c6</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2233</data>
      <data key="d6">6d95977fc850437ba5b24b335a5bc82e</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES PRICE PLANNING VARIANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sales price planning variance is calculated as (standard price - market price) * actual quantity."</data>
      <data key="d2">5374b54ad664c71f5b07af0884d0b0c6</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">2234</data>
      <data key="d6">6326cd8e79e54ad19e8f49ff2d1a10a9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TOTAL SALES MIX VARIANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Total sales mix variance is calculated by comparing the actual quantity in the actual mix to the actual quantity in the standard mix, multiplied by the standard profit."</data>
      <data key="d2">5374b54ad664c71f5b07af0884d0b0c6</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">2235</data>
      <data key="d6">cb4272e686c2474fa67ae50bdc6139be</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TOTAL SALES QUANTITY VARIANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Total sales quantity variance is calculated by comparing the actual quantity in the standard mix to the budgeted sales, multiplied by the standard profit."</data>
      <data key="d2">5374b54ad664c71f5b07af0884d0b0c6</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">2236</data>
      <data key="d6">9286b053237d494985a388b289467622</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERFORMANCE OF THE BUSINESS AND SALES MANAGER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The performance of the business and the sales manager for the quarter ended 31 May can be evaluated by analyzing the calculated variances for sales price operational, sales price planning, total sales mix, and total sales quantity."</data>
      <data key="d2">5374b54ad664c71f5b07af0884d0b0c6</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">2237</data>
      <data key="d6">cecc48281e184daabe0a7d004f05a880</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COMMODITY 1&quot;">
      <data key="d0" />
      <data key="d1" />
      <data key="d2">5374b54ad664c71f5b07af0884d0b0c6</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2238</data>
      <data key="d6">c7eca784bcc24a9589b8b3e42f402d78</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;QUANTITY VARIANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Quantity variance = (Actual quantity - Budgeted quantity) x Standard contribution per unit"</data>
      <data key="d2">9c725f949895b6929ff9aaf34a59aa27</data>
      <data key="d7">28</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2239</data>
      <data key="d6">c370f74c97f347fbb6cdd6ec3d076a36</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FINANCIAL AND NON-FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE ANALYSIS OF TIES ONLY CO&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Ties Only Co is a new business selling high-quality imported men's ties via the Internet. The company experienced losses in its first two quarters due to high initial expenses, including website development and marketing. Despite the losses, the company saw growth in sales and website hits, indicating potential for future success. Non-financial performance indicators such as on-time delivery, sales returns, and system downtime were also tracked to assess overall performance."</data>
      <data key="d2">9c725f949895b6929ff9aaf34a59aa27</data>
      <data key="d4">5</data>
      <data key="d5">2240</data>
      <data key="d6">20ed69afae8a433a9a07de6001e147cf</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WEBSITE HITS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"WEBSITE HITS" are automatically counted each time a visitor opens the home page of Ties Only Co. This metric serves as a measure of the website's traffic and potential customer interest. Additionally, the industry average conversion rate for website hits to the number of ties sold is 3.2%.</data>
      <data key="d2">19092af48cfe51bac1503c304f3ca707,9c725f949895b6929ff9aaf34a59aa27</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2241</data>
      <data key="d6">f784407cd38047e9bc9978c2c2bb1c7c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NUMBER OF TIES SOLD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">The "NUMBER OF TIES SOLD" is a measure of the company's sales volume and market demand for its products. The conversion rates for this metric are 4% for quarter 1 and 4.5% for quarter 2, both of which are ahead of the industry average data.</data>
      <data key="d2">19092af48cfe51bac1503c304f3ca707,9c725f949895b6929ff9aaf34a59aa27</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">2242</data>
      <data key="d6">fa3ca0e2dafa4c77b498d7e880ebbd14</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ON-TIME DELIVERY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"On-time delivery is a measure of the company's efficiency in fulfilling customer orders within the promised time frame."</data>
      <data key="d2">9c725f949895b6929ff9aaf34a59aa27</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2243</data>
      <data key="d6">33e854cae1404823acb6e5c08558a8e5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SALES RETURNS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"SALES RETURNS" refer to the percentage of products returned by customers, which can indicate customer satisfaction and product quality. For the first quarter, the sales returns rate is 12%, while it has increased to 18% in the second quarter. This increase in the return rate for quarter 2 may suggest issues with product quality, delivery accuracy, or customer satisfaction. Comparatively, the industry average sales return rate for internet-based clothing sales is 13%.</data>
      <data key="d2">19092af48cfe51bac1503c304f3ca707,963bb5be84f30224d6e25ea423602dfd,9c725f949895b6929ff9aaf34a59aa27</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">2244</data>
      <data key="d6">0c961f00e94045e9a41387b039c26eea</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SYSTEM DOWNTIME&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"SYSTEM DOWNTIME" refers to the percentage of time the company's website or systems are not operational, which affects customer experience and sales. For the first quarter, the system downtime rate is 2%, while for the second quarter, it increases to 4%.</data>
      <data key="d2">19092af48cfe51bac1503c304f3ca707,9c725f949895b6929ff9aaf34a59aa27</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2245</data>
      <data key="d6">f502e04474604bafaded5b1a94407a51</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ON TIME DELIVERY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"ON TIME DELIVERY" refers to the ability of the business to deliver products to customers within the promised timeframe, which is crucial for customer satisfaction and repeat business. The on-time delivery rates for the business are 95% for quarter 1 and 89% for quarter 2.</data>
      <data key="d2">19092af48cfe51bac1503c304f3ca707,963bb5be84f30224d6e25ea423602dfd</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2246</data>
      <data key="d6">82d524aa4850458c883facfda0964c62</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE OF TIES ONLY CO&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Ties Only Co has shown impressive sales growth from $420,000 to $680,000 in the first two quarters. However, gross profit has reduced by 2% in one quarter, which is a concern. Website development and launch marketing costs are high but are expected to decrease in the future. Administration and distribution costs are under control. The business has lost over $188,000 in the first two quarters, but this is not as disastrous as it looks due to the high initial costs and the potential for future profitability."</data>
      <data key="d2">19092af48cfe51bac1503c304f3ca707</data>
      <data key="d4">5</data>
      <data key="d5">2247</data>
      <data key="d6">2ca1b5d0dbc7499e8f672995b48715c0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CONVERSION RATES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The percentage of website visitors who make a purchase, indicating the effectiveness of the website in converting traffic into sales. For quarter 1, the conversion rate is 4%, and for quarter 2, it is 4.5%."</data>
      <data key="d2">963bb5be84f30224d6e25ea423602dfd</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">2248</data>
      <data key="d6">6b60c5388ac8430893087da616f1ed16</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AVERAGE PRICE PER TIE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The average price achieved for the ties sold, calculated as total sales revenue divided by the number of ties sold. For quarter 1, it is $15.20 per tie, and for quarter 2, it is $17.50 per tie."</data>
      <data key="d2">963bb5be84f30224d6e25ea423602dfd</data>
      <data key="d7">10</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2249</data>
      <data key="d6">5ad9d05def54435999bba33d2cc84567</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SYSTEM DOWN TIME&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The period during which the website is not operational, preventing customers from accessing the site and making purchases. Increased downtime can lead to lost sales and customer dissatisfaction."</data>
      <data key="d2">963bb5be84f30224d6e25ea423602dfd</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2250</data>
      <data key="d6">01ef648948a64475bc9dcc054a719140</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WEBSITE HITS GROWTH&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The increase in the number of visitors to the website, indicating the growth in online traffic. Between quarter 1 and quarter 2, the growth is 25%."</data>
      <data key="d2">963bb5be84f30224d6e25ea423602dfd</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2251</data>
      <data key="d6">0114932e2a8a4863892e866e30208e61</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERFORMANCE INDICATORS IN PUBLIC FIRE SERVICES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Measures used to evaluate the performance of publicly funded and operated fire-fighting and rescue services, including annual cost, cost per emergency call-out, average response time, and fire deaths per thousand head of population."</data>
      <data key="d2">963bb5be84f30224d6e25ea423602dfd</data>
      <data key="d7">4</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2252</data>
      <data key="d6">f807fc1d4e9e4bd79134ad2be19e25de</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ANNUAL COST OF THE SERVICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The total yearly expenditure of the fire-fighting and rescue service, used as a performance indicator to evaluate economy."</data>
      <data key="d2">963bb5be84f30224d6e25ea423602dfd</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2253</data>
      <data key="d6">b33b3df2c5944293ade89ea5fd0ae768</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COST PER EMERGENCY CALL-OUT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The average cost incurred for each emergency response, used as a performance indicator to evaluate efficiency."</data>
      <data key="d2">963bb5be84f30224d6e25ea423602dfd</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2254</data>
      <data key="d6">c936c48e2080429780189361d5ab2ae5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;AVERAGE RESPONSE TIME TO ARRIVE AT INCIDENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"AVERAGE RESPONSE TIME TO ARRIVE AT INCIDENT" is a measure of effectiveness, as responding to calls for help is the output of the organization. It represents the average time taken for the fire service to reach an incident after receiving a call and is used as a performance indicator to evaluate effectiveness. Response times can be improved with more resources.</data>
      <data key="d2">963bb5be84f30224d6e25ea423602dfd,cb50fc35976065bda7ad3244d6e4a9e0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2255</data>
      <data key="d6">a0e202e96056457e8523e20bac888694</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FIRE DEATHS PER THOUSAND HEAD OF POPULATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Fire deaths per thousand head of population" is a measure of effectiveness, as reducing casualties is a key policy objective. This metric represents the number of fire-related deaths per thousand people in the population and is used as a performance indicator to evaluate the effectiveness of fire prevention and response efforts. Managers can influence this ratio through various measures, both critical and preventative, to achieve the goal of minimizing fire-related casualties.</data>
      <data key="d2">963bb5be84f30224d6e25ea423602dfd,cb50fc35976065bda7ad3244d6e4a9e0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2256</data>
      <data key="d6">fbcf0c7dbca44724b9cbdd54dcb2b143</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EFFECTIVENESS MEASURES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Effectiveness measures are concerned with the achievement of intended results, focusing on outputs regardless of inputs. They are often 'soft' measures that cannot be objectively quantified and are used to evaluate whether policy objectives are being achieved."</data>
      <data key="d2">cb50fc35976065bda7ad3244d6e4a9e0</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2257</data>
      <data key="d6">fb69850b34fc40b5927ff6e9a071b893</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ECONOMY MEASURES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Economy measures are concerned with inputs, focusing on minimizing the cost of resources used for an activity without compromising quality. An example is 'cost per member of staff'."</data>
      <data key="d2">cb50fc35976065bda7ad3244d6e4a9e0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2258</data>
      <data key="d6">681619fa47a44fe58dbd9653da819852</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EFFICIENCY MEASURES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Efficiency measures evaluate the relationship between inputs and outputs, aiming to maximize output with a given set of inputs or minimize inputs for a given level of output. An example is 'cost per hip-replacement operation'."</data>
      <data key="d2">cb50fc35976065bda7ad3244d6e4a9e0</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2259</data>
      <data key="d6">068275b6b9cc439db91171e16e02cfa4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERFORMANCE INDICATORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Performance indicators are metrics used to evaluate the performance of an organization. They provide insights when used comparatively, both within and between organizations, and can include measures of economy, efficiency, and effectiveness."</data>
      <data key="d2">cb50fc35976065bda7ad3244d6e4a9e0</data>
      <data key="d4">4</data>
      <data key="d5">2260</data>
      <data key="d6">c662735838ae4c31bf76da7ce0773746</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ANNUAL COST OF SERVICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Annual cost of service is a measure of economy since it is based on inputs. While a low cost may be favorable in terms of public funding, it may not produce an acceptable level of service."</data>
      <data key="d2">cb50fc35976065bda7ad3244d6e4a9e0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2261</data>
      <data key="d6">b051f4b35a4a4a6bb9463f3ce289f039</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;COST PER CALL-OUT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Cost per call-out is a measure of efficiency as it links inputs to outputs. Managers can improve this ratio by reducing costs and maximizing call-outs relative to fixed costs."</data>
      <data key="d2">cb50fc35976065bda7ad3244d6e4a9e0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2262</data>
      <data key="d6">ec83ca2feb3d4fd485661a893d8c648a</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERFORMANCE ASSESSMENT OF EATWELL RESTAURANT USING FITZGERALD AND MOON&#8217;S FRAMEWORK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The owners of Eatwell Restaurant have diversified business interests and have recorded various performance metrics since buying the restaurant in 20X1. These metrics include total meals served, regular customers, items on offer, reported cases of food poisoning, special theme evenings, operating hours, proposals and contracts for special events, customer feedback, and financial data."</data>
      <data key="d2">cb50fc35976065bda7ad3244d6e4a9e0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2263</data>
      <data key="d6">1423bff617bd4518b9460b8df005e752</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INNOVATION/FLEXIBILITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Innovation/Flexibility refers to the restaurant's ability to introduce new dishes, theme evenings, and catering activities for special events. It also considers the management of resources to meet peak demand levels."</data>
      <data key="d2">05e25a78a53e695fd01856df3a302292</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2264</data>
      <data key="d6">aad1c3d3934742da9c38e25d53c92dbc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EATWELL RESTAURANT'S PERFORMANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Eatwell Restaurant's performance is assessed using Fitzgerald and Moon's dimensions of performance, including financial performance, competitiveness, quality of service, innovation/flexibility, and resource utilization."</data>
      <data key="d2">05e25a78a53e695fd01856df3a302292</data>
      <data key="d4">6</data>
      <data key="d5">2265</data>
      <data key="d6">394e3ea2fdd047d3b996e34c40d77dab</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ADDITIONAL INFORMATION FOR PERFORMANCE ASSESSMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Additional information for performance assessment includes the value of assets, cost categories, capital investment details, business risk, national trends, customer surveys, intangible factors, and expert ratings."</data>
      <data key="d2">05e25a78a53e695fd01856df3a302292</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2266</data>
      <data key="d6">d1cda839af2a4b01bf8e2def8cc76668</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FITZGERALD AND MOON'S DIMENSIONS OF PERFORMANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0" />
      <data key="d1" />
      <data key="d2">05e25a78a53e695fd01856df3a302292</data>
      <data key="d4">5</data>
      <data key="d5">2267</data>
      <data key="d6">c89cf24c86c24da6b32115f5d137fb6d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OVERHEAD CONTROL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Overhead control involves managing and reducing indirect costs associated with running a business, such as administrative expenses, rent, and utilities. Effective overhead control can improve profitability."</data>
      <data key="d2">d0b8c2893afd98f99c4f5d857b8a7a02</data>
      <data key="d7">23</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2268</data>
      <data key="d6">f8ea20399549482a8021e5726ffef488</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;NET MARGIN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPTS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Net margin is the percentage of revenue remaining after all operating expenses, interest, taxes, and preferred stock dividends have been deducted from a company's total revenue. It measures overall profitability."</data>
      <data key="d2">d0b8c2893afd98f99c4f5d857b8a7a02</data>
      <data key="d7">23</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2269</data>
      <data key="d6">15211563a4244b5a8c220fc08a8a2a95</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FINANCIAL FORECAST FOR STORE S&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EXAMPLES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The financial forecast for Store S includes projected sales, gross profit, overheads, net profit, investment, and ROI over four years. It provides a detailed analysis of expected financial performance."</data>
      <data key="d2">d0b8c2893afd98f99c4f5d857b8a7a02</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2270</data>
      <data key="d6">e0369b17ad8141b286561ca978e5900b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MINIMUM SALES VOLUME FOR BONUS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The minimum sales volume required for a bonus in year four is calculated based on achieving a 15% ROI. This involves determining the necessary net profit and gross profit to meet the target ROI."</data>
      <data key="d2">d0b8c2893afd98f99c4f5d857b8a7a02</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2271</data>
      <data key="d6">f1979b9e9b164cd78409b5172713dae1</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FINANCIAL PERSPECTIVE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The financial perspective considers how the organization appears to shareholders and how it can create value for them. It focuses on three core financial themes: revenue growth and mix, cost reduction, and asset utilization."</data>
      <data key="d2">1d33c979d505d0dcd027d816d2ab2695</data>
      <data key="d7">4</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2272</data>
      <data key="d6">ad5fccc7817a4cbda9f38e8b6e38e897</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INTERNAL PERSPECTIVE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The internal perspective requires the organization to identify the internal business processes that are critical to the implementation of its strategy. It includes processes such as innovation, operations, and post-sales."</data>
      <data key="d2">1d33c979d505d0dcd027d816d2ab2695</data>
      <data key="d7">4</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2273</data>
      <data key="d6">adeb6c04dbc94fa89f12be0890058783</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LEARNING AND GROWTH PERSPECTIVE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FEATURES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The learning and growth perspective requires the organization to ask whether it can continue to improve and create value. It focuses on investing in infrastructure, such as people, systems, and organizational procedures, to support the other three perspectives."</data>
      <data key="d2">1d33c979d505d0dcd027d816d2ab2695</data>
      <data key="d7">4</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2274</data>
      <data key="d6">c8b5a1e240ea4b24af9b0648afbf9a98</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PERFORMANCE MEASUREMENT AND INVESTMENT DECISIONS: IMPLEMENTING THE BALANCED SCORECARD AND RESIDUAL INCOME APPROACHES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CASES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Brace Co, an electronics company specializing in home audio equipment, is exploring the balanced scorecard approach and residual income (RI) for performance measurement and investment decisions. The case involves calculating ROI and RI for two divisions and discussing the implications for decision-making and goal congruence."</data>
      <data key="d2">1d33c979d505d0dcd027d816d2ab2695</data>
      <data key="d7">23</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">3</data>
      <data key="d5">2275</data>
      <data key="d6">2c7929dd4cd14519986d49c66fd587a3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ACTIVITY BASED COSTING (ABC)&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"METHODOLOGIES"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Activity based costing (ABC) is a costing method that assigns overhead and indirect costs to related products and services by identifying cost drivers and allocating costs based on actual consumption."</data>
      <data key="d2">9eecb64d9d19d6470562caacce0026a3</data>
      <data key="d4">2</data>
      <data key="d5">2276</data>
      <data key="d6">a83ca9d52f3546a6916f3c067ddcc1c9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TRANSFER PRICE USING MACHINE HOURS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Transfer price using machine hours is calculated by allocating overhead costs based on machine hours instead of labor hours. The formula involves dividing total overhead costs by total machine hours to get the overhead absorption rate, then adding this to the material and labor costs, and finally adding a 10% mark-up."</data>
      <data key="d2">9eecb64d9d19d6470562caacce0026a3</data>
      <data key="d7">0</data>
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2277</data>
      <data key="d6">959fdcebb57e4973ba54c689d84de328</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TRANSFER PRICE USING ABC&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"FORMULAS"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Transfer price using ABC is calculated by allocating overhead costs based on multiple cost drivers such as production runs, machine hours, purchase orders, and deliveries. The formula involves dividing each overhead cost by its respective cost driver to get the cost per driver, then adding these to the material and labor costs, and finally adding a 10% mark-up."</data>
      <data key="d2">9eecb64d9d19d6470562caacce0026a3</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2278</data>
      <data key="d6">6959a8cb25714003b54d5416ddef0e78</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;EVALUATING TRANSFER PRICES AND PROFITABILITY USING COSTING METHODS&quot;">
      <data key="d0" />
      <data key="d1" />
      <data key="d2">9eecb64d9d19d6470562caacce0026a3</data>
      <data key="d4">1</data>
      <data key="d5">2279</data>
      <data key="d6">20da1e8ee8184f049cb4466b7af8fada</data>
    </node>
    <edge source="&quot;LOGICAL ACCESS CONTROLS&quot;" target="&quot;HACKING&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Logical access controls are measures to protect against hacking by preventing unauthorized access to data or software."</data>
      <data key="d11">9c567bb17d8b6e625f418a34b755de3d</data>
      <data key="d12">a60121d6000845a190d39cf3a1dfcc06</data>
      <data key="d13">0</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LOGICAL ACCESS CONTROLS&quot;" target="&quot;SOFTWARE AUDIT TRAIL&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Software audit trails are part of logical access controls, providing a record of transactions that can be inspected and verified to ensure data integrity."</data>
      <data key="d11">9c567bb17d8b6e625f418a34b755de3d</data>
      <data key="d12">73cfb178b67748cf972c8d50915858d3</data>
      <data key="d13">1</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LOGICAL ACCESS CONTROLS&quot;" target="&quot;LOGICAL ACCESS CONTROLS QUIZ&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Logical Access Controls Quiz tests knowledge on the primary purposes and components of logical access controls."</data>
      <data key="d11">9cb3ca1f088473aac339bd044b8a7507</data>
      <data key="d12">754751cd6f394a2c880c1ab59fdda234</data>
      <data key="d13">2</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LOGICAL ACCESS CONTROLS&quot;" target="&quot;IMPROVING SECURITY AND INTERNAL DISTRIBUTION PROCEDURES AT ST PEREGRINE'S HOSPITAL&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The case of Improving Security and Internal Distribution Procedures at St Peregrine's Hospital includes the implementation of logical access controls to ensure personnel can only access applications and data relevant to their job."</data>
      <data key="d11">dadf38de734316ede827c46363bb8d38</data>
      <data key="d12">97559cef37e540ef87c4995aafc07c19</data>
      <data key="d13">3</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PASSWORDS&quot;" target="&quot;HACKING&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Hacking can involve password cracking, which is an attempt to gain unauthorized access by repeatedly trying different passwords."</data>
      <data key="d11">9c567bb17d8b6e625f418a34b755de3d</data>
      <data key="d12">bfa842ec33284d0da30813375ac0d70e</data>
      <data key="d13">4</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;HACKING&quot;" target="&quot;ENCRYPTION&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Encryption helps protect data from being accessed or understood by hackers."</data>
      <data key="d11">9c567bb17d8b6e625f418a34b755de3d</data>
      <data key="d12">070ab578bb644bf589745af18bcc046c</data>
      <data key="d13">5</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;INTERNAL SOURCES OF MANAGEMENT INFORMATION&quot;" target="&quot;USE OF INFORMATION IN CONTROL&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Internal sources of management information provide the detailed data needed for tactical and operational control purposes."</data>
      <data key="d11">d4fd6778c3735e1144e70c31e7a057e5</data>
      <data key="d12">2fcaf36db51446c4a84579ce0a43c9d1</data>
      <data key="d13">6</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;INTERNAL SOURCES OF MANAGEMENT INFORMATION&quot;" target="&quot;ACCOUNTING SYSTEM&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The accounting system is a component of internal sources of management information."</data>
      <data key="d11">d4fd6778c3735e1144e70c31e7a057e5</data>
      <data key="d12">c53492798f8f4ef1a928cf7f83155ba4</data>
      <data key="d13">7</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;INTERNAL SOURCES OF MANAGEMENT INFORMATION&quot;" target="&quot;INVENTORY SYSTEM&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The inventory system is a component of internal sources of management information."</data>
      <data key="d11">d4fd6778c3735e1144e70c31e7a057e5</data>
      <data key="d12">06eeb06d208344d5ade357b69716060d</data>
      <data key="d13">8</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;INTERNAL SOURCES OF MANAGEMENT INFORMATION&quot;" target="&quot;PAYROLL SYSTEM&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The payroll system is a component of internal sources of management information."</data>
      <data key="d11">d4fd6778c3735e1144e70c31e7a057e5</data>
      <data key="d12">a00230ee29a9433ea997e025a85341ed</data>
      <data key="d13">9</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;INTERNAL SOURCES OF MANAGEMENT INFORMATION&quot;" target="&quot;PURCHASE PROCESSING SYSTEM&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The purchase processing system is a component of internal sources of management information."</data>
      <data key="d11">d4fd6778c3735e1144e70c31e7a057e5</data>
      <data key="d12">7c77388a55bd4c6bb4b0e61be7a51ab5</data>
      <data key="d13">10</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;INTERNAL SOURCES OF MANAGEMENT INFORMATION&quot;" target="&quot;SALES PROCESSING SYSTEM&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The sales processing system is a component of internal sources of management information."</data>
      <data key="d11">d4fd6778c3735e1144e70c31e7a057e5</data>
      <data key="d12">0b141ba1eb8f4ccfbeebaaa1d1a48701</data>
      <data key="d13">11</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;INTERNAL SOURCES OF MANAGEMENT INFORMATION&quot;" target="&quot;QUALITATIVE INFORMATION SYSTEMS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Qualitative information systems are a component of internal sources of management information."</data>
      <data key="d11">d4fd6778c3735e1144e70c31e7a057e5</data>
