      <data key="d10">"Reverse engineering is another term for tear down analysis, which involves examining a competitor's product to identify possible improvements or cost reductions."</data>
      <data key="d11">40bae0e7483c94ad06bd066f12884d9c</data>
      <data key="d12">03f7b785582c4c908a3c6921b966e17f</data>
      <data key="d13">271</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;VALUE ENGINEERING&quot;" target="&quot;FUNCTIONAL ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Value engineering and functional analysis both aim to improve product design and reduce costs by focusing on the value provided to the customer."</data>
      <data key="d11">40bae0e7483c94ad06bd066f12884d9c</data>
      <data key="d12">d82b496526494c42aff25881e3334990</data>
      <data key="d13">272</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;VALUE ENGINEERING&quot;" target="&quot;COST REDUCTION&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Value engineering aims to achieve cost reduction by improving the design of a product to provide the same functions at a lower cost or by eliminating functions that do not add value."</data>
      <data key="d11">40bae0e7483c94ad06bd066f12884d9c</data>
      <data key="d12">04d314f5b5c54c1d8a7c2c7f937b763b</data>
      <data key="d13">273</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;VALUE ENGINEERING&quot;" target="&quot;PRODUCT DESIGN&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Value engineering involves improving product design to reduce costs while maintaining or enhancing the value provided to the customer."</data>
      <data key="d11">40bae0e7483c94ad06bd066f12884d9c</data>
      <data key="d12">9bd6eb7ac3ac48b8ae411e0297cccbd2</data>
      <data key="d13">274</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;FUNCTIONAL ANALYSIS&quot;" target="&quot;PRODUCT DESIGN&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Functional analysis helps in product design by identifying the attributes/functions of a product that customers value, ensuring that the design focuses on these aspects."</data>
      <data key="d11">40bae0e7483c94ad06bd066f12884d9c</data>
      <data key="d12">ce35f1fea9ad4f86adf106926b87881f</data>
      <data key="d13">275</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PRODUCT LIFECYCLE&quot;" target="&quot;COMPETITORS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Competitors can influence the pricing strategies adopted at different stages of the Product Lifecycle."</data>
      <data key="d11">c1d1a5691f5cfea1fd89ecd71a3421ce</data>
      <data key="d12">100a090dde6f425da359f0fcad8f8d9c</data>
      <data key="d13">276</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PRODUCT LIFECYCLE&quot;" target="&quot;CUSTOMERS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Customer behavior and preferences can influence the pricing strategies adopted at different stages of the Product Lifecycle."</data>
      <data key="d11">c1d1a5691f5cfea1fd89ecd71a3421ce</data>
      <data key="d12">ed16d9c60425458e9e4bf94466918515</data>
      <data key="d13">277</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PRODUCT LIFECYCLE&quot;" target="&quot;PERFECT COMPETITION&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"In a Perfect Competition market, the Product Lifecycle stages can be influenced by the presence of many sellers and buyers, and identical products."</data>
      <data key="d11">c1d1a5691f5cfea1fd89ecd71a3421ce</data>
      <data key="d12">751401e914b54492944575c90c8cfc3b</data>
      <data key="d13">278</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;BOTTLENECK IDENTIFICATION&quot;" target="&quot;EXPLOITING BOTTLENECKS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Bottleneck Identification is followed by Exploiting Bottlenecks to determine which products to make given the bottlenecks."</data>
      <data key="d11">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d12">938716c72c5a46849c529aeabc570944</data>
      <data key="d13">279</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;EXPLOITING BOTTLENECKS&quot;" target="&quot;SUBORDINATION TO BOTTLENECKS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Exploiting Bottlenecks is followed by Subordination to Bottlenecks to ensure other resources do not produce at a higher rate than the bottleneck."</data>
      <data key="d11">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d12">fe3c53c70c9848cc9d6328b9d4396ff6</data>
      <data key="d13">280</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;SUBORDINATION TO BOTTLENECKS&quot;" target="&quot;ELEVATING BOTTLENECKS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Subordination to Bottlenecks is followed by Elevating Bottlenecks to increase production capacity."</data>
      <data key="d11">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d12">c154973be3cd4158b24ed7b54a2f38ae</data>
      <data key="d13">281</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;ELEVATING BOTTLENECKS&quot;" target="&quot;CONTINUOUS IMPROVEMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Elevating Bottlenecks is followed by Continuous Improvement to return to bottleneck identification once a new constraint is broken."</data>
      <data key="d11">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d12">1548ac7f3b2d4b56a190261ef23b84d7</data>
      <data key="d13">282</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;THROUGHPUT CONTRIBUTION&quot;" target="&quot;LIMITING FACTOR ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Throughput Contribution is used in Limiting Factor Analysis to prioritize products that generate maximum throughput contribution per bottleneck hour."</data>
      <data key="d11">1f7a550d089ceb3dbcb11ef3bde8fa37</data>
      <data key="d12">313aa8ecadf14a74a5fdbd19ef3cc103</data>
      <data key="d13">283</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
