    <edge source="&quot;RELEVANT COSTS&quot;" target="&quot;INCREMENTAL COSTS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">3.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Relevant Costs" are costs that are pertinent to a specific decision-making process. Among these, "Incremental Costs" are a specific type of relevant cost that are directly influenced by the decision at hand. In essence, all incremental costs are relevant costs, but not all relevant costs are necessarily incremental.</data>
      <data key="d11">2b7c12bc08e4dff98f807210499e82ee,836c03bc0c3a85400d4d39d4278e3a51</data>
      <data key="d12">4628a045967d4224b8e3d527be38b1f1</data>
      <data key="d13">344</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
