    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;RELEVANT COST&quot;" target="&quot;MATERIALS FOR ONE-OFF CONTRACT&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Relevant cost is a key concept in determining the Materials for one-off contract.""Materials for one-off contract involves the concept of Relevant cost."</data>
      <data key="d11">7b2509b146e3ce8701f02f8110248a43</data>
      <data key="d12">f8e0d5e92cec447e8807b28413479ae1</data>
      <data key="d13">364</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;RELEVANT COST&quot;" target="&quot;REPLACEMENT COST&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Replacement cost is a type of Relevant cost used when materials are regularly used in the business and need to be replenished."</data>
      <data key="d11">7b2509b146e3ce8701f02f8110248a43</data>
      <data key="d12">983cc505147a494bbbde48e2dfd7d53a</data>
      <data key="d13">365</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;RELEVANT COST&quot;" target="&quot;SCRAP VALUE&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Scrap value is considered as the Relevant cost when materials are not used regularly and could be sold off instead."</data>
      <data key="d11">7b2509b146e3ce8701f02f8110248a43</data>
      <data key="d12">61e4ac57c4084897a8cea5eeb7c0b26d</data>
      <data key="d13">366</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;RELEVANT COST&quot;" target="&quot;CURRENT MARKET PRICE&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Current market price is used as the Relevant cost for materials that have not yet been acquired for a one-off contract."</data>
      <data key="d11">7b2509b146e3ce8701f02f8110248a43</data>
      <data key="d12">88e0c2cf5ea84352848d0a37fa5ad981</data>
      <data key="d13">367</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;RELEVANT COST&quot;" target="&quot;INVENTORY LEVELS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Inventory levels help determine whether existing materials can be used or if new materials need to be purchased, affecting the Relevant cost."</data>
      <data key="d11">7b2509b146e3ce8701f02f8110248a43</data>
      <data key="d12">6387e97c1238486eb2d4968d91a0d7f3</data>
      <data key="d13">368</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;RELEVANT COST&quot;" target="&quot;ALTERNATIVE USES&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Alternative uses help determine the Opportunity cost, which is a type of Relevant cost."</data>
