    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;FURTHER PROCESSING DECISION QUIZ&quot;" target="&quot;INCREMENTAL REVENUE&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The Further Processing Decision Quiz involves calculating incremental revenue, which is the additional revenue from further processing a product beyond the split-off point."</data>
      <data key="d11">f48e76ebf07d8d7de318d46534f42fd9</data>
      <data key="d12">ea2f9d76eddb4e719b2b442c9fd6e38a</data>
      <data key="d13">420</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;OUTSOURCING&quot;" target="&quot;ADVANTAGES OF OUTSOURCING&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Outsourcing includes several advantages such as lower cost, services becoming a variable cost, management focus on core competencies, higher quality from specialist suppliers, and access to a broader range of expertise."</data>
      <data key="d11">f48e76ebf07d8d7de318d46534f42fd9</data>
      <data key="d12">06ed0fbcbf3d4c2fa60bc74714f6d6b1</data>
      <data key="d13">421</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;OUTSOURCING&quot;" target="&quot;DISADVANTAGES OF OUTSOURCING&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Outsourcing includes several disadvantages such as reliance on a third party, loss of control, hidden costs, potential quality issues, operational dependence on the outsourcing company's financial stability, and potential workforce demotivation."</data>
      <data key="d11">f48e76ebf07d8d7de318d46534f42fd9</data>
      <data key="d12">9a097ba8ddc44b35ad4f2ff7971c2da1</data>
      <data key="d13">422</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;OUTSOURCING&quot;" target="&quot;MAKE VS. BUY DECISIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Make vs. Buy Decisions are related to outsourcing as they involve deciding whether to outsource the manufacture of a particular component based on financial impact."</data>
      <data key="d11">f48e76ebf07d8d7de318d46534f42fd9</data>
      <data key="d12">14f3ab90255448a5b046bc701b6d4235</data>
      <data key="d13">423</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;OUTSOURCING&quot;" target="&quot;QUIZ: LINEAR PROGRAMMING PROBLEM&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Outsourcing is related to the concept of optimizing resource allocation, which is a key aspect of linear programming problems."</data>
      <data key="d11">fd88b98a3550ab4e5c7f37314520bc3a</data>
      <data key="d12">6b132efcd1704d4ab2941da06cb93d1e</data>
      <data key="d13">424</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;OUTSOURCING&quot;" target="&quot;QUIZ: OPTIMAL MIX OF PRODUCTION&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Outsourcing decisions can impact the optimal mix of production, as it involves determining the best allocation of resources to maximize profit."</data>
      <data key="d11">fd88b98a3550ab4e5c7f37314520bc3a</data>
      <data key="d12">0b6d8054fda444c3ad175d11cf5132c4</data>
      <data key="d13">425</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;OUTSOURCING&quot;" target="&quot;QUIZ: LIMITING FACTORS IN PRODUCTION&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Outsourcing can be a strategy to address limiting factors in production, such as material and labor constraints."</data>
      <data key="d11">fd88b98a3550ab4e5c7f37314520bc3a</data>
      <data key="d12">09a4de99661048e9a66e4cd57b832186</data>
      <data key="d13">426</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;OUTSOURCING&quot;" target="&quot;DISPLAY SCREENS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Outsourcing involves comparing the cost of buying display screens from a supplier to the in-house production costs."</data>
      <data key="d11">5c4312b5c5c803bc38cc120660340db3</data>
      <data key="d12">799f43f9c2354ccdb1357e3d80bb0c53</data>
      <data key="d13">427</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;OUTSOURCING&quot;" target="&quot;KEYPADS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Outsourcing involves comparing the cost of buying keypads from a supplier to the in-house production costs."</data>
      <data key="d11">5c4312b5c5c803bc38cc120660340db3</data>
      <data key="d12">eb14eeb318b14f16bc7903c56488fafe</data>
      <data key="d13">428</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;ADVANTAGES OF OUTSOURCING&quot;" target="&quot;VARIABLE COST&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"One advantage of outsourcing is that services become a variable cost, which varies directly with the level of production or service provision."</data>
      <data key="d11">f48e76ebf07d8d7de318d46534f42fd9</data>
      <data key="d12">aab688459e89489dae358b5acdf855c6</data>
      <data key="d13">429</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;ADVANTAGES OF OUTSOURCING&quot;" target="&quot;CORE COMPETENCIES&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Outsourcing allows management to focus on core competencies, which are the main strengths or strategic advantages of a business."</data>
      <data key="d11">f48e76ebf07d8d7de318d46534f42fd9</data>
      <data key="d12">a5a0a05505364a559e8133fe48711b26</data>
      <data key="d13">430</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;SPLIT-OFF POINT&quot;" target="&quot;COMMON COST&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Costs incurred up to the split-off point are considered common costs, which are not relevant to further processing decisions but are relevant to determining overall process viability."</data>
      <data key="d11">f48e76ebf07d8d7de318d46534f42fd9</data>
      <data key="d12">bab9ae79fe824904a5129ce8c7163159</data>
      <data key="d13">431</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;VARIABLE COST&quot;" target="&quot;CONTRIBUTION PER UNIT&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Variable cost is subtracted from the selling price per unit to calculate the contribution per unit."</data>
      <data key="d11">e6f7ca658dc25c9178113951c7a31846</data>
      <data key="d12">bd3b9a9c0af745aca265e12789f6a8ad</data>
      <data key="d13">432</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;VARIABLE COST&quot;" target="&quot;CONTRIBUTION PER CUSTOMER&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Variable cost subtracted from sales revenue gives the contribution per customer."</data>
      <data key="d11">4435163b259d1a0d68e055b03df87004</data>
      <data key="d12">74fff39eac584c60a2910cc76bc572e0</data>
      <data key="d13">433</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;BREAKEVEN POINT&quot;" target="&quot;CONTRIBUTION&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Breakeven point is determined when total Contribution equals total fixed costs."</data>
      <data key="d11">98d761e221e6915f156753807cb8fbe1</data>
      <data key="d12">33b9b5e0f8da40ea89b05c9ab5355bb0</data>
      <data key="d13">434</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;BREAKEVEN POINT&quot;" target="&quot;BREAKEVEN CHART&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Breakeven chart visually represents the Breakeven point where total cost and revenue lines intersect."</data>
      <data key="d11">98d761e221e6915f156753807cb8fbe1</data>
      <data key="d12">b24cb4da575f427cad153c2974464e5e</data>
      <data key="d13">435</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;BREAKEVEN POINT&quot;" target="&quot;EXAMPLE OF DEPENDENCE ON SALES VOLUME&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The Example of Dependence on Sales Volume illustrates how to calculate the Breakeven point for Company A."</data>
      <data key="d11">98d761e221e6915f156753807cb8fbe1</data>
      <data key="d12">c70a904a968b412889bb8c3065d07df3</data>
      <data key="d13">436</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;BREAKEVEN POINT&quot;" target="&quot;MARGIN OF SAFETY&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Margin of safety measures the risk of falling below the Breakeven point by comparing actual or projected sales to the Breakeven sales volume."</data>
      <data key="d11">98d761e221e6915f156753807cb8fbe1</data>
      <data key="d12">fd70e576312442118ebaaa8bfc5e03dd</data>
      <data key="d13">437</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;BREAKEVEN POINT&quot;" target="&quot;BREAKEVEN POINT FORMULA&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The breakeven point is calculated using the breakeven point formula."</data>
      <data key="d11">08f6c24c7f87b7ffc3b8a5dfc505c552</data>
      <data key="d12">5dd112b6718847d6871f0a1b4e4ae378</data>
      <data key="d13">438</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;BREAKEVEN POINT&quot;" target="&quot;BREAKEVEN REVENUE&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Breakeven point is related to breakeven revenue as both are used to determine the level of sales needed to cover costs."</data>
      <data key="d11">08f6c24c7f87b7ffc3b8a5dfc505c552</data>
      <data key="d12">c0092c049c6044628d4941fa37c814df</data>
      <data key="d13">439</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;BREAKEVEN POINT&quot;" target="&quot;SUMMARY OF CVP ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Breakeven point is included in the Summary of CVP Analysis."</data>
      <data key="d11">08f6c24c7f87b7ffc3b8a5dfc505c552</data>
      <data key="d12">41799e2431614876a11fb872c387a65f</data>
      <data key="d13">440</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CONTRIBUTION&quot;" target="&quot;CVP ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"CVP analysis uses Contribution to determine the funds available to cover fixed costs and calculate profit."</data>
      <data key="d11">98d761e221e6915f156753807cb8fbe1</data>
      <data key="d12">8ccdda4685fc4a00bf2fa13c5d231375</data>
      <data key="d13">441</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CONTRIBUTION&quot;" target="&quot;SALES PRICE PER UNIT&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Sales price per unit is used to calculate revenue, which, after deducting variable costs, determines the Contribution."</data>
      <data key="d11">98d761e221e6915f156753807cb8fbe1</data>
      <data key="d12">6e920d6be7354ed9b380b3bb7b433dff</data>
      <data key="d13">442</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CONTRIBUTION&quot;" target="&quot;TOTAL CONTRIBUTION&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Contribution is related to Total contribution."</data>
      <data key="d11">23de7e5f5aa4638cfdebaec8afd6c5de</data>
      <data key="d12">44619429a8ee49f5b646479a33089e02</data>
      <data key="d13">443</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CONTRIBUTION&quot;" target="&quot;GROUP PROFITS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Contribution from external sales impacts group profits."</data>
      <data key="d11">34f2c5c9d893c1b631ed1646193eebf4</data>
      <data key="d12">f14dc4a6b9af432d8cd5dfa297e7e867</data>
      <data key="d13">444</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CONTRIBUTION&quot;" target="&quot;ROLLING BUDGET FOR THE NEXT FOUR QUARTERS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Contribution is a key component in the rolling budget for the next four quarters."</data>
      <data key="d11">2df3be986166cb71a016998a16e5349a</data>
      <data key="d12">7012273bd53446faa2ef77426d5bfbd7</data>
      <data key="d13">445</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CONTRIBUTION TO SALES RATIO&quot;" target="&quot;CVP ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"CVP analysis involves calculating the Contribution to sales ratio to assess profitability in single and multi-product situations."</data>
      <data key="d11">98d761e221e6915f156753807cb8fbe1</data>
      <data key="d12">8e359c7a548041f584dde64fe396f3b6</data>
      <data key="d13">446</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CONTRIBUTION TO SALES RATIO&quot;" target="&quot;MULTI-PRODUCT PROFIT-VOLUME ANALYSIS FOR HAIR CO'S ELECTRICAL GOODS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The Multi-Product Profit-Volume Analysis for Hair Co's Electrical Goods involves calculating the contribution to sales ratio for each product."</data>
      <data key="d11">a5995fbeaf1e8bc061f219d79f9689d1</data>
