    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;BREAKEVEN REVENUE FORMULA&quot;" target="&quot;FIXED COST&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">The breakeven revenue formula is a financial calculation that utilizes fixed costs as a key component. Specifically, breakeven revenue is determined by dividing fixed costs by the contribution-to-sales (C/S) ratio. This formula helps businesses understand the revenue needed to cover all fixed costs, ensuring no profit or loss.</data>
      <data key="d11">abd4a68d8185b413e829914bc2f86480,e6f7ca658dc25c9178113951c7a31846</data>
      <data key="d12">9303169e5fdb464a81a0d3b85a3be08f</data>
      <data key="d13">484</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;BREAKEVEN REVENUE FORMULA&quot;" target="&quot;WEIGHTED AVERAGE C/S RATIO&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">The breakeven revenue formula utilizes the weighted average C/S ratio in its calculation. Specifically, the weighted average C/S ratio is employed in the breakeven revenue formula for multi-product situations.</data>
      <data key="d11">abd4a68d8185b413e829914bc2f86480,e6f7ca658dc25c9178113951c7a31846</data>
      <data key="d12">79767a32e08c421dafc2ba14b4498f33</data>
      <data key="d13">485</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
