      <data key="d9">3.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"FIXED OVERHEAD EXPENDITURE VARIANCE" and "FIXED OVERHEAD VOLUME VARIANCE" are both types of fixed overhead variances. They are related to fixed overheads and involve comparisons between actual and budgeted figures. However, they measure different aspects: the expenditure variance focuses on cost differences, while the volume variance focuses on production differences.</data>
