    <edge source="&quot;DECENTRALISATION&quot;" target="&quot;BENEFITS OF DECENTRALISATION&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Decentralisation provides several benefits including strategic focus for senior management and faster decision-making."</data>
      <data key="d11">421ca5734d703d01e7e43fa8cb11733f</data>
      <data key="d12">9a5996d9d6584d568b3a07f9f65c01ae</data>
      <data key="d13">1147</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;DECENTRALISATION&quot;" target="&quot;PROBLEMS OF DECENTRALISATION&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Decentralisation can lead to problems such as lack of goal congruence and increased information requirements."</data>
      <data key="d11">421ca5734d703d01e7e43fa8cb11733f</data>
      <data key="d12">13c93826825245af8efb10c56670fbd2</data>
      <data key="d13">1148</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;DECENTRALISATION&quot;" target="&quot;CONDITIONS FOR SUCCESSFUL DECENTRALISATION&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Successful decentralisation requires carefully designed performance evaluation systems and central policies to integrate and control."</data>
      <data key="d11">421ca5734d703d01e7e43fa8cb11733f</data>
      <data key="d12">fa442e30e6d84ee7aa05464246a9547e</data>
      <data key="d13">1149</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;DECENTRALISATION&quot;" target="&quot;DIVISIONAL PERFORMANCE MEASURES&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Decentralisation impacts the effectiveness of Divisional Performance Measures."</data>
      <data key="d11">4e87d1e76027b0ff68b56a7c9c9c92c1</data>
      <data key="d12">7783c6e4f8bc498399d54dab5837cd3b</data>
      <data key="d13">1150</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;MEASUREMENT CHARACTERISTICS&quot;" target="&quot;POSSIBLE MEASURES FOR DIVISIONAL PERFORMANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Measurement characteristics guide the selection of possible measures for divisional performance."</data>
      <data key="d11">421ca5734d703d01e7e43fa8cb11733f</data>
      <data key="d12">4122a8c01d6d43b0ba71e13de8ef9478</data>
      <data key="d13">1151</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;POSSIBLE MEASURES FOR DIVISIONAL PERFORMANCE&quot;" target="&quot;RATIO ANALYSIS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Ratio analysis is one of the possible measures for evaluating divisional performance."</data>
      <data key="d11">421ca5734d703d01e7e43fa8cb11733f</data>
      <data key="d12">3be9f79a3d7e43c58013b845f6c275c2</data>
      <data key="d13">1152</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;POSSIBLE MEASURES FOR DIVISIONAL PERFORMANCE&quot;" target="&quot;NON-FINANCIAL MEASURES&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Non-financial measures are one of the possible measures for evaluating divisional performance."</data>
      <data key="d11">421ca5734d703d01e7e43fa8cb11733f</data>
      <data key="d12">385435b1487a4bada71bb1ea0404ca45</data>
      <data key="d13">1153</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;DIVISION Y&quot;" target="&quot;INVESTMENT DECISIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Division Y's investment decision involves evaluating a project with an ROI of 11%, which is above its current ROI of 9%, leading to an acceptance of the project."</data>
      <data key="d11">6cd8b16b5edca25e8d811b4efcefe5fb</data>
      <data key="d12">90f34fafa5d7418cba96d20b7715152a</data>
      <data key="d13">1154</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;INVESTMENT DECISIONS&quot;" target="&quot;GOAL CONGRUENCE&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Investment decisions are evaluated for goal congruence to ensure they align with the organisation's primary objective of maximising shareholders' wealth."</data>
      <data key="d11">6cd8b16b5edca25e8d811b4efcefe5fb</data>
      <data key="d12">39f043952c954db9b494df1c777868dd</data>
      <data key="d13">1155</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;GOAL CONGRUENCE&quot;" target="&quot;OBJECTIVES OF TRANSFER PRICING&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Goal Congruence is one of the Objectives of Transfer Pricing."</data>
      <data key="d11">4e87d1e76027b0ff68b56a7c9c9c92c1</data>
      <data key="d12">0c559308289e4692b13f3fae566937b2</data>
      <data key="d13">1156</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;GOAL CONGRUENCE&quot;" target="&quot;EXAMPLE OF GOAL CONGRUENCE&quot;">
      <data key="d9">2.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"GOAL CONGRUENCE" refers to the alignment of objectives among different members or units within an organization, ensuring that all efforts are directed towards achieving the overall goals of the organization. An "EXAMPLE OF GOAL CONGRUENCE" is a practical illustration that demonstrates this concept. However, the example of ABC Consulting is cited as a situation of goal incongruence, which underscores the significance of achieving goal congruence. This example highlights the challenges and potential issues that arise when goals are not aligned, thereby emphasizing the importance of striving for goal congruence within any organization.</data>
      <data key="d11">0622f4f26dbe7479c871198b2e72b940,4e87d1e76027b0ff68b56a7c9c9c92c1</data>
      <data key="d12">a45c8a52387643689a9eebfa6ebae68c</data>
      <data key="d13">1157</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;GOAL CONGRUENCE&quot;" target="&quot;TRANSFER PRICING&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Achieving goal congruence is a primary objective of a transfer pricing system."</data>
      <data key="d11">0622f4f26dbe7479c871198b2e72b940</data>
      <data key="d12">4d0ef11d4d4548ad8809c13abad52b95</data>
      <data key="d13">1158</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;ADVANTAGES OF ROI&quot;" target="&quot;ROI&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Advantages of ROI include ease of comparison between divisions, focus on scarce capital resources, encouragement of reduction in non-essential investment, and easily understood percentages."</data>
      <data key="d11">6cd8b16b5edca25e8d811b4efcefe5fb</data>
      <data key="d12">b3b1d330f17247f784a3d50363ab2cb5</data>
      <data key="d13">1159</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;DISADVANTAGES OF ROI&quot;" target="&quot;ROI&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Disadvantages of ROI include the risk of dysfunctional decision-making, subjective definition of capital employed, potential increase in ROI over time due to depreciation, and risk of window-dressing."</data>
      <data key="d11">6cd8b16b5edca25e8d811b4efcefe5fb</data>
      <data key="d12">e9f3782d90ec4512ae560b4ce12a8fcb</data>
      <data key="d13">1160</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;RESIDUAL INCOME (RI)&quot;" target="&quot;IMPUTED INTEREST&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Residual income (RI) is calculated by deducting imputed interest from pre-tax profit."</data>
      <data key="d11">6cd8b16b5edca25e8d811b4efcefe5fb</data>
      <data key="d12">861b6cda68e3455a815d35f7216e6074</data>
      <data key="d13">1161</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
