    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;SUPPLYING DIVISION PERSPECTIVE&quot;" target="&quot;SCENARIO 1 - OPPORTUNITY COST IS ZERO&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Scenario 1 illustrates the supplying division's perspective when the opportunity cost is zero."</data>
      <data key="d11">0622f4f26dbe7479c871198b2e72b940</data>
      <data key="d12">6a63bf5ea1c14c4186203878537c90e1</data>
      <data key="d13">1190</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;SUPPLYING DIVISION PERSPECTIVE&quot;" target="&quot;SCENARIO 2 - OPPORTUNITY COST ARISES&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Scenario 2 illustrates the supplying division's perspective when an opportunity cost arises."</data>
      <data key="d11">0622f4f26dbe7479c871198b2e72b940</data>
      <data key="d12">0dc6a7b9859f40378b64a826f10c3d70</data>
      <data key="d13">1191</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;SCENARIO 1 - OPPORTUNITY COST IS ZERO&quot;" target="&quot;QUIZ: NO OPPORTUNITY COST&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The quiz on no opportunity cost is based on Scenario 1 where the opportunity cost is zero."</data>
      <data key="d11">0622f4f26dbe7479c871198b2e72b940</data>
      <data key="d12">e2cb0d4914c1477688f73ea6a8e028e6</data>
      <data key="d13">1192</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;SCENARIO 2 - OPPORTUNITY COST ARISES&quot;" target="&quot;QUIZ: WITH OPPORTUNITY COST&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The quiz on opportunity cost is based on Scenario 2 where an opportunity cost arises."</data>
      <data key="d11">0622f4f26dbe7479c871198b2e72b940</data>
      <data key="d12">6f12645b813b4e8c917a4e3ce77247c3</data>
      <data key="d13">1193</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;MARKET PRICE METHOD&quot;" target="&quot;ADVANTAGES OF MARKET PRICE METHOD&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The Market Price Method has advantages such as being optimal for goal congruence if the selling division is at full capacity and encouraging efficiency."</data>
      <data key="d11">e96e3681999d08ff8797d8716ea0a5c3</data>
      <data key="d12">016a2b872c5741ad99b89b92aabc09c1</data>
      <data key="d13">1194</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;MARKET PRICE METHOD&quot;" target="&quot;DISADVANTAGES OF MARKET PRICE METHOD&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The Market Price Method has disadvantages such as being only possible if a perfectly competitive external market exists and market prices may fluctuate."</data>
      <data key="d11">e96e3681999d08ff8797d8716ea0a5c3</data>
      <data key="d12">d5d7f9df69b346f781e5ab301f42d97b</data>
      <data key="d13">1195</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;FULL COST PLUS METHOD&quot;" target="&quot;ADVANTAGES OF FULL COST PLUS METHOD&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The Full Cost Plus Method has advantages such as being easy to calculate if a standard costing system exists, covering all costs of the selling division, and approximating to market price."</data>
      <data key="d11">e96e3681999d08ff8797d8716ea0a5c3</data>
      <data key="d12">27b4f8b006d54a62afdef25f8afdd7dc</data>
      <data key="d13">1196</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;FULL COST PLUS METHOD&quot;" target="&quot;DISADVANTAGES OF FULL COST PLUS METHOD&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The Full Cost Plus Method has disadvantages such as leading to dysfunctional decisions as the fixed costs of the selling division become the variable costs of the buying division, and the markup is arbitrary."</data>
      <data key="d11">e96e3681999d08ff8797d8716ea0a5c3</data>
      <data key="d12">1892d7a5274f45eeba702c20b99d1b4f</data>
      <data key="d13">1197</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;FULL COST PLUS METHOD&quot;" target="&quot;EXAMPLE OF COST-BASED APPROACHES&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The Example of Cost-based Approaches includes the Full Cost Plus Method."</data>
      <data key="d11">e96e3681999d08ff8797d8716ea0a5c3</data>
      <data key="d12">0e748fdc6a9f495eafbebab84da29d5c</data>
      <data key="d13">1198</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;FULL COST PLUS METHOD&quot;" target="&quot;INTERNAL SALES&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"The full cost plus method is used to set transfer prices for internal sales."</data>
      <data key="d11">34f2c5c9d893c1b631ed1646193eebf4</data>
      <data key="d12">e7256de1caaa45adb34110b64632f7af</data>
      <data key="d13">1199</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
