    <edge source="&quot;PARTICIPATIVE BUDGETING&quot;" target="&quot;ADVANTAGES OF PARTICIPATIVE BUDGETING&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Advantages of participative budgeting include increased ownership and accountability, better information sharing, and more realistic budgets."</data>
      <data key="d11">ed11d697d920edcbfc6a01ce2c257056</data>
      <data key="d12">6fe7bc74c2f5457f95dc1c4fb4fa8b55</data>
      <data key="d13">1633</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PARTICIPATIVE BUDGETING&quot;" target="&quot;DISADVANTAGES OF PARTICIPATIVE BUDGETING&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Disadvantages of participative budgeting include potential for budgetary slack, time-consuming process, and possible conflicts among managers."</data>
      <data key="d11">ed11d697d920edcbfc6a01ce2c257056</data>
      <data key="d12">1969c8534d4b4e2f82b9af919c7a1150</data>
      <data key="d13">1634</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PARTICIPATIVE BUDGETING&quot;" target="&quot;YUMI CO'S BUDGETING PROCESS&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Participative budgeting is suggested as an alternative to Yumi Co's current top-down budgeting process to make budgets more effective and realistic."</data>
      <data key="d11">6cf39866faa0b75b5fd5a86e16914122</data>
      <data key="d12">bfe0df19643b4b4d90f83ceed63cf92d</data>
      <data key="d13">1635</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PARTICIPATIVE BUDGETING&quot;" target="&quot;CO-ORDINATION OF ACTIVITIES&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Participative budgeting requires co-ordination of activities across different departments and management levels to ensure everyone is aware of the overall plan."</data>
      <data key="d11">dcff42ba3ed5843954c648603089a728</data>
      <data key="d12">85d81499ebda41e0b11ad0fee2da10a5</data>
      <data key="d13">1636</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PARTICIPATIVE BUDGETING&quot;" target="&quot;COMMUNICATION&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Participative budgeting enhances communication by involving all levels of management in the budgeting process, ensuring everyone understands the plan and any changes."</data>
      <data key="d11">dcff42ba3ed5843954c648603089a728</data>
      <data key="d12">6386b39de6344b009a4f0f50ae5acb9c</data>
      <data key="d13">1637</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PARTICIPATIVE BUDGETING&quot;" target="&quot;SYSTEM OF CONTROL&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Participative budgeting helps establish a system of control by comparing actual results to budgeted figures and investigating differences, although it is open to abuse through budgetary slack."</data>
      <data key="d11">dcff42ba3ed5843954c648603089a728</data>
      <data key="d12">9073628b7d4d48828cbd15a3e5f99825</data>
      <data key="d13">1638</data>
      <data key="d14">0</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PARTICIPATIVE BUDGETING&quot;" target="&quot;PERFORMANCE EVALUATION&quot;">
      <data key="d9">1.0</data>
      <data key="d10">"Participative budgeting is effective for performance evaluation if the participation is genuine and free from budgetary slack, as it compares actual results to budgeted results."</data>
      <data key="d11">dcff42ba3ed5843954c648603089a728</data>
      <data key="d12">83a774435411423ca4561f0cf9983659</data>
      <data key="d13">1639</data>
